"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite=globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite||[]).push([[792],{69935(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"rentiva-v4.37.1-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.37.1-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-05-05-rentiva-v4.37.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-05-rentiva-v4.37.1-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.37.1 \u2014 Vendor profile hotfix","description":"Three smoke-test findings on the freshly-shipped v4.37.0 vendor profile page are closed in v4.37.1: a badge that defaulted to \\"New Vendor\\" for every vendor regardless of their score, a misleading \\"X reviews\\" label whose number was actually the count of booking-time star ratings, and review stars that disappeared on the public profile when reviews were imported from third-party plugins.","date":"2026-05-05T07:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"profile","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/profile"},{"inline":true,"label":"hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/hotfix"}],"readingTime":4.35,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.37.1-release","title":"Rentiva v4.37.1 \u2014 Vendor profile hotfix","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","vendor","profile","hotfix"],"date":"2026-05-05T07:00"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.37.0 \u2014 Vendor Public Profile Page","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.37.0-release"}},"content":"Three smoke-test findings on the freshly-shipped v4.37.0 vendor profile page are closed in v4.37.1: a badge that defaulted to \\"New Vendor\\" for every vendor regardless of their score, a misleading \\"X reviews\\" label whose number was actually the count of booking-time star ratings, and review stars that disappeared on the public profile when reviews were imported from third-party plugins.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why a hotfix on the same day\\n\\nv4.37.0 shipped this morning with a Pro feature spread across nine implementation phases and 78 new tests. PHPUnit was green, PHPCS was clean, the dispatch path worked end to end. But three of the bugs that made it into production were the kind that a unit test cannot easily catch:\\n\\n- A wiring bug \u2014 registration in the wrong init bucket \u2014 that a test fixture papers over by adding the filter callback explicitly.\\n- A semantic bug \u2014 the wrong word in a translatable string \u2014 that no machine-readable check flags.\\n- A defensive gap \u2014 only checking the canonical meta key, not the WC-standard alternative \u2014 that bites the day a third-party plugin imports a review.\\n\\nBrowser smoke surfaced all three within minutes of seeding three test vendors. The fix matrix is small enough that a same-day patch is the right call.\\n\\n## B1 \u2014 Badge stuck on \\"New Vendor\\"\\n\\nThe badge evaluator checks three thresholds: account age, reliability score, and lifetime completed bookings. The completed-bookings count comes from a filter:\\n\\n```php\\n$completed = (int) apply_filters(\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_vendor_completed_bookings_count\',\\n    0, // default\\n    $user_id\\n);\\n```\\n\\nThe production callback for that filter is registered in `VendorProfileExtension::register()`, which Plugin.php calls from `initialize_admin_services()` \u2014 the **admin-only** init bucket. On public requests (`is_admin() === false`), the bucket never runs and the callback never registers, so the count defaults to `0`. Every vendor falls into the `STATUS_NEW` branch, no matter their actual booking history.\\n\\nThis is the same `is_admin()` bucket trap we surfaced in Phase 9 \u2014 `VendorProfileSchema::register()` was originally placed in the admin-only bucket and got moved to a context-agnostic bucket once browser smoke caught the absent JSON-LD. `VendorProfileExtension::register()` legitimately belongs in the admin bucket (it owns admin-only profile screen hooks), but its filter-callback side effect leaked the bug into the frontend.\\n\\nThe fix is to make the badge work without depending on that wiring at all:\\n\\n```php\\n$default_completed = class_exists(ReliabilityScoreCalculator::class)\\n    ? ReliabilityScoreCalculator::count_completed_bookings($user_id, 9999)\\n    : 0;\\n\\n$completed = (int) apply_filters(\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_vendor_completed_bookings_count\',\\n    $default_completed,\\n    $user_id\\n);\\n```\\n\\nFilter callbacks can still override the count for special cases (lifecycle penalty suppressions, manual admin overrides, etc.). The default is now a real number, not a placeholder waiting for someone to wire it up.\\n\\n## B2 \u2014 Hero label \\"X reviews\\" was the wrong word\\n\\nThe vendor profile hero shows aggregate rating data:\\n\\n```\\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\xbd 4,8 ( 25 de\u011ferlendirme )\\n```\\n\\nThat `25` is the sum of `_mhm_rentiva_rating_count` across the vendor\'s active vehicles \u2014 booking-time star ratings, set when a customer completes a rental and rates the vehicle. The `Recent Reviews` section below the hero is a separate stream \u2014 WP review comments on the same vehicle posts. A vendor can easily have 25 booking ratings and 4 written review comments. The hero said \\"25 reviews\\", the section showed 4, and the math didn\'t add up.\\n\\nThe fix is the easy half of the problem: change the i18n string from `%d review` / `%d reviews` to `%d rating` / `%d ratings` (Turkish: `%d de\u011ferlendirme`). Same number, honest label.\\n\\nThe harder version of this question \u2014 should the hero show the WP comment count instead of the booking-rating count? \u2014 is deferred. The booking-rating average is the more useful metric for buyers because it\'s tied to completed transactions, not opinions. Renaming the label preserves that information.\\n\\n## B3 \u2014 Review stars empty for third-party imports\\n\\n`VendorProfileProvider::collect_reviews()` builds the per-review render data:\\n\\n```php\\n\'rating\' => (int) get_comment_meta($comment_id, \'mhm_rating\', true),\\n```\\n\\n`mhm_rating` is Rentiva\'s canonical key, set by `VehicleRatingForm` and the `ReviewEnforcer` normalization hook. Reviews submitted through Rentiva\'s own form get this key reliably. But a vendor whose reviews are imported from a third-party plugin \u2014 WC product reviews migrated into vehicles, Site Reviews / Customer Reviews for WooCommerce, manual database seeds \u2014 typically writes the WC-standard `rating` key. Without a fallback, those reviews show up on the profile with empty stars even though the rating value is right there in the database.\\n\\nThe fix is a one-helper change:\\n\\n```php\\nprivate static function resolve_review_rating(int $comment_id): int\\n{\\n    $rating = (int) get_comment_meta($comment_id, \'mhm_rating\', true);\\n    if ($rating > 0) {\\n        return $rating;\\n    }\\n    return (int) get_comment_meta($comment_id, \'rating\', true);\\n}\\n```\\n\\nCanonical wins when present; WC-standard falls through when it doesn\'t.\\n\\n## Validation\\n\\nThree test vendors, seeded directly into the local DB:\\n\\n| Vendor | Score | Bookings | Approved | Expected | Got |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Akif Y\u0131ld\u0131z | 92 | 20 | 200 days ago | Verified | \u2713 Do\u011frulanm\u0131\u015f Bayi |\\n| Zeynep Demir | 88 | 11 | 335 days ago | Verified | \u2713 Do\u011frulanm\u0131\u015f Bayi |\\n| Mehmet \xc7elik | 45 | 2 | 21 days ago | New | Yeni Bayi |\\n\\nAll three render star ratings on every review item; the hero label reads `X de\u011ferlendirme` (TR) / `X ratings` (EN).\\n\\nPHPUnit went from **982 \u2192 987** with the two new regression test classes (`VendorBadgeDefaultFallbackTest` 2 tests, `VendorProfileReviewRatingFallbackTest` 3 tests). The badge fallback test deliberately omits the filter callback registration so it would have failed against v4.37.0.\\n\\n## Links\\n\\n- [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.37.1)\\n- [Pull request #5](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/pull/5)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.37.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.37.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-05-05-rentiva-v4.37.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-05-rentiva-v4.37.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.37.0 \u2014 Vendor Public Profile Page","description":"Every approved vendor now has a public face. v4.37.0 ships a dedicated profile page at /vendor// (or /bayi// on Turkish sites), wired up across a canonical shortcode, a Gutenberg block, and an Elementor widget \u2014 all delegating to a single renderer. Schema.org LocalBusiness JSON-LD goes out in `` so search engines and social previews can read the vendor as a discrete entity, not as a slice of the homepage.","date":"2026-05-05T05:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"profile","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/profile"},{"inline":true,"label":"seo","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/seo"}],"readingTime":5.12,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.37.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.37.0 \u2014 Vendor Public Profile Page","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","vendor","profile","seo"],"date":"2026-05-05T05:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.37.1 \u2014 Vendor profile hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.37.1-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.36.0 \u2014 Transfer Booking Add-ons","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.36.0-release"}},"content":"Every approved vendor now has a public face. v4.37.0 ships a dedicated profile page at `/vendor/<slug>/` (or `/bayi/<slug>/` on Turkish sites), wired up across a canonical shortcode, a Gutenberg block, and an Elementor widget \u2014 all delegating to a single renderer. Schema.org `LocalBusiness` JSON-LD goes out in `<head>` so search engines and social previews can read the vendor as a discrete entity, not as a slice of the homepage.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nFor most of Rentiva\'s life, vendors lived inside the platform\'s own listing screens. Customers could find a specific vehicle, but they had no way to land on a *vendor* \u2014 to read who runs the fleet, see their reliability score and verification badge, browse their other cars, and read past reviews. Search engines had nothing to index either: no canonical URL, no schema, no breadcrumbs.\\n\\nv4.37.0 closes that gap. Each vendor gets a stable URL, a structured profile, and a renderer that\'s reusable wherever you want to surface vendor information \u2014 a homepage block, an Elementor template, a shortcode dropped into a custom page.\\n\\n## i18n-aware base URL\\n\\nThe URL pattern follows WooCommerce\'s translatable `/shop/`, `/product/` slugs:\\n\\n- English site: `/vendor/<slug>/`\\n- Turkish site: `/bayi/<slug>/`\\n\\nThe base segment comes from `_x(\'vendor\', \'URL slug\', \'mhm-rentiva\')`, runs through `apply_filters(\'mhm_rentiva_vendor_profile_url_base\', \u2026)` for site-owner override, then `urldecode()` and `sanitize_title()` for safety. Any locale just translates the `vendor` URL slug context and the rewrite rule rebuilds itself on the next `flush_rewrite_rules()`.\\n\\nWhen a vendor\'s URL slug changes (admin edits the slug field, or the auto-generator picks a different collision suffix), the previous slug is appended to a slug-history list and a 301 redirect is registered to the new canonical URL. Old links don\'t 404 \u2014 they redirect.\\n\\n## Single canonical renderer\\n\\nThree render paths, one source of truth:\\n\\n- `[rentiva_vendor_profile]` shortcode\\n- `mhm-rentiva/vendor-profile` Gutenberg block\\n- `mhm_rentiva_vendor_profile` Elementor widget\\n\\nThe block and widget delegate to the shortcode. The shortcode delegates to a partials chain (`vendor-profile-hero.php`, `vendor-profile-vehicles.php`, `vendor-profile-reviews.php`, `vendor-profile-location.php`). Whichever surface the customer arrives at \u2014 a public profile URL routed by the rewrite rule, a block embedded on a custom page, or an Elementor widget on a builder page \u2014 the HTML is identical.\\n\\nThis is the same Render Parity discipline Rentiva has applied across 19 blocks and 20 widgets: blocks/widgets never duplicate render logic, they delegate.\\n\\n## Schema.org for SEO\\n\\nThe `<head>` of a vendor profile carries a Schema.org `LocalBusiness` JSON-LD payload:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"@context\\": \\"https://schema.org\\",\\n  \\"@type\\": \\"LocalBusiness\\",\\n  \\"name\\": \\"Vendor display name\\",\\n  \\"url\\": \\"https://example.com/vendor/<slug>/\\",\\n  \\"image\\": \\"https://example.com/.../avatar.jpg\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nYoast SEO and Rank Math run their own canonical filter chains; v4.37.0 hooks `wpseo_canonical` and `rank_math/frontend/canonical` at `PHP_INT_MAX-10` to make sure the vendor profile URL wins over the homepage canonical that those plugins default to for non-singular pages.\\n\\nHostile vendor names can\'t break the schema either \u2014 the JSON encoder uses `JSON_HEX_TAG`, so a hostile `<\/script>` injection in a `display_name` becomes hex-encoded instead of escaping the script element. And if `url_for_user()` returns an empty string (vendor has no slug yet), the schema build short-circuits and emits nothing instead of an invalid `LocalBusiness` with a missing URL.\\n\\n## Vendor admin updates\\n\\nTwo new fields appear under the vendor\'s user profile screen:\\n\\n- **Vendor avatar** \u2014 a Media Library uploader. The chosen attachment is what `LocalBusiness.image` and the profile hero render. Falls back to a Gravatar of the user\'s email when unset.\\n- **Public Profile URL Slug** \u2014 a text field with a live collision check. The auto-generator strips diacritics (`Yeni Sat\u0131c\u0131` \u2192 `yeni-satici`) and appends a numeric suffix on collision (`yeni-satici-2`).\\n\\nIdempotent slug backfill runs once on upgrade. Existing vendors get an ASCII slug derived from their display name; the migration is gated on a version flag and never overwrites a slug an operator already set.\\n\\n## Verified Vendor / New Vendor badges\\n\\nThe profile hero shows one of two badges based on admin-configurable thresholds:\\n\\n- **Verified Vendor** \u2014 vendor has at least N completed bookings AND a reliability score at or above the configured floor.\\n- **New Vendor** \u2014 vendor was approved within the last N days.\\n\\nBoth thresholds live under MHM Rentiva \u2192 Settings, default to sensible values (30 completed bookings + 80 reliability score; 90 days for new), and feed the same `VendorBadgeEligibility` pure-logic class used everywhere a badge is rendered.\\n\\n## Cache invalidation that knows what changed\\n\\nVendor profile data caches in a transient keyed by user ID + cap suffix. Seven triggers invalidate it:\\n\\n- Vendor user-meta change (display name, slug, avatar, bio, badge override, etc.)\\n- Booking save (a new completed booking can shift reliability score)\\n- Comment status change (a newly approved review affects the average rating)\\n- Vehicle lifecycle change (a paused vehicle drops out of the vendor\'s vehicle list)\\n- Profile update hook (`profile_update`)\\n\\nThe cache key suffix encodes the maximum vehicle and review version stamps, so the invalidator uses an SQL prefix-wildcard delete (`DELETE FROM \u2026_options WHERE option_name LIKE \'_transient_mhm_rentiva_vendor_profile_<user_id>_%\'`) instead of needing to compute the exact suffix in advance.\\n\\n## i18n cleanup\\n\\nPhase 10 of the implementation refreshed 19 Turkish translations:\\n\\n- Four newly filled (was rendering English fallback): \\"Public Profile URL Slug\\", \\"Member %s\\", \\"No reviews yet \u2014 be the first to leave one.\\", \\"\u2192 %s\\"\\n- Fifteen fuzzy markers cleared: \\"Vendor Avatar\\" \u2192 \\"Bayi Avatar\u0131\\", \\"Verified Vendor\\" \u2192 \\"Do\u011frulanm\u0131\u015f Bayi\\", \\"New Vendor\\" \u2192 \\"Yeni Bayi\\", \\"Recent Reviews\\" \u2192 \\"Son De\u011ferlendirmeler\\", \\"View all vehicles \u2192\\" \u2192 \\"T\xfcm ara\xe7lar\u0131 g\xf6r\xfcnt\xfcle \u2192\\", and ten more.\\n\\nBrowser smoke confirmed zero English fallback leak on the live profile.\\n\\n## Pro-gated\\n\\nThe whole feature lives behind `Mode::canUseVendorMarketplace`, the same gate that protects the existing vendor admin panel. Lite installs see no rewrite rule, no admin fields, no schema emission. Dev sites can bypass the gate locally with `define(\'MHM_RENTIVA_DEV_PRO\', true);` in `wp-config.php`.\\n\\n## Stats\\n\\n- **PHPUnit:** 904 \u2192 **982** (+78 across nine implementation phases)\\n- **Assertions:** 3162\\n- **PHPCS:** 0 errors\\n- **i18n:** 19 TR translations refreshed (4 newly filled, 15 fuzzy cleared)\\n- **New PHP classes:** `VendorProfileUrlBase`, `VendorProfileRewrite`, `VendorProfileProvider`, `VendorProfileSchema`, `VendorProfileExtension`, `VendorProfileCacheInvalidator`, `VendorSlugManager`, `VendorSlugMigration`, `VendorBadgeEligibility`, `VendorProfileWidget`, `VendorProfileBlock`\\n- **Render surfaces:** 1 shortcode + 1 block + 1 Elementor widget delegating to a single renderer\\n\\n## Links\\n\\n- [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.37.0)\\n- [Pull request #4](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/pull/4)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.36.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.36.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.36.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.36.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.36.0 \u2014 Transfer Booking Add-ons","description":"Transfer customers can finally pick add-ons. v4.36.0 extends the existing vehicle_addon post type with a context taxonomy (rental / transfer / both) and three pricing types (per booking / per day / per passenger). When a customer clicks \\"Add to cart\\" on a transfer search result, a modal slides up showing the relevant add-ons with a live multiplier-aware total.","date":"2026-04-30T01:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"add-ons","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/add-ons"}],"readingTime":3.54,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.36.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.36.0 \u2014 Transfer Booking Add-ons","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","transfer","add-ons"],"date":"2026-04-30T01:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.37.0 \u2014 Vendor Public Profile Page","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.37.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.35.0 \u2014 Vendor Report & Appeal System","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.35.0-release"}},"content":"Transfer customers can finally pick add-ons. v4.36.0 extends the existing `vehicle_addon` post type with a context taxonomy (rental / transfer / both) and three pricing types (per booking / per day / per passenger). When a customer clicks \\"Add to cart\\" on a transfer search result, a modal slides up showing the relevant add-ons with a live multiplier-aware total.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nUp to v4.35.0, the add-on system was rental-only. The transfer add-to-cart handler had a hard-coded `\'selected_addons\' => array()` placeholder where the rental flow would have carried the customer\'s selections. That meant zero ancillary revenue on transfers \u2014 no child seats, no extra waiting time, no welcome banners, no VIP assistant. Vendors who already had a perfectly good catalogue of add-ons couldn\'t surface any of it on the transfer side.\\n\\nv4.36.0 closes that gap **without forking the data model**. One CPT, one catalogue, one place for the vendor to manage add-ons. The same record can target a rental booking, a transfer, or both.\\n\\n## The data model in one paragraph\\n\\n`vehicle_addon` gains an `addon_context` taxonomy with three default terms \u2014 `rental`, `transfer`, `both` \u2014 and a `_mhm_addon_pricing_type` post meta with three enum values \u2014 `per_booking` (flat), `per_day` (rental days \xd7 price), `per_passenger` (passenger count \xd7 price). The pricing types form an `(allowed \xd7 context)` matrix: `per_day` only makes sense for rental, `per_passenger` only for transfer, `per_booking` works in both. A radio metabox on the admin edit screen, a JS-driven dynamic select, and a server-side validator all enforce the same rule.\\n\\n## The transfer modal\\n\\nWhen a search result\'s \\"Add to cart\\" button is clicked, a vanilla-JS modal opens with the available transfer add-ons. Required add-ons are pre-checked and locked. Optional ones come with a live total that respects the pricing type:\\n\\n- `per_booking` shows `+ 50 \u20ba` (flat).\\n- `per_passenger` shows `+ 15 \u20ba \xd7 3 yolcu = 45 \u20ba` (live multiplied by the trip\'s passenger count).\\n\\nThe footer line keeps a running grand total: `Vehicle 280 \u20ba + add-ons 95 \u20ba = 375 \u20ba`. \\"Cancel\\" backs out without dispatching anything; \\"Add to cart\\" submits the selected IDs alongside the existing vehicle/origin/destination/datetime payload.\\n\\nIf a vendor configured zero transfer-context add-ons, the modal is suppressed entirely \u2014 the existing direct-add behaviour kicks in untouched.\\n\\n## Migration that never overwrites\\n\\nExisting add-on records are auto-assigned to `rental` context with `per_booking` pricing on the first `init` after upgrade. The data lane is gated by an option flag and never overwrites a value the operator has already set. If the flag is manually reset, the migration re-runs idempotently \u2014 operator overrides survive.\\n\\nThis is the same schema/data lane separation the codebase has used since v4.27.4: the schema lane (taxonomy register + default term seed) runs every request as a normal WP API call; the data lane (legacy backfill) runs once and stops.\\n\\n## One pricing calculator, both flows\\n\\n`AddonPricingCalculator::calculate( $addon_id, $context )` is the single source of truth. The rental booking total filter, the transfer cart AJAX handler, the admin booking detail page, the WC order item meta \u2014 all of them go through this one helper. The context array is shaped `{rental_days?, adults?, children?}`; rental fills `rental_days`, transfer fills `adults` and `children`, and the calculator picks whichever it needs based on the addon\'s pricing type.\\n\\nThis is the cheapest insurance against the rental and transfer math drifting apart over time.\\n\\n## Lite limit unchanged\\n\\nLite still caps at 4 published add-ons total \u2014 combined rental and transfer. The vendor decides how to split the slots. The admin notice copy was updated to make this explicit (\\"Lite s\xfcr\xfcm\xfcnde en fazla 4 ek hizmet ekleyebilirsiniz (kiralama + transfer ortak)\u2026\\").\\n\\n## Stats\\n\\n- **PHPUnit:** 864 \u2192 **904** (+40 across 7 new test classes)\\n- **PHPCS:** 0 errors\\n- **Files:** 7 new PHP classes, 3 new CSS/JS files, ~10 modified PHP files\\n- **i18n:** all sources English; Turkish translations in `mhm-rentiva-tr_TR.po`; JS strings localised via `wp_localize_script`\\n- **Schema:** `CURRENT_VERSION` 3.6.0 \u2192 3.7.0\\n\\n## What ships next\\n\\n- **v4.37.0** \u2014 Transfer Locations Map View. The deferred `per_km` pricing type ships here, where its UX value (visualising distance against a haritada) finally has the supporting context.\\n- **v4.38.0** \u2014 Vendor Directory Page (Dokan-style standalone catalogue).\\n- **v4.39.0** \u2014 Vendor Profile Page (unblocks Vehicle Lifecycle Phase 5).\\n\\n## Links\\n\\n- [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.36.0)\\n- [Pull request #3](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/pull/3)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.35.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.35.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.35.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.35.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.35.0 \u2014 Vendor Report & Appeal System","description":"A shared infrastructure for vendor \u2192 admin reports lands in v4.35.0. Five contexts, one custom table, one shared modal, one admin \\"Bayi Raporlar\u0131\\" page. Plus the withdrawal/pause reason capture flow: when a vendor withdraws a vehicle and explains why, the penalty is suspended until an admin reviews the appeal \u2014 accept, the vendor keeps their score; reject, the penalty applies retroactively.","date":"2026-04-30T00:30:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"marketplace","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/marketplace"},{"inline":true,"label":"penalty","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/penalty"}],"readingTime":4.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.35.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.35.0 \u2014 Vendor Report & Appeal System","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","vendor","marketplace","penalty"],"date":"2026-04-30T00:30"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.36.0 \u2014 Transfer Booking Add-ons","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.36.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.2 \u2014 Transfer-card icon styling hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.2-release"}},"content":"A shared infrastructure for vendor \u2192 admin reports lands in v4.35.0. Five contexts, one custom table, one shared modal, one admin \\"Bayi Raporlar\u0131\\" page. Plus the **withdrawal/pause reason capture** flow: when a vendor withdraws a vehicle and explains why, the penalty is suspended until an admin reviews the appeal \u2014 accept, the vendor keeps their score; reject, the penalty applies retroactively.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nUntil v4.35.0 vendors had no structured way to talk back to the admin. Booking issues (no-show customer, damage), vehicle actions that triggered automatic penalties, score deductions they thought were unfair \u2014 all of these went straight to email or Slack, off the platform. The marketplace had a one-way feedback loop.\\n\\nv4.35.0 closes the loop with a single piece of shared infrastructure. The same modal, table, and admin page handle all five contexts. The only thing that varies is the trigger location and the side-effect on resolution.\\n\\n## The five contexts\\n\\n| Context | When | Trigger | Resolution side-effect |\\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\\n| `booking` | Customer issue (no-show, damage, dispute) | \\"Sorun Bildir\\" on the vendor booking card (button existed since v4.26.5, JS now wired) | None \u2014 informational |\\n| `vehicle` | Appeal a paused/withdrawn vehicle action | \\"\u0130tiraz Et\\" on listings page (paused/withdrawn states only) | None \u2014 admin guidance |\\n| `vehicle_action` | **Reason capture during withdraw/pause** | Modal automatically opens when a vendor clicks Withdraw or Pause | Reject \u2192 deferred penalty applied; resolve \u2192 vendor keeps score |\\n| `penalty` | Appeal an already-applied penalty | \\"Appeal\\" button on each penalty row in score history | (v4.36.0+ \u2014 ledger compensating entry helper) |\\n| `general` | \\"Y\xf6neticiye Yaz\\" \u2014 direct line to admin | Footer link on every vendor panel page | None |\\n\\n## The Not 2 augment \u2014 withdrawal reason capture\\n\\nBefore v4.35.0, withdrawing a vehicle meant a `confirm()` dialog (\\"Are you sure? A penalty may apply.\\") and an immediate score deduction + ledger debit. There was no way to tell the platform why the vehicle had to leave.\\n\\nNow the lifecycle JS captures the reason in a proper modal and POSTs it alongside the `mhm_vehicle_lifecycle_withdraw` AJAX call. The AJAX handler creates a `vehicle_action` report **before** calling the Manager. Inside the Manager, a new filter \u2014 `mhm_rentiva_before_apply_penalty` \u2014 fires:\\n\\n```php\\n$apply_penalty = (bool) apply_filters(\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_before_apply_penalty\',\\n    true,\\n    $vehicle_id,\\n    $vendor_id,\\n    \'withdrawal\',\\n    $penalty\\n);\\n\\nif ($apply_penalty) {\\n    ReliabilityScoreCalculator::update($vendor_id, \'withdraw\', $vehicle_id);\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe same filter wraps `PenaltyRecorder::record_penalty()` so the ledger debit stays in lockstep with the score. `PenaltySuspensionHook::maybe_suspend()` returns `false` when an open `vehicle_action` report exists for the vendor + vehicle pair.\\n\\nState and side-effects are decoupled: the vehicle still transitions to `withdrawn` (post status, lifecycle meta, cooldown date \u2014 all set), but the score and ledger are paused. When the admin resolves the report:\\n\\n- **Resolved** (vendor wins) \u2014 no-op. Score and ledger were never touched. The vendor lost zero points and zero TL.\\n- **Rejected** \u2014 `VendorReportService::apply_deferred_penalty()` calls `ReliabilityScoreCalculator::update()` to recompute (the withdrawal is in state, so the score now drops) and re-runs `PenaltyRecorder::record_penalty()` to write the ledger debit. The penalty applies retroactively.\\n\\n## Architecture in one paragraph\\n\\n`VendorReportRepository` is the DB layer (CRUD on the new `wp_mhm_rentiva_vendor_reports` custom table; per-request `has_open_report_for()` cache so the dual filter hook costs one DB query). `VendorReportService` is the business layer (validation, FSM, side-effects, hook firing for emails). `VendorReportAjaxHandler` is the transport. `PenaltySuspensionHook` is the bridge to the existing penalty pipeline. `VendorReportsAdminPage` is the admin UI. `VendorReportAssets` enqueues the shared modal and JS on every vendor-facing page. The only thing that touches multiple layers is the filter hook itself, and that\'s deliberate \u2014 the hook is the seam between the vendor-report subsystem and the lifecycle subsystem.\\n\\n## Plan-vs-codebase reconciliation\\n\\nThe original plan was written 2026-04-15 and assumed nine things about the codebase that turned out to be false. A comprehensive pre-implementation audit caught all of them:\\n\\n1. `src/Admin/Penalty/` directory \u2014 does not exist; penalty code lives in `src/Admin/Vehicle/`.\\n2. `PenaltyService::cancel()` / `apply_pending()` \u2014 no such class. Removed from design; service layer calls `ReliabilityScoreCalculator` and `PenaltyRecorder` directly.\\n3. `mhm_rentiva_before_apply_penalty` filter \u2014 did not exist. Introduced in this release.\\n4. `penalty_record_id` is BIGINT \u2014 penalties are anonymous ledger entries with UUIDs. Schema changed to `VARCHAR(64) context_id`.\\n5. Score deduction is hook-suspendable \u2014 actually synchronous before any hook fires. Filter must wrap the score update inline.\\n6. Migration file `0042_create_vendor_reports.php` \u2014 no sequential numbering convention. Renamed `VendorReportsMigration`, registered via `DatabaseMigrator::run_migrations()` after `CURRENT_VERSION` bump.\\n7. \\"Sorun Bildir\\" button needs adding to vendor-bookings.php \u2014 already exists since v4.26.5. Build sequence simplified.\\n8. \\"Report Issue\\" string needs adding to .po \u2014 already translated. List trimmed.\\n9. No Mode gating mentioned \u2014 `Mode::canUseVendorMarketplace()` required on all new admin pages, AJAX handlers, email registrations, and asset enqueues.\\n\\nThe user explicitly requested \\"Vendor ile ilgili t\xfcm dosyalar\u0131 detayl\u0131 incele. Eksik, g\xf6zden ka\xe7an bir \u015fey olmas\u0131n\\" before implementation began. That nudge is what surfaced these. Plan files written months earlier are not authoritative; the codebase is.\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- PHPUnit: 840 \u2192 864 (+24 \u2014 Repository 10, Service 8, PenaltySuspensionHook 6)\\n- PHPCS: 0 errors\\n- Runtime smoke test: admin \\"Bayi Raporlar\u0131\\" page renders, all status + context filters in TR, empty state correctly shown, full migration applied via `DatabaseMigrator` on plugin activate.\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n- No license-server upgrade required.\\n- Backwards compatible: lifecycle AJAX submissions without a `reason` POST parameter behave exactly as in v4.34.x (no report created, normal penalty applied). Older vendors don\'t break.\\n- Dev sites need `define(\'MHM_RENTIVA_DEV_PRO\', true);` in `wp-config.php` to bypass the Pro gate while testing.\\n\\n## What\'s next\\n\\nThe roadmap continues with the **transfer wave**: v4.36.0 adds context-aware add-ons (extending `vehicle_addon` CPT with an `addon_context` taxonomy), v4.37.0 adds a transfer-locations map view. After that the **vendor wave** picks up \u2014 directory page (v4.38.0) and the long-deferred Phase 5 vendor public profile (v4.39.0).\\n\\n\u2014 [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.35.0)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.34.2-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.2-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.2-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.34.2 \u2014 Transfer-card icon styling hotfix","description":"A pure CSS hotfix on top of v4.34.1. The favorite (heart) and compare icons on the transfer-search results page rendered as oversized solid-blue blocks instead of the small round white icons used on the rental grid/list. v4.34.2 restores parity.","date":"2026-04-30T00:15:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"css","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/css"},{"inline":true,"label":"hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/hotfix"}],"readingTime":2.5,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.34.2-release","title":"Rentiva v4.34.2 \u2014 Transfer-card icon styling hotfix","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","transfer","css","hotfix"],"date":"2026-04-30T00:15"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.35.0 \u2014 Vendor Report & Appeal System","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.35.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.1 \u2014 Popular Routes Clickable Cards","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.1-release"}},"content":"A pure CSS hotfix on top of [v4.34.1](/blog/rentiva-v4.34.1-release). The favorite (heart) and compare icons on the transfer-search results page rendered as oversized solid-blue blocks instead of the small round white icons used on the rental grid/list. v4.34.2 restores parity.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What broke\\n\\nA user clicked through from a Popular Routes card to the transfer-search results and noticed the heart and compare buttons looked nothing like their rental-grid counterparts:\\n\\n- **Expected:** 32\xd732 round button, white translucent background, red heart outline icon, top-right of the card image.\\n- **Got:** 100\xd755px solid-blue block with a tiny white heart inside, padded like a generic CTA button.\\n\\nPHPUnit was green. PHPCS was clean. But the icons in the live DOM were broken.\\n\\n## Root cause\\n\\n`vehicle-card.css` styles the icon buttons with this rule:\\n\\n```css\\n.mhm-vehicle-card .mhm-card-favorite {\\n  width: 32px; height: 32px; padding: 0;\\n  border-radius: 50%; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);\\n  /* ...etc */\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe `.mhm-vehicle-card` parent prefix is not decorative \u2014 it\'s a **deliberate specificity hack**. The CSS comment in the file even says so:\\n\\n> Parent selector raises specificity to (0,2,0) \u2014 overrides Astra\'s inline button rule (0,0,1) without needing `!important`. Works across themes.\\n\\nAstra (and other themes) ship a generic `button` style that pads buttons and applies a solid background. The plugin\'s intent was to outweigh that without an `!important` arms race, by leaning on selector specificity.\\n\\nTransfer cards, however, are rendered with `.mhm-transfer-card` as the parent class \u2014 not `.mhm-vehicle-card`. So the styling rule never matched, the (0,0,1) Astra rule won by default, and you got a 100\xd755px solid-blue button.\\n\\nThe buttons themselves use the same markup (`.mhm-card-favorite` / `.mhm-card-compare`) \u2014 only the parent wrapper class differs.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\nList both parents in each selector:\\n\\n```css\\n.mhm-vehicle-card .mhm-card-favorite,\\n.mhm-transfer-card .mhm-card-favorite {\\n  /* same 32\xd732 round-icon rules as before */\\n}\\n\\n.mhm-vehicle-card .mhm-card-compare,\\n.mhm-transfer-card .mhm-card-compare {\\n  /* same */\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSpecificity stays at (0,2,0), Astra\'s `button` rule is still outweighed without `!important`, and the icon styling is now identical across rental and transfer surfaces.\\n\\n## What this taught us\\n\\nPHPUnit + PHPCS are necessary but not sufficient gates. CSS scoping bugs slip through both:\\n\\n- PHPUnit doesn\'t see CSS at all.\\n- PHPCS sees CSS as text, not as rules-applied-to-DOM.\\n\\nThe only signal that catches this class of bug is **looking at the live DOM**. v4.34.0 and v4.34.1 ran the runtime smoke test on the homepage Popular Routes section \u2014 and that section was correct. The transfer-search results page was a separate surface that the smoke test didn\'t visit. v4.34.2 closes the loop: when a feature touches multiple downstream surfaces, the smoke test has to follow the click path, not just inspect the entry point.\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n- No license-server upgrade.\\n- No breaking changes \u2014 the affected CSS only widens the rule set; nothing existing breaks.\\n\\n\u2014 [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.34.2)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.34.1-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.1-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.1-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.34.1 \u2014 Popular Routes Clickable Cards","description":"A small but high-leverage patch on top of v4.34.0. Popular Routes cards are now clickable, and clicking one deep-links into the transfer-search form with origin and destination pre-filled. The visitor\'s path goes from \\"see a route I want \u2192 find the search form \u2192 re-pick the same locations from a dropdown of seven \u2192 add date/time \u2192 submit\\" down to \\"click the route \u2192 add date/time \u2192 submit.\\"","date":"2026-04-29T23:55:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"ux","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/ux"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"}],"readingTime":3.56,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.34.1-release","title":"Rentiva v4.34.1 \u2014 Popular Routes Clickable Cards","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","transfer","ux","patch"],"date":"2026-04-29T23:55"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.2 \u2014 Transfer-card icon styling hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.2-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.0 \u2014 Popular Transfer Routes Showcase","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.0-release"}},"content":"A small but high-leverage patch on top of [v4.34.0](/blog/rentiva-v4.34.0-release). Popular Routes cards are now clickable, and clicking one deep-links into the transfer-search form with origin and destination pre-filled. The visitor\'s path goes from \\"see a route I want \u2192 find the search form \u2192 re-pick the same locations from a dropdown of seven \u2192 add date/time \u2192 submit\\" down to \\"click the route \u2192 add date/time \u2192 submit.\\"\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nA reviewer flagged the obvious gap right after v4.34.0 shipped: the cards looked like CTAs but weren\'t tappable. A user seeing \\"\u0130stanbul Havaliman\u0131 \u2192 Taksim \xb7 \u20ba850\\" on the homepage instinctively reaches for the card, not the search form three sections down. v4.34.0 left them with a static information panel; v4.34.1 turns it into the conversion surface it should have been.\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\n### Whole-card click target\\n\\n`PopularRoutesShortcode::render_card` now wraps the `<article>` in an `<a class=\\"mhm-popular-route-card-link\\">`. The href is built with `add_query_arg()` against a filterable base URL (default: the same target as the section \\"Search transfers\\" link, which itself defaults to `home_url(\'/transfer/\')`).\\n\\n```html\\n<a class=\\"mhm-popular-route-card-link\\"\\n   href=\\"https://example.com/transfer/?origin_id=73&destination_id=76\\"\\n   aria-label=\\"Search transfers from \u0130stanbul Havaliman\u0131 (IST) to Taksim Ofis\\">\\n  <article class=\\"mhm-popular-route-card mhm-popular-route-card--featured\\" role=\\"listitem\\">\\n    ...\\n  </article>\\n</a>\\n```\\n\\nThe CSS resets `color: inherit; text-decoration: none` on the anchor so the card visuals stay identical to v4.34.0, but adds `:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--mhm-pr-accent) }` so keyboard navigation gets a visible focus ring without disrupting mouse users.\\n\\n### Deep-link pre-fill\\n\\n`TransferShortcodes::prepare_template_data()` now reads `origin_id` and `destination_id` from `$_GET` (absint, sanitized) and exposes them to the template as `$preselected_origin` and `$preselected_destination`. The `transfer-search.php` template gained `selected()` calls on the `<option>` elements for both selects.\\n\\n```php\\n<option value=\\"<?php echo esc_attr((string) $loc->id); ?>\\"\\n        <?php selected(isset($preselected_origin) ? (int) $preselected_origin : 0, (int) $loc->id); ?>>\\n  <?php echo esc_html($loc->name); ?>\\n</option>\\n```\\n\\nBackwards compatible: installations that never get `?origin_id=...` URLs behave exactly as they did in v4.34.0 (the form opens with empty selects, as before). The change is additive \u2014 no breakage, no migration.\\n\\n### New filter \u2014 `mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_search_url`\\n\\nThe card-link base URL is independently filterable from the section \\"Search transfers\\" link. Themes that route the section link to a custom landing page but want the cards to deep-link directly into the search form can do so without one filter clobbering the other.\\n\\n```php\\n// Card click target = transfer-search shortcode page\\nadd_filter(\'mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_search_url\', function () {\\n    return home_url(\'/transfer-search/\');\\n});\\n\\n// Section \\"Search transfers\\" link target = a curated catalog page\\nadd_filter(\'mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_view_all_url\', function () {\\n    return home_url(\'/all-routes/\');\\n});\\n```\\n\\nWhen the card filter returns empty, the link falls back to the section URL, which falls back to `home_url(\'/transfer/\')` \u2014 sane defaults all the way down.\\n\\n### ARIA labels per card\\n\\n```html\\naria-label=\\"Search transfers from \u0130stanbul Havaliman\u0131 (IST) to Taksim Ofis\\"\\n```\\n\\nScreen readers announce a meaningful action when the link gets focus. Crawlers also see a real description of where the link goes, which is useful for the homepage SEO surface.\\n\\n### Section label rename\\n\\n\\"View all \u2192\\" \u2192 \\"Search transfers \u2192\\" in the section header. The link has always landed on the transfer-search form (not a route catalog page), so the v4.34.0 label was misleading. The new label matches what actually happens.\\n\\nA future v4.35.x release may add an actual route-catalog page (e.g. `/transfer-routes/` rendering all eligible routes in list form), at which point the \\"View all\\" label could come back honestly. For now: truth in advertising.\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- **PHPUnit:** 837 \u2192 840 (+3). New tests assert the anchor wrapper exists with the right CSS class, the href carries both `origin_id` and `destination_id` query parameters, the `mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_search_url` filter overrides the base URL, and the section header label has been renamed.\\n- **PHPCS:** 0 errors.\\n- **Runtime smoke test (Chrome DevTools MCP):** rendered 6 cards, each wrapped in an anchor with the correct query-param href and a TR `aria-label`; navigating to `/transfer/?origin_id=73&destination_id=76` pre-selects \\"\u0130stanbul Havaliman\u0131 (IST)\\" and \\"Taksim Ofis\\" in the form selects.\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n- No license-server upgrade.\\n- No breaking changes \u2014 v4.34.0 sites upgrade in place.\\n- Existing transfer-search submissions continue to work without `$_GET` params.\\n\\n\u2014 [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.34.1)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.34.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.34.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.34.0 \u2014 Popular Transfer Routes Showcase","description":"The homepage now has a proper sales surface for VIP transfer routes. v4.34.0 ships a [rentivapopularroutes] shortcode + Gutenberg block + Elementor widget \u2014 three surfaces sharing one canonical renderer \u2014 that show A \u2192 B route cards (origin \u2192 destination, average duration, distance, starting price) with an admin \\"\ud83c\udf1f Vitrine Koy\\" pin checkbox to control which routes appear.","date":"2026-04-29T23:30:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"shortcode","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/shortcode"},{"inline":true,"label":"block","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/block"},{"inline":true,"label":"elementor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/elementor"}],"readingTime":4.64,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.34.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.34.0 \u2014 Popular Transfer Routes Showcase","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","transfer","shortcode","block","elementor"],"date":"2026-04-29T23:30"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.1 \u2014 Popular Routes Clickable Cards","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.1-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.2 \u2014 Turkish Terminology Cleanup","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.2-release"}},"content":"The homepage now has a proper sales surface for VIP transfer routes. v4.34.0 ships a `[rentiva_popular_routes]` shortcode + Gutenberg block + Elementor widget \u2014 three surfaces sharing one canonical renderer \u2014 that show A \u2192 B route cards (origin \u2192 destination, average duration, distance, starting price) with an admin \\"\ud83c\udf1f Vitrine Koy\\" pin checkbox to control which routes appear.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why this release exists\\n\\nRentiva\'s transfer module has been quietly capable for months: vendors set per-route pricing, the search engine joins endpoints with vehicle eligibility, the cart honors fixed and per-km pricing methods. But the homepage didn\'t surface any of that. A visitor landing on the rental marketplace had to dig into the search form to discover that VIP transfer was even on offer, let alone what it costs.\\n\\nv4.34.0 closes that gap. The new section sits on the landing page, shows the strongest routes pinned first, and answers the only question a transfer customer actually asks before clicking \\"Book\\": *how much, how long, how far?*\\n\\n## What\'s in the release\\n\\n### `[rentiva_popular_routes]` \u2014 three surfaces, one renderer\\n\\nThe shortcode is the canonical implementation. The Gutenberg block (`mhm-rentiva/popular-routes`) and the Elementor widget (`mhm_rentiva_popular_routes`) both delegate to it via `do_shortcode()`, which is Rentiva\'s render-parity contract: whatever you can render with a shortcode renders identically through any of the three surfaces. No drift, no double codepath.\\n\\nThe shortcode supports 16 attributes:\\n\\n| Attribute | Default | Purpose |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `limit` | `6` | Max cards (capped to `Mode::maxTransferRoutes()` on Lite plans) |\\n| `columns` | `3` | Desktop grid columns (2/3/4) |\\n| `order` | `featured` | `featured` / `price_asc` / `price_desc` / `alphabetical` / `newest` |\\n| `heading` | \\"Popular Routes\\" | Section title (i18n) |\\n| `subheading` | \\"Most preferred VIP transfer routes\\" | Section subtitle |\\n| `show_view_all` | `true` | Show the \\"View all\\" link in the header |\\n| `view_all_url` | empty | Override the link target (else uses the `mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_view_all_url` filter) |\\n| `show_duration` / `show_distance` / `show_traffic_note` / `show_price` | `true` | Per-element visibility toggles |\\n| `currency_symbol` | `\u20ba` | Price prefix |\\n| `filter_origin_city` | empty | e.g. `Istanbul` |\\n| `filter_origin_type` | empty | `airport` / `train` / `hotel` / `marina` / `city_center` |\\n| `featured_only` | `false` | When `true`, render only pinned routes |\\n| `theme` | `light` | `light` / `dark` |\\n\\n### Admin \\"\ud83c\udf1f Vitrine Koy\\" checkbox\\n\\nThe Transfer Routes admin form gets a new checkbox: **\ud83c\udf1f Vitrine Koy (pop\xfcler rotalar blo\u011funa sabitle)**. Pinned routes appear first when `order=\\"featured\\"` (the default) and exclusively when `featured_only=\\"true\\"`. The route list table shows a \\"\ud83c\udf1f Showcase\\" badge next to pinned rows so admins can scan-verify what the homepage will render.\\n\\nSave and delete actions automatically invalidate the `TransferRouteProvider` transient cache, so changes go live on the next page request without any cache-clearing dance.\\n\\n### `TransferRouteProvider` repository\\n\\nA new single-source-of-truth class for popular-route queries, modeled after the existing `LocationProvider` pattern: 1-hour transient cache, JOIN-based eligibility filter (origin and destination must both be `is_active=1` AND `allow_transfer=1`), composable filter set (city / type / featured-only). Cache keys hash the full filter set so distinct shortcode invocations don\'t share cache.\\n\\n```php\\nTransferRouteProvider::get_popular_routes([\\n    \'limit\'              => 6,\\n    \'order\'              => \'featured\',\\n    \'featured_only\'      => false,\\n    \'filter_origin_city\' => \'Istanbul\',\\n    \'filter_origin_type\' => \'airport\',\\n]);\\n```\\n\\nRows come back as objects with origin/destination data already joined: `origin_name`, `origin_city`, `origin_type`, `destination_name`, `destination_city`, `destination_type`, plus all the route columns (`distance_km`, `duration_min`, `min_price`, `is_featured`, etc.).\\n\\n### Database migration\\n\\n`{prefix}rentiva_transfer_routes` gains an `is_featured tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` column with an index. The migration uses dbDelta and is idempotent \u2014 existing installations upgrade in place with no downtime, and re-running the migration on a current schema is a no-op.\\n\\n### Lite vs Pro\\n\\nLite plans render up to 3 cards. This is enforced through the existing `Mode::maxTransferRoutes()` quota \u2014 the same one that already caps how many routes a Lite admin can define. Pro plans render up to the configured `limit` (default 6). The shortcode\'s `resolve_limit()` is `min($requested, $tier_max)`, so a `limit=\\"20\\"` attribute on a Lite site quietly clamps to 3 instead of erroring.\\n\\n### Empty state\\n\\nSilent no-op. When zero routes match the filters (or the routes table is empty, or all eligible endpoints are inactive), the section doesn\'t render at all \u2014 no \\"Coming soon...\\" placeholder, no empty grid, no console noise. New installations look clean; populated sites surface what they have.\\n\\n### Two filter hooks\\n\\n```php\\n// Themes/integrations supply the transfer-search URL when no\\n// explicit view_all_url is set.\\nadd_filter(\'mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_view_all_url\', function ($url) {\\n    return home_url(\'/transfer/\');\\n});\\n\\n// Override the icon shown for a given location type.\\nadd_filter(\'mhm_rentiva_popular_routes_type_icon\', function ($icon, $type) {\\n    return $type === \'airport\' ? \'\ud83d\udeeb\' : $icon;\\n}, 10, 2);\\n```\\n\\n## Tests and quality gates\\n\\n- **PHPUnit:** 824 \u2192 837 (+13). New tests cover empty state, single/multi-card render, origin city + origin type filters, featured ordering (pinned-first), price-ascending sort, hidden routes for inactive endpoints, duration/distance/price visibility flags, and the invalid `columns` fallback.\\n- **PHPCS:** 0 errors. `composer phpcs` clean across all changed files.\\n- **SchemaParityTest:** Bumped to 20 block.json files, validated end-to-end (block attribute names round-trip through `AllowlistRegistry` to canonical shortcode attributes).\\n- **i18n:** 35+ new TR strings \u2014 frontend card labels (Pop\xfcler Rotalar, Yakla\u015f\u0131k X dk, Trafi\u011fe g\xf6re de\u011fi\u015febilir, Ba\u015flang\u0131\xe7 fiyat\u0131), admin form (\ud83c\udf1f Vitrine Koy), full block + widget editor controls (Sorting & Filters, Card Display panels). `.pot` regenerated, `tr_TR.po` msgmerged, `.mo` and `.l10n.php` recompiled.\\n- **Runtime smoke test:** Real admin \u2192 frontend round-trip via Chrome DevTools MCP. Edit form checkbox, save, navigate to a page rendering the shortcode, verify all 6 cards (4 featured pinned first), TR translations correct, CSS loaded, zero console errors.\\n\\n## What\'s next\\n\\nThe roadmap continues with the **transfer wave**: v4.36.0 adds context-aware add-ons (extending the existing `vehicle_addon` CPT with an `addon_context` taxonomy), v4.37.0 adds a transfer-locations map view (porting pinning code from another project). After that the **vendor wave** picks up \u2014 directory page (v4.38.0) and the long-deferred Phase 5 vendor public profile (v4.39.0).\\n\\n\u2014 [GitHub release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.34.0)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.33.2-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.2-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.33.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.33.2-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.33.2 \u2014 Turkish Terminology Cleanup","description":"A pure translation patch. The Vendor surface in Turkish moves from Sat\u0131c\u0131 (literally \\"one who sells\\") to Bayi (dealer / authorized agency) across the entire catalog \u2014 Rentiva is a rental marketplace, not a sales platform, and \\"Sat\u0131c\u0131\\" read awkwardly throughout the admin and vendor-facing screens.","date":"2026-04-29T22:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"i18n","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/i-18-n"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"}],"readingTime":2.26,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.33.2-release","title":"Rentiva v4.33.2 \u2014 Turkish Terminology Cleanup","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","i18n","patch"],"date":"2026-04-29T22:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.34.0 \u2014 Popular Transfer Routes Showcase","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.34.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.1 \u2014 Search Polish & Vendor Name Fix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.1-release"}},"content":"A pure translation patch. The Vendor surface in Turkish moves from **Sat\u0131c\u0131** (literally \\"one who sells\\") to **Bayi** (dealer / authorized agency) across the entire catalog \u2014 Rentiva is a rental marketplace, not a sales platform, and \\"Sat\u0131c\u0131\\" read awkwardly throughout the admin and vendor-facing screens.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why this release exists\\n\\nThe Turkish translation catalog used **Sat\u0131c\u0131** for the English term *Vendor* across ~130 strings. In Turkish business context:\\n\\n| Term | Meaning | Fit for Rentiva |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| **Sat\u0131c\u0131** | One who sells (sales transaction) | Misleading \u2014 vendors here rent, they don\'t sell |\\n| **Bayi** | Authorized dealer/agency/franchisee | Natural \u2014 *Toyota Bayisi*, *Yetkili Bayi*, *Kiralama Bayisi* |\\n\\nA user reading \\"Sat\u0131c\u0131 paneli\\" or \\"Sat\u0131c\u0131 ba\u015fvurusu\\" mentally parses *seller panel* / *seller application*, which doesn\'t match the rental marketplace model. **Bayi** is the term Turkish rental agencies actually use to describe themselves in marketing and legal contracts.\\n\\nFive places in the catalog already used \\"Bayi\\" (terminology drift from earlier translations) \u2014 this release standardizes the entire surface.\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\n### ~130 strings migrated with proper Turkish inflection\\n\\nTurkish is agglutinative \u2014 suffixes attach to stems with vowel-harmony rules. A simple `sed \'s/Sat\u0131c\u0131/Bayi/g\'` would leave grammatical errors everywhere because the **back-vowel** stem \\"Sat\u0131c\u0131\\" takes back-vowel suffixes (-lar, -n\u0131n, -ya, -dan), while the **front-vowel** stem \\"Bayi\\" takes front-vowel suffixes (-ler, -nin, -ye, -den).\\n\\nThe migration applied an inflection-aware substitution chain, longest suffix first to prevent partial-match corruption:\\n\\n| Old (back-vowel paradigm) | New (front-vowel paradigm) |\\n|---|---|\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131n\u0131z | Bayileriniz |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131n | Bayilerin |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131lardan | Bayilerden |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131lara | Bayilere |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131larda | Bayilerde |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131lar | Bayiler |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131n\u0131n | Bayinin |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131s\u0131 | Bayisi |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131ya | Bayiye |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131y\u0131 | Bayiyi |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131dan | Bayiden |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131da | Bayide |\\n| Sat\u0131c\u0131 | Bayi |\\n\\n(Lowercase variants the same pattern.)\\n\\n### One vowel-harmony fixup applied manually\\n\\nThe string *\\"...zaten aktif bir sat\u0131c\u0131s\u0131n\u0131z.\\"* has the 2nd-person plural copula suffix `-s\u0131n\u0131z` (back-vowel paradigm). Sed only replaced the `sat\u0131c\u0131s\u0131` portion \u2192 produced `bayis\u0131n\u0131z`, which is grammatically wrong. The correct front-vowel form on the new stem is `bayisiniz`.\\n\\nA manual targeted Edit fixed the single occurrence: `bayis\u0131n\u0131z \u2192 bayisiniz`.\\n\\n### Files updated\\n\\n- `languages/mhm-rentiva-tr_TR.po` \u2014 ~130 substitutions across the catalog\\n- `languages/mhm-rentiva-tr_TR.mo` \u2014 recompiled via `msgfmt`\\n- `languages/mhm-rentiva-tr_TR.l10n.php` \u2014 regenerated via `wp i18n make-php` (WP 6.5+ priority format)\\n- `README-tr.md` \u2014 10 occurrences in marketing copy\\n- `changelog-tr.json` \u2014 v4.33.1 entry self-references updated to use the new term\\n- Plugin version 4.33.1 \u2192 4.33.2 + changelog entries (EN + TR + readme.txt)\\n\\n## What did NOT change\\n\\n- English copy is untouched\\n- All PHP / JavaScript / CSS code unchanged\\n- PHPUnit baseline holds at **824 / 824** (pure translation patch)\\n- No license-server upgrade required\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\nDrop-in replacement for v4.33.1. WordPress automatically loads the new `.l10n.php` / `.mo` files after the plugin update \u2014 no admin action needed beyond the standard update flow.\\n\\n## Links\\n\\n- [GitHub Release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.33.2)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.33.1-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.1-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.33.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-rentiva-v4.33.1-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.33.1 \u2014 Search Polish & Vendor Name Fix","description":"A focused patch bundling three fixes around vehicle admin and the Featured Vehicles surface \u2014 the Lifecycle meta box now identifies the vendor by name, the Featured Vehicles slider stops flickering on short lists, and Featured Vehicles gains a \\"View All\\" link in parity with Vehicles Grid.","date":"2026-04-29T18:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"ux","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/ux"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"}],"readingTime":2.35,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.33.1-release","title":"Rentiva v4.33.1 \u2014 Search Polish & Vendor Name Fix","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","ux","patch"],"date":"2026-04-29T18:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.2 \u2014 Turkish Terminology Cleanup","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.2-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.0 \u2014 Pro Gate Unification","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.0-release"}},"content":"A focused patch bundling three fixes around vehicle admin and the Featured Vehicles surface \u2014 the Lifecycle meta box now identifies the vendor by name, the Featured Vehicles slider stops flickering on short lists, and Featured Vehicles gains a \\"View All\\" link in parity with Vehicles Grid.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why this release exists\\n\\nThree small frictions had been piling up:\\n\\n1. The Lifecycle meta box on the vehicle edit screen rendered the vendor\'s reliability score (e.g. *Vendor Score: 100/100 \u2014 Excellent*) without saying which vendor the score belonged to. Admins had to cross-reference the users list to find out.\\n2. The Featured Vehicles slider used Swiper\'s `loop: true` unconditionally. On short lists (slide count \u2264 columns \xd7 2) Swiper\'s loop algorithm doesn\'t have enough duplicate slides to cycle, and the slider rotates through blank frames.\\n3. Vehicles Grid had a *View All* link below the grid (`view_all_url` / `view_all_text` attributes); Featured Vehicles did not. Two shortcodes that should behave consistently were not.\\n\\nThis release fixes all three.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### Fixed: Lifecycle meta box now identifies the vendor by name\\n\\n`src/Admin/Vehicle/Meta/LifecycleMetaBox.php` now resolves the vendor from `$post->post_author` and renders a **Vendor:** row above the reliability score:\\n\\n```\\nStatus: Active\\nStarted: 30 Mar 2026\\nExpires: 28 Jun 2026 (60 days)\\n\\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\\nVendor: Acme Filo Kiralama\\nVendor Score: 100/100 \u2014 Excellent\\n```\\n\\nResolution chain: `$user->display_name` \u2192 `$user->user_login` (fallback when display name is empty). The vendor row is never blank for a non-zero `post_author`.\\n\\n### Fixed: Featured Vehicles slider stops flickering on short lists\\n\\n`assets/js/frontend/featured-vehicles.js` now counts `.swiper-slide` elements on the page before initializing Swiper, and only enables `loop: true` when there are more slides than `columns \xd7 2`:\\n\\n```js\\nconst slideCount = container.find(\'.swiper-slide\').length;\\nconst enableLoop = slideCount > columns * 2;\\n\\nnew Swiper(container[0], {\\n    loop: enableLoop,\\n    // ...\\n});\\n```\\n\\nFew slides = plain swipe (no loop, no flicker). Many slides = infinite loop (the original behavior). Automatic; no user-facing setting.\\n\\n### Added: `view_all_url` and `view_all_text` for Featured Vehicles\\n\\nParity with Vehicles Grid. Three surfaces:\\n\\n**Shortcode:**\\n```\\n[rentiva_featured_vehicles limit=\\"6\\" view_all_url=\\"/vehicles/\\" view_all_text=\\"See All Cars\\"]\\n```\\n\\n**Elementor widget:** Two new fields in the *Carousel Options* panel (*View All URL* and *View All Button Text*).\\n\\n**Gutenberg block:** Two new TextControls in Inspector Controls (visible after a URL is entered).\\n\\nThe link renders in the template footer when `view_all_url` is non-empty. Default text is \\"View All Vehicles\\" (translatable).\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- 822 \u2192 **824 PHPUnit** (+2: `lifecycle_meta_box_renders_vendor_display_name`, `lifecycle_meta_box_falls_back_to_user_login_when_display_name_is_empty`)\\n- `FeaturedVehiclesDefaultsParityTest` extended with two new mappings (`view_all_url`, `view_all_text`)\\n- PHPCS: 0 errors across the six changed files\\n- i18n: 2 new strings (*Vendor:*, *Adds a \\"View All\\" link below the carousel...*) with Turkish translations; existing *View All Vehicles* / *View All URL* / *View All Button Text* translations reused from Vehicles Grid via `msgmerge` (fuzzy=0)\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\nNo license-server upgrade required. Drop-in replacement for v4.33.0.\\n\\n## Links\\n\\n- [GitHub Release](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.33.1)"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.33.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-27-rentiva-v4.33.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-27-rentiva-v4.33.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.33.0 \u2014 Pro Gate Unification","description":"v4.33.0 closes three holes left over from the v4.31.0 RSA token migration: 22 callsites that bypassed the token check, a misleading License Admin message, and the impossibility of testing Pro features locally without running a license server.","date":"2026-04-27T18:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"license","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/license"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"}],"readingTime":4.92,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.33.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.33.0 \u2014 Pro Gate Unification","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","license","security"],"date":"2026-04-27T18:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.1 \u2014 Search Polish & Vendor Name Fix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.1-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Currency Switcher v0.7.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/cs-v0.7.0-release"}},"content":"v4.33.0 closes three holes left over from the v4.31.0 RSA token migration: 22 callsites that bypassed the token check, a misleading License Admin message, and the impossibility of testing Pro features locally without running a license server.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why this release exists\\n\\nv4.31.0 introduced RSA-signed feature tokens as the single Pro authority via `Mode::featureGranted()`. Every Pro feature gate was supposed to call this method (or one of the `canUse*()` wrappers that delegate to it). But 22 places in the codebase still called the old `Mode::featureEnabled()` API, which only checked `isPro()` \u2014 no token verify. A cracked binary patching `LicenseManager::isActive()` to return `true` could unlock messages, advanced reports, and exports at those callsites without ever having a valid token.\\n\\nThis release migrates every callsite, soft-deprecates the old API, and adds two UX fixes that were piling up.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd12 Security: 22 callsites now token-verify\\n\\n| File | Callsites |\\n|---|---|\\n| `Frontend/Account/AccountRenderer.php` | 1 |\\n| `Frontend/Account/WooCommerceIntegration.php` | 2 |\\n| `Messages/Core/Messages.php` | 1 |\\n| `Messages/Frontend/CustomerMessages.php` | 1 |\\n| `Messages/REST/*.php` (3 files) | 3 |\\n| `Reports/Reports.php` | 2 |\\n| `Utilities/Export/Export.php` | 3 |\\n| `Utilities/Export/ExportReports.php` | 6 |\\n| `Utilities/Menu/Menu.php` | 3 |\\n\\nAll migrated to the appropriate `Mode::canUse*()` method. `Mode::featureEnabled()` is now a soft-deprecated wrapper that emits a `_deprecated_function()` notice in `WP_DEBUG`. The body is preserved for any third-party callers; hard removal slated for v5.0.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd27 License Admin: actual state instead of static text\\n\\nThe License page used to print **\\"All Pro features active: Unlimited vehicles/bookings, export, advanced reports, Vendor & Payout.\\"** every time a license was active \u2014 regardless of which feature tokens the server had actually granted. Customers with empty or partial tokens would read that line and then wonder why the Vendor menu was missing.\\n\\nThe new rendering derives the list from real gate decisions:\\n\\n> Active Pro features: Vendor & Payout, Advanced Reports, Messages, Expanded Export\\n\\nIf no gates are active (license active but token empty \u2014 a state that shouldn\'t normally happen but did during the v4.30.x \u2192 v4.31.0 transition), the page now shows a warning notice with a \\"Re-validate Now\\" CTA instead of the misleading text.\\n\\n### \u2728 Developer Mode for local Pro testing\\n\\nAdding a Pro feature locally has been awkward since v4.31.0: the RSA-signed feature token is issued by the license server, which devs may not run on their machine. The result was a fail-closed gate \u2014 local Pro features were untestable without copying tokens from production (which you shouldn\'t).\\n\\nTwo new constants enable a bypass:\\n\\n```php\\n// wp-config.php (development only)\\ndefine( \'WP_DEBUG\', true );\\ndefine( \'MHM_RENTIVA_DEV_PRO\', true );\\n```\\n\\nWhen **both** are true, `Mode::featureGranted()` skips the token verification step and returns `true`. The `isPro()` check still runs first, so a Lite license cannot bypass to Pro \u2014 you still need an active license, just not a valid token.\\n\\nProduction safety: Hostinger production environments have `WP_DEBUG=false` by default, so even if `MHM_RENTIVA_DEV_PRO` slipped into a production `wp-config.php` (it shouldn\'t), the bypass would not engage.\\n\\nThe yellow \\"Geli\u015ftirici Modu\\" banner subtitle now reflects whether the bypass is actually active or just dormant.\\n\\nA new filter `mhm_rentiva_dev_pro_bypass` exposes the bypass decision for testability \u2014 PHPUnit cannot toggle PHP defines within a single process.\\n\\n### \u26a0\ufe0f BREAKING: Lite users lose xlsx/pdf export access\\n\\nOld `featureEnabled(FEATURE_EXPORT)` returned `true` unconditionally for Lite users. This was a bug \u2014 the format check in callers (`! in_array($format, [\'csv\', \'json\'])`) was supposed to be the second gate, but `featureEnabled` short-circuited it. So Lite users could request xlsx and pdf exports.\\n\\n`canUseExport()` correctly returns `false` for Lite. CSV and JSON are still free; xlsx and pdf are now Pro-only as intended.\\n\\nMigration path for affected Lite users: upgrade to Pro for full format access, or stick with CSV/JSON.\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf10 Translation quality (collateral)\\n\\nThe v4.33.0 i18n pass triggered a `msgmerge` over the entire TR catalog. Some pre-existing translations had been auto-flagged as fuzzy in earlier releases and never reviewed. We fixed 22 of them in this pass:\\n\\n- **\\"Airport Transfer\\"** had been mistranslated as **\\"Aktar\u0131m\u0131 \u0130zin Ver\\"** (literally \\"Allow Transfer\\"). Now correctly **\\"Havaliman\u0131 Transferi\\"**.\\n- **\\"Report Issue\\"** was **\\"Raporlar\\"** (Reports). Now **\\"Sorun Bildir\\"**.\\n- Multiple plural forms shifted from `%d/%d` to positional `%1$d/%2$d` (matches the source argument order).\\n- A handful of email label colons that had been dropped in earlier passes were restored.\\n\\n`msgmerge` fuzzy count post-merge: 0 \u2014 verified by automation.\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n| Component | Required version |\\n|---|---|\\n| `mhm-license-server` | **v1.11.2** (adds `\'export\'` to the issued feature-token allowlist) |\\n| `mhm-polar-bridge` | v1.9.0+ |\\n| WordPress | 6.7+ |\\n| PHP | 8.1+ |\\n\\nIf v4.33.0 ships before mhm-license-server v1.11.2, **Pro users will lose xlsx/pdf export for up to 24 hours** \u2014 the new `canUseExport()` gate looks for an `\'export\'` token claim that the server doesn\'t issue yet. The server\'s daily cron reissues tokens; manually clicking \\"Re-validate Now\\" on the License page refreshes immediately.\\n\\nThat\'s why the release chain order is server v1.11.2 first, then plugin v4.33.0.\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- 807 \u2192 822 PHPUnit (+15)\\n  - 5 in `ModeDevBypassTest`\\n  - 4 in `LicenseAdminActiveFeaturesTest`\\n  - 6 in `ModeGateMigrationTest`\\n- PHPCS: 0 errors, 0 warnings (release scope)\\n- Plugin Check (WordPress.org compliance): 0 ERROR, 27 WARNING (all pre-existing, all known false-positives from Plugin Check not reading `phpcs.xml` prefix config)\\n\\n## Upgrade notes\\n\\n1. Wait until mhm-license-server v1.11.2 is live (otherwise Pro export breaks for ~24h).\\n2. Update the plugin via WP Admin \u2192 Plugins \u2192 Upload, or replace the ZIP via FTP.\\n3. After update, click \\"Re-validate Now\\" on the License page once. This forces the client to fetch a fresh token from the server \u2014 without it, the daily cron is the next refresh window.\\n4. Lite users who relied on (bug-enabled) xlsx exports: upgrade to Pro, or switch to CSV/JSON.\\n\\n## Local development\\n\\nIf you maintain a fork or extend the plugin:\\n\\n```php\\n// wp-config.php\\ndefine( \'WP_DEBUG\', true );\\ndefine( \'MHM_RENTIVA_DEV_PRO\', true );  // skip token check, exercise Pro gates\\n```\\n\\nThis unlocks Vendor Marketplace, Advanced Reports, Messages, and Expanded Export against an active license without a real RSA-signed token. Don\'t ship this to production."},{"id":"cs-v0.7.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/cs-v0.7.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-27-cs-v0.7.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-27-cs-v0.7.0-release.md","title":"Currency Switcher v0.7.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","description":"The License tab now has a Manage Subscription button that opens the Polar customer portal in a new tab. Cancel auto-renewal, update your card, switch plans, or resubscribe \u2014 all without leaving WordPress admin. Snake-case + REST/React parity to MHM Rentiva v4.32.0.","date":"2026-04-27T08:30:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"currency-switcher","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/currency-switcher"},{"inline":true,"label":"license","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/license"}],"readingTime":2.21,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"cs-v0.7.0-release","title":"Currency Switcher v0.7.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","currency-switcher","license"],"date":"2026-04-27T08:30"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.33.0 \u2014 Pro Gate Unification","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.33.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.32.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.32.0-release"}},"content":"The License tab now has a **Manage Subscription** button that opens the Polar customer portal in a new tab. Cancel auto-renewal, update your card, switch plans, or resubscribe \u2014 all without leaving WordPress admin. Snake-case + REST/React parity to **MHM Rentiva v4.32.0**.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\nInside the License tab\'s **License Management** zone (visible when a Pro license is active), a third button joins the existing two:\\n\\n1. **Manage Subscription** \u2014 opens Polar customer portal (this release)\\n2. Re-validate Now\\n3. Deactivate License\\n\\nThe plugin reaches Polar through the same license server already in use. No new external services contacted from your site\'s perspective. Schema and signature integrity remain RSA-protected (v0.6.0+ pipeline).\\n\\n## State-driven emphasis\\n\\nThe button changes color based on how close your subscription is to renewal:\\n\\n| Days remaining | Color | Intent |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| > 30 | Standard primary blue | \\"Plenty of runway\\" |\\n| \u2264 30 | Yellow | \\"Heads up \u2014 renewal is coming\\" |\\n| \u2264 7 | Amber + glow | \\"Decide now\\" |\\n| Expired (0) | Amber + glow | \\"Resubscribe to keep Pro\\" |\\n\\nWhile the portal session is being minted (a brief async call), the button text becomes \\"Opening\u2026\\" and the styling dims to communicate the click registered.\\n\\n## Failure handling\\n\\nIf the portal session can\'t be minted (server error, network blip, license revoked between page load and click), the button surfaces an in-tab notice instead of breaking:\\n\\n> Subscription management is not available right now. Please try again later or contact support@wpalemi.com.\\n\\nNo raw technical strings ever leak to end users.\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n- New public method `LicenseManager::create_customer_portal_session(string $return_url): array` (snake_case parity to Rentiva\'s camelCase)\\n- New REST endpoint `POST /mhm-currency/v1/license/manage-subscription` (manage_options gated)\\n- New React state + callback in `License.jsx`, button rendered before Deactivate when `isActive && license.maskedKey`\\n- New CSS rules using compound selectors (`.button.mhm-cs-license-warning` / `.mhm-cs-license-urgent`) to avoid colliding with the existing `.mhm-cs-license-warning` alert pill\\n- 4 new translatable strings, all translated to Turkish\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n| Component | Required version |\\n|---|---|\\n| `mhm-license-server` | v1.11.0+ (new `/customer-portal-session` endpoint) |\\n| `mhm-polar-bridge` | v1.9.0+ (renewal reminder cron) |\\n| WordPress | 6.0+ |\\n| PHP | 7.4+ |\\n\\nOlder license-server versions without the customer-portal endpoint return a graceful in-tab notice instead of breaking.\\n\\n## Out of scope (not in this release)\\n\\n- Past-due / dunning notifications \u2014 Polar handles these directly via email.\\n- Yearly subscription renewal reminders \u2014 Polar sends these 7 days before renewal automatically.\\n\\nMonthly subscribers receive an additional 7-day-out reminder email from `mhm-polar-bridge v1.9.0+`, since Polar doesn\'t generate these for short billing cycles.\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- 148 \u2192 158 PHPUnit (+10 new across 2 test files)\\n- PHPCS new files: 0 errors (after PHPCBF)\\n- PHPStan level 6: 0 errors\\n- npm run build: success\\n- i18n: 0 fuzzy on new strings, all 4 translated"},{"id":"rentiva-v4.32.0-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.32.0-release","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-27-rentiva-v4.32.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-27-rentiva-v4.32.0-release.md","title":"Rentiva v4.32.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","description":"The License page now has a Manage Subscription button that opens the Polar customer portal in a new tab. Cancel auto-renewal, update your card, switch plans, or resubscribe \u2014 all without leaving WordPress admin.","date":"2026-04-27T08:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"license","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/license"}],"readingTime":2.02,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rentiva-v4.32.0-release","title":"Rentiva v4.32.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","rentiva","license"],"date":"2026-04-27T08:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Currency Switcher v0.7.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/cs-v0.7.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"License Security Hardening Sprint: Rentiva v4.30.0 \u2192 v4.30.2 (with mhm-license-server v1.9.0\u2013v1.9.3 and CS v0.5.x)","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/license-security-sprint-v4.30.x"}},"content":"The License page now has a **Manage Subscription** button that opens the Polar customer portal in a new tab. Cancel auto-renewal, update your card, switch plans, or resubscribe \u2014 all without leaving WordPress admin.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\nInside the License Management section (visible when a license is active), you\'ll now see three buttons:\\n\\n1. **Manage Subscription** \u2014 opens Polar customer portal (this release)\\n2. Re-validate Now (v4.31.2)\\n3. Deactivate License\\n\\nThe new button reaches Polar through the same license server already in use. No new external services contacted from your site\'s perspective. Schema and signature integrity remain RSA-protected (v4.30.0+ pipeline).\\n\\n## State-driven emphasis\\n\\nThe button changes color based on how close your subscription is to renewal:\\n\\n| Days remaining | Color | Intent |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| > 30 | Standard primary blue | \\"Plenty of runway\\" |\\n| \u2264 30 | Yellow | \\"Heads up \u2014 renewal is coming\\" |\\n| \u2264 7 | Amber + glow | \\"Decide now\\" |\\n| Expired (0) | Amber + glow | \\"Resubscribe to keep Pro\\" |\\n\\nCustomers always see how close their renewal is at a glance, regardless of whether they read the email reminders.\\n\\n## Failure handling\\n\\nIf the portal session can\'t be minted (server error, network blip, license revoked between page load and click), the admin lands back on the License page with a customer-friendly translated warning:\\n\\n> \u2139\ufe0f Subscription management is not available right now (service unavailable). Please try again later or contact support@wpalemi.com.\\n\\nFive reason codes are mapped to short Turkish labels via `get_manage_unavailable_label()` \u2014 no raw technical strings ever leak to end users.\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n- New public method `LicenseManager::createCustomerPortalSession(string $return_url): array`\\n- New admin-post handler `LicenseAdmin::handle_manage_subscription()` \u2014 capability + nonce gated\\n- New CSS file additions in `assets/css/admin/license-admin.css`, cache-busted via `filemtime`\\n- 9 new translatable strings, all translated to Turkish\\n\\n## Compatibility\\n\\n| Component | Required version |\\n|---|---|\\n| `mhm-license-server` | v1.11.0+ (new `/customer-portal-session` endpoint) |\\n| `mhm-polar-bridge` | v1.9.0+ (renewal reminder cron) |\\n| WordPress | 6.7+ |\\n| PHP | 8.1+ |\\n\\nOlder license-server versions without the customer-portal endpoint return a graceful `manage_unavailable` notice instead of breaking \u2014 customers see a translated warning, not a broken redirect.\\n\\n## Out of scope (not in this release)\\n\\n- **Past-due / dunning notifications** \u2014 Polar handles these directly via email.\\n- **Yearly subscription renewal reminders** \u2014 Polar sends these 7 days before renewal automatically.\\n\\nMonthly subscribers receive an additional 7-day-out reminder email from `mhm-polar-bridge v1.9.0+`, since Polar doesn\'t generate these for short billing cycles.\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- 793 \u2192 807 PHPUnit (+14 new across 3 test files)\\n- PHPCS: 0 errors\\n- i18n: 0 fuzzy on new strings, all 9 translated"},{"id":"license-security-sprint-v4.30.x","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/license-security-sprint-v4.30.x","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-25-license-security-sprint.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-25-license-security-sprint.md","title":"License Security Hardening Sprint: Rentiva v4.30.0 \u2192 v4.30.2 (with mhm-license-server v1.9.0\u2013v1.9.3 and CS v0.5.x)","description":"A two-day cross-plugin sprint that hardened the Rentiva (and Currency Switcher) Pro licensing layer against source-edit bypass attacks. Three Rentiva client releases (v4.30.0 / v4.30.1 / v4.30.2) shipped alongside four license-server releases (v1.9.0 \u2192 v1.9.3) and three Currency Switcher releases (v0.5.0 / v0.5.1 / v0.5.2). Live-deployed and verified end-to-end on mhmrentiva.com + wpalemi.com.","date":"2026-04-25T22:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"license","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/license"},{"inline":true,"label":"hardening","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/hardening"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-license-server","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-license-server"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-currency-switcher","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-currency-switcher"}],"readingTime":7.56,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"license-security-sprint-v4.30.x","title":"License Security Hardening Sprint: Rentiva v4.30.0 \u2192 v4.30.2 (with mhm-license-server v1.9.0\u2013v1.9.3 and CS v0.5.x)","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","security","license","hardening","mhm-rentiva","mhm-license-server","mhm-currency-switcher"],"date":"2026-04-25T22:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rentiva v4.32.0 \u2014 Manage your subscription from the plugin","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/rentiva-v4.32.0-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.4\u2013v4.27.6: Migration Lane Architecture, License Slug Forwarding, WordPress.org Polish","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability-sprint"}},"content":"A two-day cross-plugin sprint that hardened the Rentiva (and Currency Switcher) Pro licensing layer against source-edit bypass attacks. **Three Rentiva client releases** (v4.30.0 / v4.30.1 / v4.30.2) shipped alongside **four license-server releases** (v1.9.0 \u2192 v1.9.3) and **three Currency Switcher releases** (v0.5.0 / v0.5.1 / v0.5.2). Live-deployed and verified end-to-end on mhmrentiva.com + wpalemi.com.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why this sprint happened\\n\\nThe Rentiva plugin source ships on a **public GitHub repository**. A motivated attacker can clone, patch `Mode::canUseVendorMarketplace()` to `return true;`, and unlock Pro features without ever calling the license server. v1.8.0 closed *cross-product* key reuse (Currency Switcher key on Rentiva) but did nothing about source-edit bypass. **v4.30.x raises the cost: a crack now has to forge an HMAC signature, host a fake validator, AND keep emitting fresh feature tokens \u2014 and even then, tokens expire within 24 hours.**\\n\\nFive attack scenarios were used as the design target:\\n\\n| Attack | Mechanism | Defended by |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Source-edit `isActive() { return true; }` | Patch local Pro gate | Layer 4 (feature token) |\\n| Cross-product key reuse | Use CS key on Rentiva | Layer 1 (slug binding, v1.8.0) |\\n| Empty `product_slug` body | Strip the line, ride legacy compat | Layer 1 hardened in v1.9.3 |\\n| Fake activate POST from script | No control over claimed site | Layer 3 (reverse site validation) |\\n| Pirated key + fake server | DNS hijack to lookalike | Layer 2 (response signing) |\\n\\n## v4.30.0 \u2014 Phase B Client (the foundation, 2026-04-24)\\n\\nCompanion to **mhm-license-server v1.9.0** (Phase A \u2014 server-side three-layer defense).\\n\\n### Four new helpers under `src/Admin/Licensing/`\\n\\n- **`ClientSecrets`** \u2014 resolves three new wp-config constants (`MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_RESPONSE_HMAC_SECRET`, `MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_FEATURE_TOKEN_KEY`, `MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_PING_SECRET`).\\n- **`ResponseVerifier`** \u2014 HMAC-SHA256 verification of every signed activate/validate response. Mirrors the server\'s recursive ksort + JSON_UNESCAPED_SLASHES|UNICODE canonicalization byte-for-byte \u2014 drift = legitimate responses look tampered.\\n- **`FeatureTokenVerifier`** \u2014 verifies `{base64(json)}.{hmac}` tokens issued by the server. 24h TTL. `hasFeature($payload, $flag)` accessor used by Mode gates.\\n- **`VerifyEndpoint`** \u2014 public REST route `/wp-json/mhm-rentiva-verify/v1/ping` answering the server\'s `X-MHM-Challenge` during reverse validation.\\n\\n### Mode gate refactor\\n\\n`canUseVendorMarketplace()`, `canUseMessages()`, `canUseAdvancedReports()`, `canUseVendorPayout()` now route through a single `featureGranted()` private helper that:\\n\\n1. Hard-checks `isPro()` first\\n2. If `FEATURE_TOKEN_KEY` is unset \u2192 legacy `isPro()` fallback (existing customers don\'t break)\\n3. Otherwise verifies the locally-stored feature token\'s HMAC\\n4. Reads the specific flag from the payload (`vendor_marketplace`, `messaging`, `advanced_reports`, etc.)\\n\\nA `return true;` patch on `isActive()` no longer unlocks anything because the gate independently asks for a server-granted flag.\\n\\n### LicenseManager wiring\\n\\n- `activate()` request body now includes `client_version = MHM_RENTIVA_VERSION`. Server uses this for per-version reverse-validation enforcement (\u22654.30.0 floor for Rentiva).\\n- Successful response\'s `feature_token` field is persisted alongside the existing license record.\\n- Daily verification cron refreshes the token on every tick.\\n\\n### Test coverage\\n\\n6 new test files, **36 new tests** across `tests/Unit/Licensing/` and `tests/Integration/Licensing/`. Total: 776 / 2715, PHPCS clean, 3 new TR translations.\\n\\n## v4.30.1 \u2014 Reverse Validation UX Fix (2026-04-25 morning)\\n\\nv4.30.0 made `MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_PING_SECRET` **mandatory** \u2014 without it, `VerifyEndpoint` returned 503 `ping_secret_not_configured`, and the license server then rejected activation with `site_unreachable`. **Every customer site needed an operator-pinned secret in `wp-config.php`** \u2014 unworkable for an end-customer product.\\n\\n### Fix\\n\\n`VerifyEndpoint::handle_ping()` falls back to the per-activation `site_hash` (computed the same way `LicenseManager::siteHash()` does \u2014 `sha256(home_url + site_url)` JSON-encoded) when `ClientSecrets::getPingSecret()` returns empty. Server-side `mhm-license-server v1.9.1+` applies the matching fallback in `Security\\\\SiteVerifier`, so the HMAC challenge stays verifiable even though `site_hash` is technically not secret.\\n\\n### Why it\'s still safe\\n\\n`site_hash` is publicly derivable, but tampering still fails because the reverse ping targets the claimed `site_url`. An attacker that doesn\'t control that domain cannot intercept the GET and reply with a forged HMAC, regardless of whether the HMAC key is private.\\n\\n### Backward compatibility\\n\\nWhen `MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_PING_SECRET` IS defined, `VerifyEndpoint` still uses it \u2014 v4.30.0 deploys with operator config baked in keep working unchanged.\\n\\n## v4.30.2 \u2014 License Notice Defensive Fix (2026-04-25 afternoon)\\n\\nTwo layered bugs in `LicenseAdmin::admin_notices()`:\\n\\n### Bug A \u2014 Empty error_message rendered \\"License activation failed: \\" (with empty trailing space)\\n\\nStale URL state (`?license=error` without `&message=...`, e.g. browser back/forward, bookmark, truncated copy-paste) leaked through the `match`\'s default arm into a `sprintf(\\"...: %s\\", \'\')` call. Visible at the top of the License page even though the customer hadn\'t pressed anything.\\n\\n### Bug B \u2014 Missing match arms for v1.8.0+/v1.9.x server error codes\\n\\n`site_unreachable`, `site_verification_failed`, `tampered_response`, `product_mismatch`, `product_slug_required` had no friendly translations. They fell through to the same default arm, leaking raw technical codes to end users (\\"License activation failed: site_unreachable\\").\\n\\n### Fix (three layers)\\n\\n1. **Defensive guard:** `if (\'\' === $error_message) { break; }` skips the notice entirely when there\'s no actionable code.\\n2. **Five new match arms** with customer-friendly EN strings + Turkish translations.\\n3. **Generic default + `data-error-code` attribute:** unknown future codes render \\"License activation failed. Please try again.\\" with the technical code exposed via a `data-error-code` HTML attribute (debug / support only \u2014 never inline text).\\n\\n### Stable tag drift caught\\n\\nWhile bumping the version, an audit caught that `readme.txt` Stable tag had been stuck at `4.30.0` \u2014 the v4.30.1 release accidentally skipped the bump. v4.30.2 corrects to `4.30.2`.\\n\\n### Test coverage\\n\\n`tests/Unit/Licensing/LicenseAdminAdminNoticesTest.php` \u2014 5 new tests covering empty defense, `site_unreachable` mapping, generic default + data attribute, and two regression cases (`activated`, no-license-query). Total: **781 / 2726**, PHPCS clean.\\n\\n### Live verification\\n\\nChrome DevTools MCP scripted a tour of mhmrentiva.com after v4.30.2 deployment:\\n\\n| URL | Expected | Live result |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `?license=error` | No notice (defensive guard) | \u2705 0 notice elements |\\n| `?license=error&message=site_unreachable` | Friendly EN message + `data-error-code=\\"site_unreachable\\"`, no raw code in inline text | \u2705 confirmed via DOM script |\\n| `?license=error&message=imaginary_code_42` | Generic message + `data-error-code=\\"imaginary_code_42\\"`, no raw code in inline text | \u2705 confirmed |\\n\\n## Companion server releases (mhm-license-server, on wpalemi.com)\\n\\n- **v1.9.0** \u2014 Phase A: HMAC response signing, reverse site validation, feature token issuer (24h TTL).\\n- **v1.9.1** \u2014 `site_hash` fallback inside `Security\\\\SiteVerifier::verify()` (paired with v4.30.1 client).\\n- **v1.9.2** \u2014 `SecretManager::getPingSecret()` opt-in only (no file fallback) \u2014 closed an asymmetric HMAC bug where the server auto-generated `wp-uploads/mhm-license-secrets/ping.key` while customers ran zero-config and the two paths produced different HMAC keys.\\n- **v1.9.3 (CRITICAL)** \u2014 `LicenseActivator::activate()` now hard-rejects empty `product_slug` against a slug-bound license row. The previous code path let a single source edit drop the slug from the request body and slide through both v1.8.0 binding AND v1.9.0 reverse validation (because `REVERSE_VALIDATION_FLOOR[\'\'] === null` took the legacy-pass branch).\\n\\nCombined: **143 PHPUnit, 398 assertions, PHPCS clean** on the server side.\\n\\nThree live attack scenarios were curl-verified against `wpalemi.com` after v1.9.3 deployment:\\n\\n| Scenario | Expected | Live result |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `product_slug` removed from body | `product_slug_required` reject | \u2705 confirmed |\\n| Cross-product slug swap (CS slug + Rentiva site) | `site_unreachable` (CS verify endpoint absent on Rentiva site) | \u2705 confirmed |\\n| Correct flow regression | 200 active | \u2705 confirmed |\\n\\n## Companion Currency Switcher releases\\n\\n`mhm-currency-switcher v0.5.0` (Phase C client) \u2192 `v0.5.1` (CI hotfix: `str_ends_with` PHP 7.4 compat + `OrderFilterTest` `WC_Order` stub) \u2192 `v0.5.2` (`VerifyEndpoint` `site_hash` fallback). Same five-attack-surface defense applied to CS Mode gates with eight feature flags (`fixed_pricing`, `nav_menu_switcher`, `flag_library`, `geolocation`, `payment_restrictions`, `auto_rate_update`, `multilingual`, `rest_api_filter`).\\n\\n## Customer-facing impact\\n\\nAfter this sprint, customers on Rentiva v4.30.1+ (and CS v0.5.2+):\\n\\n- **Just enter the license key and click Activate.** No `wp-config.php` edits.\\n- Server-side three-layer defense (slug binding + response signing + reverse validation) is fully active.\\n- License notice messages are friendly and locale-aware; no raw technical jargon visible.\\n- Existing v4.27.x installs keep working unchanged through legacy fallback paths until they upgrade.\\n\\n## Known limitation (deferred)\\n\\nA sufficiently determined attacker running a cracked plugin binary on **their own** site with **their own** product-matching license can still patch `Mode::canUse*()` directly when the customer has not defined `MHM_RENTIVA_LICENSE_FEATURE_TOKEN_KEY` in `wp-config.php` (zero-config deployment intentionally accepts this trade-off).\\n\\nClosing the source-edit + zero-config gap requires **asymmetric crypto** (RSA-signed feature tokens, public key embedded in the plugin source \u2014 open-source-safe). This is deferred to **mhm-license-server v1.10.0 + mhm-rentiva v4.31.0 + mhm-currency-switcher v0.6.0**, planned post-launch.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Lessons captured (memory + KB)\\n\\n- **`patterns/license-defense-in-depth-stack.md`** \u2014 five-layer defense documentation, attack matrix, asymmetric crypto roadmap.\\n- **`patterns/admin-notice-url-state-defense.md`** \u2014 three-layer defense for redirect-after-action notices (empty guard + generic default + data attribute).\\n- **`patterns/release-zip-audit.md`** \u2014 three audits before tag/release; caught three ZIP leaks during this sprint (`drafts/`, `bin/`, `*.po~`).\\n- **`standards/i18n-workflow.md`** \u2014 updated with `.po~` msgmerge backup pattern + `.l10n.php` deploy mandate.\\n- **`wp-conductor` skill** \u2014 new \\"Long Session / Chained Release Discipline\\" gate with per-release verification requirements (8 release chain on 2026-04-25 was the baseline failure that motivated this).\\n\\n---\\n\\n*GitHub Releases:*\\n- *Rentiva: [v4.30.0](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.30.0) \xb7 [v4.30.1](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.30.1) \xb7 [v4.30.2](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.30.2)*\\n- *License Server: [v1.9.0](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-license-server/releases/tag/v1.9.0) \xb7 [v1.9.1](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-license-server/releases/tag/v1.9.1) \xb7 [v1.9.2](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-license-server/releases/tag/v1.9.2) \xb7 [v1.9.3](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-license-server/releases/tag/v1.9.3)*\\n- *Currency Switcher: [v0.5.0](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-currency-switcher/releases/tag/v0.5.0) \xb7 [v0.5.1](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-currency-switcher/releases/tag/v0.5.1) \xb7 [v0.5.2](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-currency-switcher/releases/tag/v0.5.2)*"},{"id":"v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability-sprint","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability-sprint","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.4\u2013v4.27.6: Migration Lane Architecture, License Slug Forwarding, WordPress.org Polish","description":"A retrospective covering three patch releases shipped in succession on 2026-04-23: a critical migration architecture fix (v4.27.4), per-product license binding compatibility (v4.27.5), and WordPress.org submission readiness (v4.27.6). Backfilling these blog posts now in the wake of the v4.30.x security sprint.","date":"2026-04-23T22:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"migration","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/migration"},{"inline":true,"label":"license","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/license"},{"inline":true,"label":"wordpress-org","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/wordpress-org"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":3.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability-sprint","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.4\u2013v4.27.6: Migration Lane Architecture, License Slug Forwarding, WordPress.org Polish","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","migration","license","wordpress-org","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-23T22:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"License Security Hardening Sprint: Rentiva v4.30.0 \u2192 v4.30.2 (with mhm-license-server v1.9.0\u2013v1.9.3 and CS v0.5.x)","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/license-security-sprint-v4.30.x"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.2: Settings Testing Pollution Hotfix + Duplicate Addon Notice Dedupe","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.2-settings-testing-pollution-hotfix"}},"content":"A retrospective covering three patch releases shipped in succession on 2026-04-23: a **critical migration architecture fix** (v4.27.4), **per-product license binding compatibility** (v4.27.5), and **WordPress.org submission readiness** (v4.27.6). Backfilling these blog posts now in the wake of the v4.30.x security sprint.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## v4.27.4 \u2014 Migration Lane Architecture Fix (CRITICAL)\\n\\nThe v4.27.1 (i18n locale leak) and v4.27.2 (Settings Testing pollution) data-cleanup migrations **never actually ran on upgraded sites** \u2014 the regression cleared during v4.27.0 prep had quietly broken the migration trigger.\\n\\n### Root cause\\n\\n`plugins_loaded` migration callback used a single short-circuit:\\n\\n```php\\nif ( $stored_version === MHM_RENTIVA_VERSION ) {\\n    return; // skip ALL migrations\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBut `mhm_rentiva_single_site_activation()` (which fires BEFORE `plugins_loaded` on any ZIP-replace upgrade path) had already stamped the new version into the option. By the time `plugins_loaded` fired, `$stored === $current` was true \u2192 **all flag-gated cleanups got skipped forever.**\\n\\nLive evidence at mhmrentiva.com: Brand Name displayed as `1`, currency stats rendered as `0,00 1` instead of `0,00 \u20ba` (because the v4.27.2 pollution migration never executed).\\n\\n### Fix \u2014 two-lane architecture\\n\\n`plugins_loaded` callback split into two independent lanes:\\n\\n- **Lane A (schema drift, version-gated):** runs only when `$stored !== $current`. Idempotent across multiple loads of the same version.\\n- **Lane B (flag-gated data cleanups):** runs on every request, but each migration has its own `mhm_rentiva_<flag>` option that flips after successful run. Genuinely idempotent.\\n\\nBoth lanes have their own error containment so a failure in Lane B never blocks Lane A or vice versa.\\n\\n### Test coverage\\n\\n`tests/Migration/MigrationLaneIndependenceTest.php` \u2014 3 new tests, 8 assertions guarding the split.\\n\\n### Empirical verification\\n\\nChrome DevTools MCP browser tour of mhmrentiva.com after deployment: 0 duplicate notices, stats display `0,00 \u20ba` (U+20BA), Brand Name reads \\"MHM Rentiva\\". Manual one-time **Reset to Defaults** across 11 admin tabs cleared residual state from the period when migrations weren\'t running.\\n\\n## v4.27.5 \u2014 License Client Per-Product Slug Forwarding\\n\\nPairs with `mhm-license-server v1.8.0+` which introduced per-product license binding. Before v4.27.5, a customer could buy a cheap MHM Currency Switcher Monthly key and use it to activate Rentiva Pro \u2014 server had no way to enforce that the license was issued for a specific product.\\n\\n### Change\\n\\n`LicenseManager::activate()` and `validate()` request bodies now include `product_slug => \'mhm-rentiva\'`. The server checks this against the license row\'s stored slug and rejects mismatches with a `product_mismatch` error.\\n\\n### Bonus fix\\n\\nAdditional Services admin page rendered two **Documentation** buttons \u2014 the global `all_admin_notices` docs hook + the page\'s own header both fired. The hook now skips the `vehicle_addon` screen; the page header\'s button is the single source.\\n\\n## v4.27.6 \u2014 WordPress.org Submission Polish\\n\\nPlugin Check (PCP) compliance for WordPress.org plugin directory submission: **1 ERROR + 115 WARNING \u2192 0 ERROR + 61 WARNING**. The remaining warnings are all false positives caused by Plugin Check not reading the project\'s `phpcs.xml` prefix configuration.\\n\\n### Concrete fixes\\n\\n- `unlink()` \u2192 `wp_delete_file()` in the demo image importer (the only real ERROR).\\n- Reasoned `phpcs:ignore` comments for warnings the project\'s ruleset already excludes (audit `error_log()` calls, `mhm_rentiva_` prefixed hooks Plugin Check refuses to recognise, accepted `meta_query` / `post__not_in` performance tradeoffs, ledger queries with core-controlled table names bound through `$wpdb->prepare()`).\\n- `$pending_messages` template-scope variable \u2192 `$mhm_rentiva_pending_messages` to honour Plugin Check\'s prefix convention.\\n- `readme.txt` Changelog section trimmed to fit WP.org\'s 5000-character limit; older releases linked to GitHub.\\n- `changelog-tr.json` backfill for v4.27.5 + new v4.27.6 entry.\\n\\n### No functional change\\n\\n740/740 PHPUnit still passes. PHPCS clean. The plugin behaves identically \u2014 only the Plugin Check noise was reduced.\\n\\n## \u2705 Verification across all three\\n\\n| Check | v4.27.4 | v4.27.5 | v4.27.6 |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| PHPUnit | 740/740, 2642 assertions, 6 skipped | unchanged | unchanged |\\n| PHPCS | 0 / 0 | 0 / 0 | 0 / 0 |\\n| Plugin Check ERROR | unchanged | unchanged | 1 \u2192 0 |\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Lessons captured (memory)\\n\\n- **`feedback_migration_lane_architecture.md`** \u2014 when activation hooks stamp version BEFORE `plugins_loaded`, the version gate breaks all flag-gated migrations. Always split version-drift and data-cleanup lanes.\\n- **`feedback_empirical_dom_verification.md`** \u2014 DOM-level verification through Chrome DevTools MCP is the only way to catch runtime-DB-state bugs that 100% PHPUnit + 0 PHPCS happily ship.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd1c Next\\n\\nThe v4.27.x umbrella closed here. Next major was v4.28.0 (Popular Routes) \u2014 but the security audit of the cross-product attack surface re-prioritised the roadmap into the **License Security Hardening** sprint (v4.30.x), shipped 2026-04-24/25.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*GitHub Releases: [v4.27.4](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.4) \xb7 [v4.27.5](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.5) \xb7 [v4.27.6](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.6)*"},{"id":"v4.27.2-settings-testing-pollution-hotfix","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.2-settings-testing-pollution-hotfix","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.2-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.2: Settings Testing Pollution Hotfix + Duplicate Addon Notice Dedupe","description":"After the v4.27.1 i18n hotfix, a user reported three more bugs \u2014 all originating from the same fresh-install scenario, all triggered by pressing \\"Run All Diagnostics\\" once on the Settings Testing page. v4.27.2 breaks the chain.","date":"2026-04-23T19:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/hotfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"settings","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/settings"},{"inline":true,"label":"diagnostics","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/diagnostics"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":4.26,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.27.2-settings-testing-pollution-hotfix","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.2: Settings Testing Pollution Hotfix + Duplicate Addon Notice Dedupe","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","hotfix","settings","diagnostics","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-23T19:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.4\u2013v4.27.6: Migration Lane Architecture, License Slug Forwarding, WordPress.org Polish","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.4-v4.27.6-stability-sprint"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.1: i18n Locale-Leak Hotfix \u2014 Vehicle Settings Labels No Longer Frozen at First-Install Language","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.1-i18n-locale-leak-hotfix"}},"content":"After the v4.27.1 i18n hotfix, a user reported three more bugs \u2014 all originating from the same fresh-install scenario, all triggered by **pressing \\"Run All Diagnostics\\" once on the Settings Testing page**. v4.27.2 breaks the chain.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Bug 1: All Text Fields Show \\"1\\" on Fresh Install\\n\\n**Scenario:**\\n1. Plugin is freshly installed.\\n2. User goes to **Settings \u2192 Settings Testing** tab and presses \\"Run All Diagnostics\\".\\n3. Returns to General Settings \u2014 **Brand Name = \\"1\\"**, **Cancellation Deadline = 1**, **Payment Deadline = 1**, Support Email, Brand Logo URL, etc. all show \\"1\\".\\n4. Pressing **\\"Reset to Defaults\\"** fixes it.\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n\\n`SettingsTester::test_settings_save()` was converting empty strings to `\'1\'` to trigger a \\"change detected save\\":\\n\\n```php\\n// Fresh install: $current_str == \'\'\\nif ( in_array( $current_str, array( \'0\', \'1\', \'\' ) ) ) {\\n    $test_value = ( $current_str === \'1\' ) ? \'0\' : \'1\'; // \u2192 \'1\'\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis `\'1\'` payload was then passed to the **real** sanitizer. The sanitizer rewrote ALL fields for the target tab (not just the key under test). The restore mechanism only reverted the explicitly tested keys \u2192 collateral writes to other tab fields persisted in the DB.\\n\\n**The critical point:** On a fresh install, when the General test runs:\\n- `brand_name` \u2192 \'1\' (test flip, then restored) \u2713\\n- `currency` \u2192 \'1\' (flip + restore) \u2713\\n- `dark_mode` \u2192 sanitizer wrote it, test never touched it \u2192 **stayed in DB**\\n- `support_email` \u2192 sanitizer wrote `admin@...` as default, then flipped to \'1\', not restored \u2192 **stayed in DB**\\n- ... and more\\n\\n### Fix\\n\\n#### 1. Harness fix \u2014 full snapshot/restore\\n\\n```php\\n// NEW v4.27.2: snapshot the ENTIRE option, restore the ENTIRE option.\\n$option_existed_before = false !== get_option( $option_name, false );\\n$full_option_snapshot  = (array) get_option( $option_name, array() );\\n\\n// ... test runs, sanitizer pollutes DB ...\\n\\nif ( $option_existed_before ) {\\n    update_option( $option_name, $full_option_snapshot );\\n} else {\\n    delete_option( $option_name );\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe test now leaves the DB truly read-only. Collateral writes are automatically undone.\\n\\n#### 2. Migration \u2014 clean up existing installs\\n\\n`SettingsCore::migrate_clean_test_pollution()` \u2014 one-time flagged migration (`mhm_rentiva_v4272_test_pollution_cleaned`):\\n\\n```php\\n$polluted_keys = array(\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_brand_name\', \'mhm_rentiva_email_from_name\',\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_email_from_address\', \'mhm_rentiva_support_email\',\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_booking_url\', \'mhm_rentiva_login_url\',\\n    \'mhm_rentiva_currency\', /* ... */\\n);\\n\\nforeach ($polluted_keys as $key) {\\n    $value = $settings[$key] ?? null;\\n    if (\'0\' === $value || \'1\' === $value) {\\n        unset($settings[$key]); // fallback to default\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nOnly cleans **text, email, URL, currency** fields that carry the pollution signature (`\'0\'` / `\'1\'`). Numeric fields (deadlines) are not touched \u2014 the user may genuinely have entered 1 (rare). Legitimate string values are preserved.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Bug 2: Duplicate Limit Notice on Add-ons Page\\n\\nThe Lite limit warning was appearing **twice** on the Additional Services admin page \u2014 once above and once below the stats cards.\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n\\n`AddonMenu::add_addon_page_title()` emitted the notice inside a nested `<div class=\\"wrap\\">` block. The WordPress core admin-notice relocator JS then:\\n- Placed the standard copy after the `wp-header-end` marker\\n- Left the original copy inside the inner wrap\\n- \u2192 Two copies\\n\\n### Fix\\n\\nThe notice is now emitted in a separate `admin_notices` callback \u2014 `AddonMenu::render_addon_limit_notice()` \u2014 at priority 20. It fires AFTER the inner wrap is closed, and WordPress places it exactly once.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Bug 3: Settings Testing \\"Defaults Set\\" Phantom Key FAILs\\n\\nThe Settings Testing page reported \\"Defaults Set: FAIL\\" for setting keys that do not exist anywhere:\\n- `mhm_rentiva_timezone` (not in General)\\n- `mhm_rentiva_db_auto_optimize` (not in Core)\\n- `mhm_rentiva_wp_optimization_enabled` (not in Core)\\n- `mhm_rentiva_my_account_url` (not in Frontend)\\n\\n### Fix\\n\\nRemoved these phantom keys from the check list. Additionally, the \\"Email Address Valid\\" and \\"Email Validation Works\\" FAILs were a side-effect of Bug 1 (`\'1\'` \u2192 `is_email(\'1\')` = false) \u2014 they clear automatically once the pollution migration runs.\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddea Tests\\n\\n`tests/Migration/SettingsTestPollutionMigrationTest.php` \u2014 **5 new tests, 19 assertions**:\\n\\n1. Text/email/URL/currency pollution is cleaned\\n2. Legitimate user values are preserved\\n3. Numeric fields (deadlines) are not touched\\n4. Post-migration legitimate \\"1\\" rename is not overwritten (idempotent)\\n5. Flag is set on fresh install\\n\\n## \u2705 Verification\\n\\n| Check | Result |\\n|---|---|\\n| PHPCS release | 0 error / 0 warning |\\n| PHPUnit | **737/737** (+5 new, 732\u2192737), 6 skipped, 0 regressions |\\n| Plugin Check (PCP) | 0 error, 3 trivial warnings (unchanged) |\\n\\n## \u26a0\ufe0f Upgrade Note\\n\\nUsers who pressed \\"Run All Diagnostics\\" and saw Brand Name = 1: the migration runs automatically on the next admin page load. **You do NOT need to press \\"Reset to Defaults\\"**. Text/email/URL/currency fields will revert to their defaults.\\n\\n**Numeric deadlines (Cancellation / Payment)** are not touched \u2014 the migration cannot distinguish these from a deliberate user choice. Manually set the deadlines in the Booking tab to 24 hours / 30 minutes (or your preferred values).\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Installation\\n\\n`mhm-rentiva.4.27.2.zip` \u2192 **Plugins \u2192 Add New \u2192 Upload Plugin**, or use the Rentiva Pro auto-updater.\\n\\n**Requirements:** PHP 8.1+, WordPress 6.7+.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Lesson\\n\\nAll three of these bugs \u2014 like the v4.27.1 i18n hotfix \u2014 are in the **runtime DB-state** class. Neither PHPCS, PCP, nor the unit test suite can catch them. They only surface when testing a fresh-install scenario through the real admin UI. The `feedback_runtime_smoke_test.md` memory note now reads **\\"fresh-install UI smoke test mandatory before every major release\\"** \u2014 the next major release will integrate this pattern into the checklist.\\n\\nIn context: we shipped 3 releases in one day \u2014 v4.27.0 (WPCS submission prep) \u2192 v4.27.1 (i18n locale leak) \u2192 v4.27.2 (Settings Testing pollution + duplicate Addon notice). Each with zero regressions and new regression tests. The agile patch pipeline works.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd1c Next\\n\\n- v4.28.0: Popular Routes shortcode/block/widget (new feature)\\n- v4.29.0: Vendor Report / Appeal System (new subsystem)\\n- The v4.27.x roadmap is closed \u2014 the next umbrella is v4.28.0\\n\\n---\\n\\n*GitHub Release: [v4.27.2](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.2)*"},{"id":"v4.27.1-i18n-locale-leak-hotfix","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.1-i18n-locale-leak-hotfix","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.1-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.1: i18n Locale-Leak Hotfix \u2014 Vehicle Settings Labels No Longer Frozen at First-Install Language","description":"A few hours after the v4.27.0 WordPress.org submission readiness release, a critical bug was caught: On an English WordPress site, the Vehicle Settings page was displaying Turkish labels. This is a global plugin; English is the primary language. The bug was submission-blocker severity. v4.27.1 fixes it.","date":"2026-04-23T18:30:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"hotfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/hotfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"i18n","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/i-18-n"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":3.2,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.27.1-i18n-locale-leak-hotfix","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.1: i18n Locale-Leak Hotfix \u2014 Vehicle Settings Labels No Longer Frozen at First-Install Language","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","hotfix","i18n","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-23T18:30"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.2: Settings Testing Pollution Hotfix + Duplicate Addon Notice Dedupe","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.2-settings-testing-pollution-hotfix"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.0: WordPress.org Submission Readiness \u2014 Zero PHPCS Errors, Zero PCP Errors","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.0-release-summary"}},"content":"A few hours after the v4.27.0 WordPress.org submission readiness release, a critical bug was caught: **On an English WordPress site, the Vehicle Settings page was displaying Turkish labels.** This is a global plugin; English is the primary language. The bug was submission-blocker severity. v4.27.1 fixes it.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Bug Scenario\\n\\nTypical reproduction steps:\\n1. Plugin is installed on a Turkish WordPress site; the Vehicle Settings page is visited once.\\n2. The site is switched to English (or a Turkish DB backup is restored onto an English site).\\n3. The admin panel still shows Turkish labels: **G\xfcnl\xfck Fiyat**, **Model Y\u0131l\u0131**, **Plaka**, **Klima**, **Yedek Lastik**...\\n\\nYet every `__( \'Daily Price\', \'mhm-rentiva\' )` call in the source code correctly returns the English value for the current WordPress locale. So why was the admin UI still showing Turkish?\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd0d Root Cause\\n\\n`VehicleMeta::ensure_default_options()` performed the following on the first admin page load:\\n\\n```php\\n$default_details = self::get_default_details(); // Array with TRANSLATED __() calls\\n// ...\\nif (get_option(\'mhm_vehicle_details\', array()) === array()) {\\n    update_option(\'mhm_vehicle_details\', $default_details); // \ud83d\udd25 Wrote Turkish values to DB\\n}\\n```\\n\\nInside `get_default_details()`:\\n```php\\nreturn array(\\n    \'price_per_day\' => __(\'Daily Price\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),   // Turkish site \u2192 \\"G\xfcnl\xfck Fiyat\\"\\n    \'year\'          => __(\'Model Year\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),    // Turkish site \u2192 \\"Model Y\u0131l\u0131\\"\\n    // ...\\n);\\n```\\n\\n`__()` returns the translation **for the locale active at the moment of the call**. With a Turkish site, this returned \\"G\xfcnl\xfck Fiyat\\" and wrote it to `wp_options`.\\n\\nLater, in the `get_all_available_details()` render flow:\\n```php\\n$details = self::get_default_details();              // live __() \u2192 English (site is EN now)\\n$stored  = get_option(\'mhm_vehicle_details\');        // FROZEN Turkish\\nforeach ($stored as $key => $label) {\\n    $details[$key] = $label;                         // Override: Turkish wins\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**The frozen translation always overwrote the live translation.**\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Fix\\n\\n### 1. Stop auto-persisting\\n\\nThe three `update_option(\'mhm_vehicle_*\', $translated_defaults)` calls inside `VehicleMeta::ensure_default_options()` were removed entirely. It continues to seed `mhm_selected_*` (key lists only \u2014 no translated strings).\\n\\n### 2. Clean up existing installs\\n\\nNew method `VehicleMeta::migrate_remove_auto_populated_labels()` \u2014 a one-time migration guarded by the `mhm_rentiva_v4271_labels_migrated` flag:\\n\\n```php\\nforeach ([\'mhm_vehicle_details\', \'mhm_vehicle_features\', \'mhm_vehicle_equipment\'] as $key) {\\n    $stored = get_option($key, null);\\n    if (is_array($stored) && !empty($stored)) {\\n        delete_option($key);\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nMigration is triggered inside the existing version-drift block on the `plugins_loaded` hook \u2014 runs across admin, cron, and WP-CLI flows.\\n\\n### 3. User custom fields are preserved\\n\\n`mhm_custom_details`, `mhm_custom_features`, `mhm_custom_equipment` \u2014 fields added by the user via \\"Add Custom\\" live in separate options. The migration does not touch them.\\n\\n## \u2696\ufe0f Trade-off\\n\\nIf you renamed a core field via \\"Edit Names\\" (e.g. \\"Daily Price\\" \u2192 \\"Rental Rate\\"), you will need to re-apply that rename once after upgrading. This is a rare scenario \u2014 but the bug affected every install. The trade-off is fair.\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddea Tests\\n\\n`tests/Migration/LocaleLeakLabelsMigrationTest.php` \u2014 **4 new regression tests, 13 assertions**:\\n\\n1. **Leaked label arrays are cleaned** (Turkish, English, and mixed content)\\n2. **Migration is idempotent** \u2014 second call is a no-op, does not overwrite a legitimate post-migration rename\\n3. **Fresh install** \u2014 no legacy option present; flag is still set (skips future calls)\\n4. **`mhm_custom_*`** \u2014 user custom fields are not touched\\n\\n## \u2705 Verification\\n\\n| Check | Result |\\n|---|---|\\n| PHPCS release scope | 0 error, 0 warning |\\n| PHPUnit | **732/732** (+4 new), 6 skipped, 0 regressions |\\n| Plugin Check (PCP) | 0 error, 3 trivial warnings (.distignore-excluded) |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Installation\\n\\n`mhm-rentiva.4.27.1.zip` \u2192 **Plugins \u2192 Add New \u2192 Upload Plugin**, or use the Rentiva Pro auto-updater.\\n\\n**Requirements:** PHP 8.1+, WordPress 6.7+.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd1c Next\\n\\n- **v4.27.2**: Search Results UX improvements + Shortcode Review Backlog (combined patch)\\n- **v4.28.0**: Popular Routes shortcode/block/widget (new feature)\\n- **v4.29.0**: Vendor Report / Appeal System (new subsystem)\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Lesson\\n\\nThis bug was caught **a few hours after the v4.27.0 WordPress.org submission readiness release**. The zero PHPCS / zero PCP validation suite had passed, but neither PHPCS nor PCP can see a _runtime_ bug (existing DB state overwriting `__()` output). Real admin UI testing is the only safeguard. We needed a smoke test run before WordPress.org submission \u2014 v4.27.1 establishes this pattern: **manual verification is mandatory for any UI that routes through the translation layer.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n*GitHub Release: [v4.27.1](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.1)*"},{"id":"v4.27.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-23-v4.27.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.0: WordPress.org Submission Readiness \u2014 Zero PHPCS Errors, Zero PCP Errors","description":"v4.27.0 is a milestone release completing the code quality audit ahead of submitting the plugin to the official WordPress.org plugin directory. The entire distributed codebase now passes the project\'s strict PHPCS ruleset with zero errors, zero warnings, and achieves zero errors against Plugin Check (PCP) \u2014 the official WordPress.org review tool. Four real defects uncovered during the process have also been closed.","date":"2026-04-23T14:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"minor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/minor"},{"inline":true,"label":"wpcs","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/wpcs"},{"inline":true,"label":"phpcs","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/phpcs"},{"inline":true,"label":"plugin-check","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/plugin-check"},{"inline":true,"label":"wordpress-org","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/wordpress-org"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"},{"inline":true,"label":"quality","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/quality"}],"readingTime":3.82,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.27.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.0: WordPress.org Submission Readiness \u2014 Zero PHPCS Errors, Zero PCP Errors","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","minor","wpcs","phpcs","plugin-check","wordpress-org","mhm-rentiva","quality"],"date":"2026-04-23T14:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.1: i18n Locale-Leak Hotfix \u2014 Vehicle Settings Labels No Longer Frozen at First-Install Language","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.1-i18n-locale-leak-hotfix"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.6: Vehicles Grid Shortcode Review Fixes","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.6-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.27.0 is a milestone release completing the code quality audit ahead of submitting the plugin to the official WordPress.org plugin directory. The entire distributed codebase now passes the project\'s strict PHPCS ruleset with **zero errors, zero warnings**, and achieves **zero errors** against Plugin Check (PCP) \u2014 the official WordPress.org review tool. Four real defects uncovered during the process have also been closed.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf Why This Release?\\n\\nWordPress.org submission can be summarised as: \\"they reject on the smallest error; too many warnings also means rejection.\\" Therefore:\\n\\n1. **Plugin Check (PCP) zero errors required** \u2014 the official review tool; human reviewers run this first.\\n2. **Zero errors under strict PHPCS ruleset** \u2014 so human reviewers don\'t see a messy codebase when scanning manually.\\n3. **PHPUnit 728/728 green** \u2014 functionality must be preserved.\\n\\nAll three were achieved.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcca Verification Summary\\n\\n| Check | Before | After |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| PHPCS errors | 5158 | **0** |\\n| PHPCS warnings | 1273 | **0** |\\n| Plugin Check errors | 37 | **0** |\\n| Plugin Check warnings | 326 | 3 trivial (excluded from release ZIP) |\\n| PHPUnit | 720/720 | **728/728** (+8 new tests, 0 regressions) |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd27 Real Defects (Found Along the Way)\\n\\nFour real bugs were identified during the cleanup:\\n\\n### 1. CurrencyHelper \u2014 Duplicate `\\"TRY\\"` Aliases\\nThe Turkish Lira normalisation map defined the `\\"\u20ba\\" => \'TRY\'` key silently twice. PHP overwrites the first with the second, so the map functioned correctly, but it was confusing to read. Removed.\\n\\n### 2. SearchResults \u2014 Duplicate `error` i18n Key\\nThe i18n dictionary passed to Search Results JavaScript defined the `error` key twice:\\n```php\\n\'error\' => __(\'An error occurred. Please try again.\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),\\n// ...\\n\'error\' => __(\'Error\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),  // This overwrote the first\\n```\\nThe long message was dead code; users only ever saw \\"Error\\". Restructured as a single key.\\n\\n### 3. WooCommerceBridge \u2014 Unreachable Duplicate `return`\\n```php\\nif (! $order) {\\n    return;\\n    return;  // This line was never reached\\n}\\n```\\nThe second `return` was removed.\\n\\n### 4. Cron Sweep Silent Exception Swallowing\\nThe `AutoCancel` and `AutoComplete` cron jobs processed each booking inside a `try/catch`, but the `catch` blocks were completely empty:\\n```php\\n} catch (\\\\Throwable $e) {\\n    // Handle silently in production\\n}\\n```\\nThe problem: an error in a single booking would stall the entire loop while leaving no trace in logs. Fix \u2014 the error is logged and the loop continues:\\n```php\\n} catch (\\\\Throwable $e) {\\n    error_log(\'[mhm-rentiva] auto-cancel skipped booking \' . $bid . \': \' . $e->getMessage());\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf0d i18n Gaps\\n\\n24 lines using `sprintf` / `_n` / `__` with placeholders (`%s`, `%d`, `%1$d`) were missing translator comments. The standard comment was added to each:\\n\\n```php\\n/* translators: %d: maximum number of vehicles allowed in Lite tier */\\nsprintf( __( \'%d vehicles\', \'mhm-rentiva\' ), $max_vehicles );\\n```\\n\\nAffected areas: license dashboard Lite limits, message widget, dashboard countdown, vehicle lifecycle error messages, vendor settings, vendor booking detail, upcoming operations table.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Mechanical Updates\\n\\n- **`json_encode()` \u2192 `wp_json_encode()`**: 18 call sites updated (CLI commands, REST helpers, reports, exports, notifications, GDPR tools).\\n- **`declare(strict_types=1)`**: Added to two block placeholder files.\\n- **Control structure assignments**: Two instances of the `if ($cached = ...)` pattern split into two-line form.\\n- **Loop condition `count()`**: Computed once and stored in a variable inside the IP masking helper.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb phpcs.xml \u2014 Defensible Suppress Block\\n\\nMost of the 678 remaining violations were not \\"real defects\\" from a WordPress.org perspective, but the ruleset flagged them anyway. Each sniff was suppressed with a documented justification:\\n\\n- **Public API Stability**: `ValidFunctionName.MethodNameInvalid` (194), `ValidHookName.UseUnderscores` (45), reserved keyword parameter names \u2014 renaming these would break all Elementor widgets, theme overrides, and third-party integrations. Addressed in a v5.0 major release with documented migration.\\n- **Discouraged-but-not-forbidden PHP functions**: `base64_encode/decode` (HMAC signature), `serialize` (legacy WP options), `urlencode` (RFC 3986), `file_get_contents` (local asset), `error_log` (structured log) \u2014 WordPress core uses the same functions.\\n- **Performance heuristics**: `meta_query`, `posts_per_page`, `post__not_in` \u2014 each usage is justified; the alternative (custom tables) requires a major migration.\\n- **Codex quality noise**: `unused-after-last-used` (hook callback signatures), `loose-equal`, `short-ternary` (standard PHP feature), `current_time(\'timestamp\')` \u2014 intentional choices.\\n- **WP global accessor pattern**: `$wp_query`, `$post`, `$wpdb` \u2014 WP public API.\\n- **Sub-15-minute cron**: `CronSchedulesInterval` \u2014 booking auto-cancel runs every 5 minutes; this is a UX decision.\\n- **Template strict types**: The `templates/` directory is excluded from the `RequireStrictTypes` rule (type juggling required).\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Tooling\\n\\n- **`phpcompatibility/phpcompatibility-wp`** added as a dev dependency; `PHPCompatibilityWP` rule re-enabled with `testVersion=8.1-`.\\n- Composer scripts: `phpcs:release`, `phpcbf:release`, `plugin-check:release` \u2014 repeatable verification.\\n- Local `*fixer*.php` dev tools and the `.worktrees/` directory excluded from the release ZIP via `.distignore`.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Installation\\n\\nDownload `mhm-rentiva.4.27.0.zip` and install via **Plugins \u2192 Add New \u2192 Upload Plugin**, or use the Rentiva Pro auto-updater.\\n\\n**Requirements:** PHP 8.1+, WordPress 6.7+.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd1c Next\\n\\n- v4.26.8 shortcode review backlog\\n- v4.26.9 Popular Routes shortcode (transfer location showcase)\\n- v4.27.x: WP 6.9 final test pass and official WordPress.org submission\\n\\n---\\n\\n*GitHub Release: [v4.27.0](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.27.0)*"},{"id":"v4.26.6-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.6-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.6-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.6-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.6: Vehicles Grid Shortcode Review Fixes","description":"v4.26.6 is the product of a shortcode review session during YouTube stream preparation. Accumulated silent bugs in the rentivavehiclesgrid and rentivafeaturedvehicles shortcodes have been resolved, and two new features \u2014 viewallurl and a service type badge \u2014 have been added.","date":"2026-04-15T23:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"shortcode","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/shortcode"},{"inline":true,"label":"vehicles-grid","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vehicles-grid"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured-vehicles","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/featured-vehicles"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":1.87,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.6-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.6: Vehicles Grid Shortcode Review Fixes","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","shortcode","vehicles-grid","featured-vehicles","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-15T23:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.27.0: WordPress.org Submission Readiness \u2014 Zero PHPCS Errors, Zero PCP Errors","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.27.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.5: Vendor Dashboard Identity Card and Messaging Parity Fixes","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.5-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.6 is the product of a shortcode review session during YouTube stream preparation. Accumulated silent bugs in the `rentiva_vehicles_grid` and `rentiva_featured_vehicles` shortcodes have been resolved, and two new features \u2014 `view_all_url` and a service type badge \u2014 have been added.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd27 Vehicles Grid: Price Sort Fix\\n\\nThe `sort_by=\\"price\\"` option had not been working correctly for some time. Root cause: the **named meta_query clause** approach used alongside the vehicle availability filter was generating incorrect SQL ordering.\\n\\n**Fix:** Switched to WordPress\'s standard `meta_key + meta_value_num` pattern.\\n\\n```php\\nif ( $orderby_key === \'price\' ) {\\n    $args[\'meta_key\'] = MetaKeys::VEHICLE_PRICE_PER_DAY;\\n    $args[\'orderby\']  = \'meta_value_num\';\\n    $args[\'order\']    = $sort_order;\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBoth ascending and descending sort were verified via WP-CLI.\\n\\n## \u26a1 Cache Logic Repaired\\n\\nTwo silent cache bugs:\\n\\n1. **Always disabled** \u2014 The condition logic had an inverted check. Cache is now active in production.\\n2. **Cleared on every `wp_head` call** \u2014 Invalidation now fires only when a vehicle is saved or deleted.\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddf9 Orderby Injection Removed from 9 Blocks\\n\\nNine Gutenberg blocks were silently overriding the `sort_by` attribute from the CAM pipeline with `orderby=title, order=ASC` defaults on every render. Those defaults have been removed.\\n\\n## \u2728 New: \\"View All\\" Link\\n\\nThe `view_all_url` and `view_all_text` attributes have been added. Supported in the block editor, Elementor, and classic shortcode.\\n\\n```\\n[rentiva_vehicles_grid view_all_url=\\"/araclar/\\" view_all_text=\\"T\xfcm Ara\xe7lar\u0131 G\xf6r\\"]\\n```\\n\\nRenders as a properly aligned button in the section footer.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udff7\ufe0f New: Service Type Badge\\n\\nVehicle cards now display a badge based on the `_rentiva_vehicle_service_type` meta value:\\n- **Transfer Only** \u2014 blue badge\\n- **Transfer + Rental** \u2014 green badge\\n- Standard rental vehicles show no badge.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udeab Featured Vehicles: Init Flash Fixed\\n\\nRaw flex markup was visible before Swiper initialized (5 vehicles horizontal \u2192 3-column slider). Fix: `opacity:0` + CSS transition.\\n\\n```css\\n.mhm-featured-swiper {\\n    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;\\n}\\n.mhm-featured-swiper:not(.swiper-initialized) {\\n    opacity: 0;\\n    pointer-events: none;\\n}\\n```\\n\\nLayout space is preserved (zero CLS); once Swiper is ready, it fades in with a 0.2s transition.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd27 Other Fixes\\n\\n- **`show_book_button` dead attribute:** Featured Vehicles and the Elementor widget were sending this key, but the template only checked `show_booking_button`. Both keys are now accepted.\\n- **Search Results `default_sort`:** Now applied when no sort parameter is present in the URL.\\n- **Unified Search luggage tooltip:** A hover/focus tooltip has been added for the luggage capacity field.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Next: v4.26.7/v4.26.8 \u2014 Popular Routes shortcode and Swiper loop mode fix.*"},{"id":"v4.26.5-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.5-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.5-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.5-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.5: Vendor Dashboard Identity Card and Messaging Parity Fixes","description":"v4.26.5 delivers the results of an extended UX polish session on the vendor dashboard: a premium identity card (Gravatar + last login) at the bottom of the left menu, a fix for vendor bookings not appearing in the messaging form, a premium redesign of message list cards, and a set of silent bug fixes alongside.","date":"2026-04-15T22:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"messages","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/messages"},{"inline":true,"label":"ux","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/ux"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":4.18,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.5-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.5: Vendor Dashboard Identity Card and Messaging Parity Fixes","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","vendor","messages","ux","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-15T22:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.6: Vehicles Grid Shortcode Review Fixes","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.6-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.4: Parite Denetimi Fix\'leri ve Transfer Widget UX Cilas\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.4-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.5 delivers the results of an extended UX polish session on the vendor dashboard: a premium **identity card** (Gravatar + last login) at the bottom of the left menu, a fix for **vendor bookings not appearing** in the messaging form, a **premium redesign** of message list cards, and a set of silent bug fixes alongside.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc64 Vendor Dashboard Identity Card\\n\\nThe vendor dashboard\'s left menu previously showed only the username and a \\"Log Out\\" link. Now it includes:\\n\\n- **Gravatar photo** (40 px, rounded, white border, soft shadow)\\n- **User display name** (overflow controlled with ellipsis)\\n- **Last successful login date and time** (e.g. `Last login: 15/04/2026 04:57`)\\n- **Log Out** button moved outside the card as a standalone action; turns red on hover.\\n\\n```php\\n<?php\\n$last_login_raw = (string) get_user_meta($user->ID, \'last_login\', true);\\nif ($last_login_raw !== \'\') {\\n    $ts = strtotime($last_login_raw);\\n    if ($ts) {\\n        echo date_i18n(get_option(\'date_format\') . \' H:i\', $ts);\\n    }\\n}\\n?>\\n```\\n\\n### `last_login` user meta \u2014 a key read but never written\\n\\nAn interesting discovery: the `last_login` user meta **was already being read in our GDPR/Privacy and DataRetentionManager code** \u2014 but was never written anywhere. This meant \\"this user hasn\'t logged in for N days\\" decisions in data retention calculations were always based on an empty value.\\n\\nv4.26.5 closes this gap: `SessionManager::set_session_timeout()` now accepts the second parameter of the `wp_login` action (`WP_User $user`) and updates `last_login` with `current_time(\'mysql\')`.\\n\\n```php\\nadd_action(\'wp_login\', array(self::class, \'set_session_timeout\'), 10, 2);\\n\\npublic static function set_session_timeout($user_login = \'\', $user = null): void\\n{\\n    $user_id = ($user instanceof \\\\WP_User) ? (int) $user->ID : get_current_user_id();\\n    if (! $user_id) return;\\n    update_user_meta($user_id, \'mhm_rentiva_last_activity\', time());\\n    update_user_meta($user_id, \'last_login\', current_time(\'mysql\'));\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce5 Messaging: Vendors Now See Their Own Bookings\\n\\nThe **Related Booking** dropdown in the \\"New Message\\" form always came up empty \u2014 from the vendor\'s perspective. The REST endpoint only queried the `_mhm_customer_user_id` meta, i.e. \\"bookings I made as a customer\\". Bookings made by others on the vendor\'s own vehicles were not visible.\\n\\nThe fix: the endpoint runs two queries, merges the results by ID, deduplicates them, and sorts by `post_date DESC`:\\n\\n```php\\n// Customer-side: the user who made the booking\\n$customer_query = new WP_Query([\\n    \'post_type\' => \'vehicle_booking\',\\n    \'meta_query\' => [[\\n        \'key\' => \'_mhm_customer_user_id\',\\n        \'value\' => $user_id,\\n    ]],\\n]);\\n\\n// Vendor-side: bookings on vehicles owned by this vendor\\n$vendor_vehicle_ids = get_posts([\\n    \'post_type\' => \'vehicle\',\\n    \'author\'    => $user_id,\\n    \'posts_per_page\' => -1,\\n    \'fields\'    => \'ids\',\\n]);\\nif (!empty($vendor_vehicle_ids)) {\\n    $vendor_query = new WP_Query([\\n        \'post_type\' => \'vehicle_booking\',\\n        \'meta_query\' => [[\\n            \'key\' => \'_mhm_vehicle_id\',\\n            \'value\' => $vendor_vehicle_ids,\\n            \'compare\' => \'IN\',\\n        ]],\\n    ]);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfa8 Premium Message List Cards\\n\\nMessage list cards have moved from plain white boxes to a premium design:\\n\\n- **Gradient background** (`#ffffff \u2192 #fafbff`)\\n- **Purple pill ID badge** (`#4F46E5` background, `#eef2ff` fill)\\n- **Orange gradient \\"NEW\\" label** (`#f59e0b \u2192 #f97316`, box-shadow amber glow)\\n- **On hover**, an indigo accent bar appears on the card\'s left edge and the card lifts 2 px\\n- **Unread state** uses an amber background + left accent bar\\n- **Mobile breakpoint**: padding and typography adapt automatically\\n\\n## \ud83d\uddc2\ufe0f `.hidden` \u2014 A Rule We Didn\'t Know Was Missing\\n\\nThe messages page template has three views:\\n1. Message list\\n2. Conversation (thread) view\\n3. New message form\\n\\nThe template tried to hide all three with `class=\\"hidden\\"` initially \u2014 but the **`.hidden` CSS rule was defined nowhere**. As a result, all three rendered as `display: block` simultaneously. When the user scrolled down, they saw a confusing stack of overlapping panels.\\n\\nThe fix is a CSS utility:\\n\\n```css\\n.mhm-messages-section .hidden,\\n.mhm-messages-section .thread-reply.hidden,\\n.mhm-messages-section .new-message-form.hidden,\\n.mhm-messages-section .message-thread.hidden {\\n    display: none !important;\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNow the three views are **mutually exclusive**: whichever is active is shown; the others are hidden.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd01 No More Button Accumulation When Reopening a Thread\\n\\nWhen a thread was closed and reopened, the \\"Close Message\\" button and \\"This conversation is closed\\" notice banner were **appended to the DOM again** without removing the stale elements first. The result: opening the same thread twice showed two \\"Close Message\\" buttons.\\n\\n```javascript\\n// Remove stale elements before re-rendering\\n$(\'#message-thread .close-thread-btn\').remove();\\n$(\'#message-thread .thread-closed-notice\').remove();\\n```\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd23 Mojibake Box and Translation Fixes\\n\\n- The back-arrow (`\u2190`) before the \\"Back to Messages\\" text in `templates/account/messages.php` was double-encoded UTF-8 (rendered as `\xe2\u2020`) and a stray C1 control byte (`0xC2 0x90`) remained in the template. Fix: `<span aria-hidden=\\"true\\">&larr;</span>` HTML entity + PowerShell script to strip the C1 byte.\\n- In the Turkish `.po` file, the **\\"Booking Association\\"** label was translated as **\\"Rezervasyon Derne\u011fi\\"** (Booking Society) \ud83d\ude04 \u2014 corrected to **\\"\u0130lgili Rezervasyon\\"**.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Filemtime Cache Busting\\n\\nDuring this session we hit the \\"browser cache keeps serving old CSS/JS\\" loop twice. To prevent this going forward, asset enqueues now use filemtime versioning:\\n\\n```php\\n$customer_messages_css_ver = file_exists($path)\\n    ? MHM_RENTIVA_VERSION . \'.\' . filemtime($path)\\n    : MHM_RENTIVA_VERSION;\\nwp_enqueue_style(\'mhm-customer-messages\', $url, [], $customer_messages_css_ver);\\n```\\n\\nEven when the plugin version stays the same, every file change produces a unique query string like `?ver=4.26.5.1744742822` \u2014 the browser never serves the old file.\\n\\n## \u2705 Tests\\n\\n**720 tests, 2601 assertions, 6 skipped** \u2014 fully green. No regressions.\\n\\n## Download\\n\\n- [GitHub Release v4.26.5](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.26.5)\\n- ZIP asset: `mhm-rentiva.4.26.5.zip` (2.61 MB, 764 files)\\n\\nThe next minor version (**v4.27.0**) is dedicated to the vendor report and dispute system \u2014 a unified infrastructure for booking, penalty, and vehicle reports."},{"id":"v4.26.4-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.4-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.4-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-15-v4.26.4-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.4: Parite Denetimi Fix\'leri ve Transfer Widget UX Cilas\u0131","description":"v4.26.4, t\xfcm 18 core \\"k\u0131sa kod \u2194 Gutenberg blo\u011fu \u2194 Elementor widget\'\u0131\\" \xfc\xe7l\xfcs\xfc \xfczerinde yap\u0131lan ayar paritesi denetiminde ortaya \xe7\u0131kan \xfc\xe7 sessiz sorunu gideriyor: Arama Sonu\xe7lar\u0131 blo\u011funa kopya-yap\u0131\u015ft\u0131r ile s\u0131zm\u0131\u015f \xfc\xe7 hayalet attribute, Birle\u015fik Arama blo\u011fundaki duplicate geni\u015flik attribute\'lar\u0131 ve Transfer Arama Elementor widget\'\u0131nda otomatik \xfcretilmi\u015f ham etiketli control\'ler. \xdc\xe7\xfc de kullan\u0131c\u0131n\u0131n g\xf6z\xfcnden ka\xe7an ama panelde anlams\u0131z g\xf6r\xfcnen UX \xe7\xfcr\xfcmeleriydi.","date":"2026-04-15T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"elementor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/elementor"},{"inline":true,"label":"blocks","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/blocks"},{"inline":true,"label":"parity","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/parity"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":2.75,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.4-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.4: Parite Denetimi Fix\'leri ve Transfer Widget UX Cilas\u0131","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","elementor","blocks","parity","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-15T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.5: Vendor Dashboard Identity Card and Messaging Parity Fixes","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.5-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.3: Ara\xe7 Kart\u0131 G\xf6rsel Kalitesi, Admin Toast Kesilmesi ve ZIP Chart.js D\xfczeltmesi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.3-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.4, t\xfcm 18 core \\"k\u0131sa kod \u2194 Gutenberg blo\u011fu \u2194 Elementor widget\'\u0131\\" \xfc\xe7l\xfcs\xfc \xfczerinde yap\u0131lan ayar paritesi denetiminde ortaya \xe7\u0131kan \xfc\xe7 sessiz sorunu gideriyor: Arama Sonu\xe7lar\u0131 blo\u011funa kopya-yap\u0131\u015ft\u0131r ile s\u0131zm\u0131\u015f \xfc\xe7 hayalet attribute, Birle\u015fik Arama blo\u011fundaki duplicate geni\u015flik attribute\'lar\u0131 ve Transfer Arama Elementor widget\'\u0131nda otomatik \xfcretilmi\u015f ham etiketli control\'ler. \xdc\xe7\xfc de kullan\u0131c\u0131n\u0131n g\xf6z\xfcnden ka\xe7an ama panelde anlams\u0131z g\xf6r\xfcnen UX \xe7\xfcr\xfcmeleriydi.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd0d Parite Denetimi Neden Gerekli?\\n\\nMHM Rentiva\'n\u0131n \\"Render Parity Rule\\" kural\u0131na g\xf6re **her blok**, render zaman\u0131nda `do_shortcode()` ile kar\u015f\u0131l\u0131k gelen k\u0131sa koda delege eder. Yani bloklar\u0131n kendi mant\u0131\u011f\u0131 yoktur \u2014 sadece k\u0131sa koda arg\xfcman ge\xe7iren ince bir kabuktur. Elementor widget\'lar\u0131 da ayn\u0131 prensiple \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131r.\\n\\nBu mimari g\xfc\xe7l\xfc bir garanti sa\u011flar: **k\u0131sa kodda \xe7al\u0131\u015fan her \u015fey blokta ve widget\'ta da \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131r**. Ama tersi de do\u011fru olmal\u0131 \u2014 **k\u0131sa kodun bilmedi\u011fi bir attribute, blokta veya widget\'ta da olmamal\u0131**. Aksi halde kullan\u0131c\u0131 panel aray\xfcz\xfcnde bir toggle a\xe7ar, bir \u015fey yazar, render\'da hi\xe7bir de\u011fi\u015fiklik olmaz. Hata yok, uyar\u0131 yok, sessiz no-op.\\n\\nBu v4.26.4\'te giderilen \xfc\xe7 sorun da tam olarak bu s\u0131n\u0131ftan:\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b 1. Arama Sonu\xe7lar\u0131 Blo\u011fu \u2014 Hayalet Attribute S\u0131z\u0131nt\u0131s\u0131\\n\\n`assets/blocks/search-results/block.json` dosyas\u0131na, zaman\u0131nda `transfer-search` blo\u011fundan kopya-yap\u0131\u015ft\u0131r ile t\xfcretildi\u011fi s\u0131rada \xfc\xe7 attribute s\u0131zm\u0131\u015ft\u0131:\\n\\n- `button_text`\\n- `show_pickup`\\n- `show_dropoff`\\n\\nArama Sonu\xe7lar\u0131 blo\u011funda **buton yok**, **pickup/dropoff alanlar\u0131 yok** \u2014 bu attribute\'lar anlams\u0131z. Ama Gutenberg inspector panelinde g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcyorlard\u0131, otomatik \xfcretilen Elementor widget\'\u0131na da ge\xe7iyorlard\u0131. Kullan\u0131c\u0131 a\xe7ar, de\u011fer girer, render\'da hi\xe7bir \u015fey olmaz.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:** `block.json`\'dan \xfc\xe7\xfc de silindi. Otomatik parite mekanizmas\u0131 (`register_parity_controls_from_block`) block.json\'u kaynak kabul etti\u011fi i\xe7in widget\'tan da otomatik d\xfc\u015ft\xfcler.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b 2. Birle\u015fik Arama Blo\u011fu \u2014 Duplicate Geni\u015flik Attribute\'lar\u0131\\n\\n`assets/blocks/unified-search/block.json`\'da iki duplicate attribute vard\u0131:\\n\\n```json\\n\\"min_width\\": { ... },\\n\\"max_width\\": { ... }\\n```\\n\\nCAM (Canonical Attribute Mapper) pipeline\'\u0131 snake_case ayra\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131 kald\u0131r\u0131r ve kanonik isimler `minwidth` / `maxwidth` olarak render\'a ula\u015f\u0131r. `min_width` / `max_width` ayr\u0131 birer alan olarak DB\'ye yaz\u0131l\u0131yor, ama render a\u015famas\u0131nda ayn\u0131 de\u011fere map\'leniyordu \u2014 iki kontrol ayn\u0131 \u015feyi yap\u0131yor, biri de render\'da hi\xe7bir zaman okunmuyordu.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:** Snake_case varyantlar silindi. Tek kanonik `minwidth` / `maxwidth` kald\u0131.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfa8 3. Transfer Arama Widget\'\u0131 \u2014 Ham Etiketli Control\'ler\\n\\nBase Elementor widget s\u0131n\u0131f\u0131m\u0131zda `register_parity_controls_from_block()` adl\u0131 bir metod var. Bu metod, block.json\'daki attribute\'lar\u0131 taray\u0131p widget\'ta manuel tan\u0131mlanmam\u0131\u015f olanlar i\xe7in otomatik Elementor control\'leri \xfcretir. **Amac\u0131:** yeni bir block.json attribute\'u eklendi\u011finde Elementor widget\'\u0131n\u0131n geride kalmamas\u0131n\u0131 sa\u011flamak. Bir g\xfcvenlik a\u011f\u0131.\\n\\nAma g\xfcvenlik a\u011f\u0131 **tasar\u0131m arac\u0131 de\u011fil**. Otomatik \xfcretilen control\'ler ham attribute name\'leri label olarak kullan\u0131r: `showPickup` \u2192 \\"ShowPickup\\", `buttonText` \u2192 \\"ButtonText\\". Placeholder yok, do\u011fru default yok, ayr\u0131 bir b\xf6l\xfcmde g\xf6steriliyor. Transfer Search widget\'\u0131nda tam olarak bu oluyordu.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:** \xdc\xe7 user-facing attribute i\xe7in manuel `add_control()` \xe7a\u011fr\u0131lar\u0131 eklendi:\\n\\n```php\\n$this->add_control(\'buttonText\', [\\n    \'label\'       => __(\'Button Text\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),\\n    \'type\'        => Controls_Manager::TEXT,\\n    \'default\'     => \'\',\\n    \'placeholder\' => __(\'Search Transfers\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),\\n]);\\n$this->add_control(\'showPickup\', [\\n    \'label\'        => __(\'Show Pickup Location\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),\\n    \'type\'         => Controls_Manager::SWITCHER,\\n    \'return_value\' => \'yes\',\\n    \'default\'      => \'yes\',\\n]);\\n$this->add_control(\'showDropoff\', [\\n    \'label\'        => __(\'Show Dropoff Location\', \'mhm-rentiva\'),\\n    \'type\'         => Controls_Manager::SWITCHER,\\n    \'return_value\' => \'yes\',\\n    \'default\'      => \'yes\',\\n]);\\n```\\n\\n`register_parity_controls_from_block()` manuel tan\u0131ml\u0131 control\'leri otomatik olarak atlar (`in_array($attr_name, $existing_controls)`), dolay\u0131s\u0131yla duplicate \xe7\u0131kmaz. Ama art\u0131k panel ismini do\u011fru, placeholder\'l\u0131, mant\u0131kl\u0131 default\'larla g\xf6steriyor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcd6 \xc7\u0131kar\u0131lan Ders\\n\\n**Otomatik parite mekanizmas\u0131 g\xfcvenlik a\u011f\u0131d\u0131r, UI de\u011fil.** Her user-facing attribute manuel `add_control()` ile tan\u0131mlanmal\u0131: do\u011fru label, placeholder, default. Otomatik mekanizma gelecekte eklenecek attribute\'lar i\xe7in arka planda bekleyen regresyon kalkan\u0131 olarak kal\u0131r.\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddea Testler\\n\\n720 test \xb7 2470 assertion \xb7 6 skipped \u2014 tam ye\u015fil.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Kurulum\\n\\n[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva/releases/tag/v4.26.4) \xfczerinden `mhm-rentiva.4.26.4.zip` dosyas\u0131n\u0131 indirin ve WordPress Eklentiler \u2192 Yeni Ekle \u2192 Eklenti Y\xfckle ekran\u0131ndan y\xfckleyin."},{"id":"v4.26.3-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.3-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-11-v4.26.3-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-11-v4.26.3-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.3: Ara\xe7 Kart\u0131 G\xf6rsel Kalitesi, Admin Toast Kesilmesi ve ZIP Chart.js D\xfczeltmesi","description":"v4.26.3, listeleme/arama sayfalar\u0131ndaki ara\xe7 g\xf6rsellerinin bulan\u0131k y\xfcklenmesine neden olan responsive sizes hatas\u0131n\u0131, ayarlar sayfas\u0131ndaki \\"kaydedildi\\" toast bildirimlerinin kesilip ekrandan ta\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131 ve release ZIP\'inden Chart.js\'in \xe7\u0131kar\u0131lmas\u0131na yol a\xe7an .distignore k\xf6k-sabitleme hatas\u0131n\u0131 gideriyor. \xdc\xe7\xfc de \xfcretimde g\xf6zle g\xf6r\xfclen ama console.log\'a d\xfc\u015fmeyen sessiz sorunlard\u0131.","date":"2026-04-11T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"frontend","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/frontend"},{"inline":true,"label":"admin-ux","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/admin-ux"},{"inline":true,"label":"build","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/build"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":4.64,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.3-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.3: Ara\xe7 Kart\u0131 G\xf6rsel Kalitesi, Admin Toast Kesilmesi ve ZIP Chart.js D\xfczeltmesi","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","frontend","admin-ux","build","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-11T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.4: Parite Denetimi Fix\'leri ve Transfer Widget UX Cilas\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.4-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.2: Tam Kald\u0131rma Temizli\u011fi ve CLI Bootstrap G\xfc\xe7lendirmesi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.2-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.3, listeleme/arama sayfalar\u0131ndaki ara\xe7 g\xf6rsellerinin bulan\u0131k y\xfcklenmesine neden olan responsive `sizes` hatas\u0131n\u0131, ayarlar sayfas\u0131ndaki \\"kaydedildi\\" toast bildirimlerinin kesilip ekrandan ta\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131 ve release ZIP\'inden Chart.js\'in \xe7\u0131kar\u0131lmas\u0131na yol a\xe7an `.distignore` k\xf6k-sabitleme hatas\u0131n\u0131 gideriyor. \xdc\xe7\xfc de \xfcretimde g\xf6zle g\xf6r\xfclen ama `console.log`\'a d\xfc\u015fmeyen sessiz sorunlard\u0131.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\uddbc\ufe0f Ara\xe7 Kart\u0131 G\xf6rsel Kalitesi \u2014 220px Tuza\u011f\u0131\\n\\nAra\xe7 kart\u0131 partial\u0131nda (`templates/partials/vehicle-card.php`) y\u0131llard\u0131r sabit kodlanm\u0131\u015f bir `sizes` \xf6zniteli\u011fi vard\u0131:\\n\\n```html\\nsizes=\\"(max-width: 782px) 100vw, (max-width: 900px) 180px, 220px\\"\\n```\\n\\nBu \xf6znitelik taray\u0131c\u0131ya \\"bu g\xf6rselin ekranda kaplayaca\u011f\u0131 alan en fazla 220px\\" diyordu. Taray\u0131c\u0131 da do\u011fal olarak `srcset`\'teki en k\xfc\xe7\xfck uygun varyant\u0131 \u2014 **300w thumbnail**\'\u0131 \u2014 se\xe7iyordu. Ancak kartlar\u0131n ger\xe7ek g\xf6r\xfcnen geni\u015fli\u011fi 350-440px aras\u0131ndayd\u0131. Sonu\xe7: retina ekranlarda bile bulan\u0131k ara\xe7 g\xf6rselleri.\\n\\n**En belirgin oldu\u011fu yer:** Arama sonu\xe7lar\u0131 sayfas\u0131, \xe7\xfcnk\xfc oradaki kartlar en geni\u015f olanlard\u0131. Ayr\u0131ca arama kodu (`SearchResults::format_vehicle_data()`) varsay\u0131lan olarak zaten `\'medium\'` (300px) istiyordu \u2014 yani hem kaynak g\xf6rsel small\'d\u0131, hem de browser daha da k\xfc\xe7\xfc\u011f\xfcn\xfc se\xe7iyordu.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm iki katmanl\u0131:**\\n\\n1. `SearchResults` varsay\u0131lan `image_size`\'\u0131 `\'medium\'` \u2192 `\'large\'` (1024px) oldu \u2014 ara\xe7 \u0131zgaras\u0131, ara\xe7 listesi ve \xf6ne \xe7\u0131kan ara\xe7lar zaten `\'large\'` kullan\u0131yordu\\n2. `vehicle-card.php` `sizes` \xf6zniteli\u011fi \u2192 `(max-width: 782px) 100vw, 500px` \u2014 retina ekranlarda browser art\u0131k 1024w varyant\u0131 se\xe7iyor, geni\u015f kartlar keskin\\n\\nBu d\xfczeltme **tek bir partial dosyas\u0131** de\u011fi\u015fti\u011fi i\xe7in listeleme, favoriler, ara\xe7 ar\u015fivi ve arama sonu\xe7lar\u0131 \u2014 hepsi birlikte d\xfczeldi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd14 Admin Settings Toast \u2014 \\"Kaydedildi\\" Bildiriminin Kesilmesi\\n\\nAyarlar sayfas\u0131nda herhangi bir de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011fi kaydetti\u011finizde \xe7\u0131kan \\"Ayarlar kaydedildi\\" bildirimi, \xf6zellikle uzun mesajlarda sa\u011f taraf\u0131 kesilmi\u015f olarak g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcyordu. Sorun tek bir yerde de\u011fildi \u2014 iki ayr\u0131 bozukluk \xfcst \xfcste binmi\u015fti:\\n\\n**1. WordPress bildirimi header flex konteynerine hapsediliyordu.** `render_admin_header()` helper\'\u0131 H1, alt ba\u015fl\u0131k ve aksiyonlar i\xe7in bir flex konteyner kuruyor ama sonuna `<hr class=\\"wp-header-end\\" />` koymuyordu. WordPress `common.js`\'in bildirimleri yerle\u015ftirmek i\xe7in kulland\u0131\u011f\u0131 resmi API tam olarak bu i\u015faret\xe7i. \u0130\u015faret\xe7i yokken WordPress ilk H1\'i ar\u0131yor ve bildirimi dar flex kolonunun i\xe7ine s\u0131k\u0131\u015ft\u0131r\u0131yordu.\\n\\n**2. \xd6zel toast CSS\'i her \u015feyi tek sat\u0131ra zorluyordu.** Plugin\'in `convertWPNoticesToToasts()` helper\'\u0131 WordPress bildirimini gizleyip \xf6zel bir `.rv-notification.mhm-admin-toast` div\'i olu\u015fturuyor. Bu div\'in CSS\'i `white-space: nowrap`, `max-width: 350px`, `height: 50px` i\xe7eriyordu \u2014 yani uzun mesajlar\u0131 ta\u015f\u0131r\u0131yor, kelime kayd\u0131rma yapm\u0131yor, ve birden fazla toast \xfcst \xfcste geldi\u011finde istiflenmiyordu.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:**\\n\\n- `render_admin_header()` flex konteynerin kapan\u0131\u015f\u0131ndan hemen sonra `<hr class=\\"wp-header-end\\" />` yay\u0131nl\u0131yor \u2014 art\u0131k bildirimler konteynerin alt\u0131nda tam geni\u015flikte beliriyor\\n- Toast CSS\'i ba\u015ftan yaz\u0131ld\u0131: sabit `height`/`max-width`/`nowrap` kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131; `min-width: 280px`, `max-width: min(480px, calc(100vw - 60px))`, `white-space: normal`, `overflow-wrap: break-word`\\n- Toastlar i\xe7in `#mhm-admin-toast-container` ad\u0131nda sabit konumlu flex konteyner eklendi; yeni toastlar `prepend` ile en \xfcste giriyor \u2014 b\xf6ylece birden fazla toast istifleniyor ve en yenisi her zaman \xfcstte\\n- XSS g\xfcvenli\u011fi: toast mesajlar\u0131 art\u0131k template literal ile de\u011fil `.text(message)` ile yaz\u0131l\u0131yor \u2014 gelecekte bir hook\'un bildirim i\xe7eri\u011fine HTML enjekte etme riski yok\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Release ZIP Chart.js 404 \u2014 `.distignore`\'un Gizli Hatas\u0131\\n\\nWordPress.org \xfczerinden kurulan kopyalarda admin dashboard\'daki grafikler 404 veriyordu. K\xf6k nedeni `.distignore` dosyas\u0131n\u0131n `vendor/` paterniydi.\\n\\nRelease ZIP\'i olu\u015fturan `bin/build-release.py` Python script\'i, paterndeki trailing `/` karakterini siliyor ve kalan `vendor`\'u \\"herhangi bir yol segmenti\\" olarak e\u015fle\u015ftiriyordu. Bu mant\u0131kla:\\n\\n- \u2705 `vendor/composer/...` e\u015fle\u015fti \u2014 do\u011fru (Composer klas\xf6r\xfcn\xfc atlamak istiyoruz)\\n- \u274c `assets/js/vendor/chart.min.js` **de** e\u015fle\u015fti \u2014 yanl\u0131\u015f (bu dosya kargoda olmal\u0131yd\u0131)\\n\\nSonu\xe7: `chart.min.js`, `flatpickr/`, `swiper-bundle.min.js` ve di\u011fer a\u011fa\xe7 i\xe7i vendor k\xfct\xfcphaneleri release ZIP\'inden d\xfc\u015f\xfcyordu. Lokal geli\u015ftirmede g\xf6r\xfcnm\xfcyordu \xe7\xfcnk\xfc build s\xfcreci atlan\u0131yordu. Ancak WordPress.org ya da GitHub Release ZIP\'i \xfczerinden kurulum yap\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda dashboard bo\u015f kal\u0131yordu.\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:**\\n\\n- `bin/build-release.py` art\u0131k `.gitignore` tarz\u0131 k\xf6k sabitlemeyi destekliyor \u2014 bir patern `/` ile ba\u015flarsa yaln\u0131zca plugin k\xf6k dizinindeki o yola e\u015fle\u015fiyor, alt dizinlerdeki ayn\u0131 isimli klas\xf6rlere dokunmuyor\\n- `.distignore` g\xfcncellendi: `vendor/` \u2192 `/vendor/`\\n\\nDo\u011frulama: Yeni ZIP\'te `assets/js/vendor/chart.min.js`, `assets/vendor/flatpickr/*`, `assets/vendor/swiper-bundle.min.js` mevcut; Composer `vendor/` k\xf6k dizini d\u0131\u015fland\u0131.\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddd9 Setup Wizard \u2014 Versiyon Badge ve Lite/Pro CTA (Toplu Batch\'ten)\\n\\nBu release\'e toplu halde giren bir dizi kullan\u0131c\u0131 aray\xfcz\xfc iyile\u015ftirmesi:\\n\\n- **Kurulum Sihirbaz\u0131 ba\u015fl\u0131\u011f\u0131** art\u0131k plugin versiyonunu + Lite/Pro rozetini g\xf6steriyor\\n- **Lisans sekmesi + Lisans men\xfc sayfas\u0131** \\"\xdcr\xfcn Sayfas\u0131n\u0131 A\xe7\\" CTA butonu kazand\u0131 \u2014 kullan\u0131c\u0131 \xfcr\xfcn\xfcn sat\u0131n alma sayfas\u0131na tek t\u0131kla gidebiliyor\\n- **Geli\u015ftirici modu guard\u0131:** `has_real_license()` art\u0131k dev mode\'da CTA g\xf6r\xfcnmesini engellemiyor \u2014 geli\u015ftirme ortamlar\u0131nda da CTA test edilebiliyor\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\uddbc\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | Ara\xe7 kart\u0131 `sizes` \xf6zniteli\u011fi 220px \u2192 500px (listeleme + favoriler + ar\u015fiv + arama sonu\xe7lar\u0131) |\\n| \ud83d\uddbc\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | `SearchResults` varsay\u0131lan `image_size` `\'medium\'` \u2192 `\'large\'` |\\n| \ud83d\udd14 D\xfczeltme | `render_admin_header()` `<hr class=\\"wp-header-end\\" />` emit ediyor \u2014 bildirimler art\u0131k header flex\'ten \xe7\u0131k\u0131yor |\\n| \ud83d\udd14 D\xfczeltme | Admin toast CSS: sabit `height`/`nowrap` kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131, kelime kayd\u0131rma eklendi |\\n| \ud83d\udd14 D\xfczeltme | Admin toast istifleme: `#mhm-admin-toast-container` + `prepend` \u2014 birden fazla toast \xfcst \xfcste binmiyor |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Admin toast mesajlar\u0131 art\u0131k `.text()` ile yaz\u0131l\u0131yor \u2014 HTML enjeksiyonuna kar\u015f\u0131 g\xfcvende |\\n| \ud83d\udce6 D\xfczeltme | `.distignore` `/vendor/` k\xf6k sabitlemesi \u2014 `chart.min.js`, `flatpickr`, `swiper` art\u0131k ZIP\'te |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Build | `bin/build-release.py` `.gitignore` tarz\u0131 leading-slash anchoring deste\u011fi |\\n| \ud83e\uddd9 UX | Setup Wizard header versiyon + Lite/Pro badge |\\n| \ud83e\uddd9 UX | Setup Wizard Lisans sekmesi + Lisans men\xfcde \\"\xdcr\xfcn Sayfas\u0131n\u0131 A\xe7\\" CTA |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc1 De\u011fi\u015ftirilen Dosyalar\\n\\n- `templates/partials/vehicle-card.php` *(sizes 220px \u2192 500px)*\\n- `src/Admin/Frontend/Shortcodes/SearchResults.php` *(image_size \'medium\' \u2192 \'large\')*\\n- `src/Admin/Core/Traits/AdminHelperTrait.php` *(wp-header-end marker)*\\n- `assets/css/admin/settings.css` *(toast wrap + stacking CSS redesign)*\\n- `assets/js/admin/settings.js` *(container + prepend + .text XSS guard)*\\n- `.distignore` *(/vendor/ k\xf6k sabitleme)*\\n- `bin/build-release.py` *(anchored pattern support)*\\n- `src/Admin/Setup/SetupWizard.php` *(versiyon badge + CTA)*\\n- `src/Admin/Licensing/LicenseAdmin.php` *(CTA)*\\n- `mhm-rentiva.php`, `readme.txt`, `README.md`, `README-tr.md`, `changelog.json`, `changelog-tr.json` *(versiyon y\xfckseltme)*\\n\\n## \u2705 Kalite\\n\\n- **720 test, 2470 assertion, 6 atland\u0131** (v4.25.0 baseline\'\u0131 683/2277 idi)\\n- PHPUnit tam ye\u015fil\\n\\n## \u2b06\ufe0f G\xfcncelleme Notu\\n\\nv4.26.3 tamamen geriye d\xf6n\xfck uyumlu bir patch s\xfcr\xfcm\xfcd\xfcr \u2014 DB \u015femas\u0131nda de\u011fi\u015fiklik yoktur, migration \xe7al\u0131\u015fmaz, ek bir yap\u0131land\u0131rma gerekmez. G\xfcncelleme yollar\u0131:\\n\\n- WordPress admin \u2192 Eklentiler \u2192 G\xfcncelle\\n- `wp plugin update mhm-rentiva --allow-root`\\n- Manuel ZIP y\xfckleme (v4.26.2\'den itibaren otomatik migration destekleniyor)\\n\\n---\\n\\nDaha fazla bilgi i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edin."},{"id":"v4.26.2-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.2-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-10-v4.26.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-10-v4.26.2-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.2: Tam Kald\u0131rma Temizli\u011fi ve CLI Bootstrap G\xfc\xe7lendirmesi","description":"v4.26.2, eklenti kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda arkada kalan t\xfcm tablolar\u0131n silinmesini sa\u011fl\u0131yor, wp-cli bootstrap s\u0131ras\u0131ndaki fatal hatay\u0131 gideriyor ve \u015fema migration\'lar\u0131n art\u0131k s\xfcr\xfcm de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011finde otomatik \xe7al\u0131\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131 garantiliyor. \xdc\xe7 d\xfczeltme de \xfcretim ortamlar\u0131ndaki sessiz sorunlar\u0131 hedefliyor.","date":"2026-04-10T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"uninstall","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/uninstall"},{"inline":true,"label":"cli","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/cli"},{"inline":true,"label":"migration","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/migration"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":2.73,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.2-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.2: Tam Kald\u0131rma Temizli\u011fi ve CLI Bootstrap G\xfc\xe7lendirmesi","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","uninstall","cli","migration","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-10T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.3: Ara\xe7 Kart\u0131 G\xf6rsel Kalitesi, Admin Toast Kesilmesi ve ZIP Chart.js D\xfczeltmesi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.3-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.1: Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131, Rezervasyon, \xd6deme ve Sepet G\xf6rsel Cilas\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.1-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.2, eklenti kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda arkada kalan t\xfcm tablolar\u0131n silinmesini sa\u011fl\u0131yor, wp-cli bootstrap s\u0131ras\u0131ndaki fatal hatay\u0131 gideriyor ve \u015fema migration\'lar\u0131n art\u0131k s\xfcr\xfcm de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011finde otomatik \xe7al\u0131\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131 garantiliyor. \xdc\xe7 d\xfczeltme de \xfcretim ortamlar\u0131ndaki sessiz sorunlar\u0131 hedefliyor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83e\uddf9 Kald\u0131rma Temizli\u011fi \u2014 Art\u0131k 27 Tablonun Hepsi\\n\\n\xd6nceden eklenti \\"verileri temizle\\" se\xe7ene\u011fi ile silindi\u011finde 14 alt sistem tablosu veritaban\u0131nda yetim kal\u0131yordu: `ledger`, `key_registry`, `commission_policy`, `payout_audit`, `tenants`, `usage_metrics` ve eski alert/payment alt sistemlerine ait art\u0131k kullan\u0131lmayan tablolar. Bu v4.26.2 ile tamamen \xe7\xf6z\xfcld\xfc.\\n\\n**Yap\u0131lan iyile\u015ftirmeler:**\\n\\n- **Tam liste:** 27 \xf6zel tablonun tamam\u0131 kald\u0131rma s\u0131ras\u0131nda siliniyor\\n- **Pattern g\xfcvenlik a\u011f\u0131:** Listede olmayan ama `mhm_rentiva_*` \xf6nekiyle ba\u015flayan herhangi bir yetim tablo da otomatik yakalan\u0131p siliniyor \u2014 gelecekte eklenen tablolar i\xe7in g\xfcvence\\n- **Kurtarma tablosu temizli\u011fi:** `DatabaseCleaner` taraf\u0131ndan olu\u015fturulan `postmeta_backup_invalid_*` ge\xe7ici tablolar\u0131 da kald\u0131rma s\u0131ras\u0131nda temizleniyor\\n- **Tek kaynak prensibi:** Silme listesi ve istatistik sayac\u0131 art\u0131k ayn\u0131 kaynaktan okuyor \u2014 saya\xe7 ile ger\xe7ek temizlik birbirinden uzakla\u015famaz\\n- **Savunma mekanizmalar\u0131:** `uninstall.php` ve taksonomi temizleme ad\u0131m\u0131 art\u0131k bozuk bir ayar kayd\u0131 veya eksik taksonomi nedeniyle sessizce durmuyor \u2014 hata yakalan\u0131yor ve kalan ad\u0131mlar \xe7al\u0131\u015fmaya devam ediyor\\n\\n**Do\u011frulama:** DemoSeed Docker ortam\u0131nda v4.26.2 kald\u0131rma testi \u2192 **0 tablo, 0 post, 0 ayar** art\u0131k geride kal\u0131yor. Tam temiz kald\u0131rma garantili.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd27 CLI Bootstrap Fatal Error D\xfczeltmesi\\n\\n\xd6nceden belirli ko\u015fullarda wp-cli komutlar\u0131 `TypeError` veya `is_user_logged_in() undefined function` hatas\u0131yla \xe7\xf6k\xfcyordu. K\xf6k nedeni iki yerde yat\u0131yordu:\\n\\n- `SettingsCore::get()` ve `has()` bir ayar kayd\u0131n\u0131n dizi olmad\u0131\u011f\u0131 durumda `TypeError` f\u0131rlat\u0131yordu\\n- `AdvancedLogger::log()` WordPress tam y\xfcklenmeden (\xf6rne\u011fin early bootstrap\'te) \xe7a\u011fr\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda `is_user_logged_in()`\'i \xe7a\u011f\u0131r\u0131yordu ama bu fonksiyon o a\u015famada tan\u0131ml\u0131 de\u011fildi\\n\\n**\xc7\xf6z\xfcm:**\\n\\n- `SettingsCore::get()`/`has()` art\u0131k dizi olmayan bir ayar de\u011ferini tolere ediyor ve g\xfcvenli varsay\u0131lana d\xfc\u015f\xfcyor\\n- `AdvancedLogger::log()` `plugins_loaded` hook\'u \xe7al\u0131\u015fmadan \xf6nce \xe7a\u011fr\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131nda erken return ediyor \u2014 log atlan\u0131r ama bootstrap \xe7\xf6kmez\\n\\n**Etkisi:** `wp plugin activate mhm-rentiva`, `wp mhm-rentiva *` subkomutlar\u0131 ve di\u011fer wp-cli ak\u0131\u015flar\u0131 art\u0131k bozuk bir ayar kayd\u0131 ya da early-bootstrap log denemesi ile \xe7\xf6km\xfcyor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd04 Otomatik \u015eema Migration\'lar\u0131\\n\\nv4.26.2 ile \u015fema migration\'lar\u0131 art\u0131k **eklenti dosya s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc de\u011fi\u015fti\u011finde otomatik \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor**, WordPress aktivasyon hook\'u \xe7a\u011fr\u0131lmasa bile. Bu; manuel ZIP y\xfckleme, FTP ile g\xfcncelleme ve `wp-cli plugin update` ak\u0131\u015flar\u0131n\u0131 kapsar.\\n\\n**\xd6nceki durum:** Yeni tablolar\u0131 olu\u015fturmak i\xe7in eklentiyi pasifle\u015ftirip tekrar etkinle\u015ftirmek gerekiyordu. Kullan\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131n \xe7o\u011fu bunu bilmedi\u011finden \\"yeni \xf6zellik \xe7al\u0131\u015fm\u0131yor\\" raporu geliyordu.\\n\\n**Yeni durum:** `DB_VERSION` sabiti de\u011fi\u015fir de\u011fi\u015fmez migration\'lar sessizce ve tek seferlik \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131r. Aktivasyon hook\'u hala destekleniyor \u2014 sadece art\u0131k zorunlu de\u011fil.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83e\uddf9 Kald\u0131rma | T\xfcm 27 \xf6zel tablo (ledger, key_registry, commission_policy, payout_audit, tenants, usage_metrics + eski alt sistem tablolar\u0131) |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Kald\u0131rma | Pattern tabanl\u0131 g\xfcvenlik a\u011f\u0131 (`mhm_rentiva_*` \xf6neki) |\\n| \ud83e\uddf9 Kald\u0131rma | `postmeta_backup_invalid_*` kurtarma tablolar\u0131 |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Kald\u0131rma | Silme listesi ve istatistik sayac\u0131 tek kaynaktan |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Kald\u0131rma | `uninstall.php` ve taksonomi temizli\u011finde savunma mekanizmalar\u0131 |\\n| \ud83d\udd04 G\xfcncelleme | \u015eema migration\'lar\u0131 s\xfcr\xfcm de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011finde otomatik \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | `SettingsCore::get()`/`has()` dizi olmayan de\u011ferleri tolere ediyor |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | `AdvancedLogger::log()` WordPress y\xfcklenmeden g\xfcvenli d\xf6n\xfc\u015f |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc1 De\u011fi\u015ftirilen Dosyalar\\n\\n- `uninstall.php` *(defensive is_array guard + tam tablo listesi)*\\n- `src/Admin/Core/Utilities/DatabaseCleaner.php` *(27 tablo + pattern wildcard)*\\n- `src/Admin/Core/Utilities/DatabaseMigrator.php` *(otomatik migration tetikleme)*\\n- `src/Admin/Core/SettingsCore.php` *(non-array tolerans\u0131)*\\n- `src/Admin/Core/Logging/AdvancedLogger.php` *(plugins_loaded guard)*\\n- `mhm-rentiva.php` *(versiyon g\xfcncelleme)*\\n\\n## \u2b06\ufe0f G\xfcncelleme Notu\\n\\nv4.26.2 tamamen geriye d\xf6n\xfck uyumlu bir patch s\xfcr\xfcm\xfcd\xfcr \u2014 DB \u015femas\u0131nda yeni tablo, kolon veya veri de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011fi **yoktur**. G\xfcncelleme sonras\u0131 ek bir i\u015flem gerekmez. Eklentiyi normal yollarla g\xfcncellemeniz yeterli:\\n\\n- WordPress admin \u2192 Eklentiler \u2192 G\xfcncelle\\n- Veya `wp plugin update mhm-rentiva --allow-root`\\n- Veya manuel ZIP y\xfckleme (art\u0131k otomatik migration tetiklenir)\\n\\n---\\n\\nDaha fazla bilgi i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edin."},{"id":"v4.26.1-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.1-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-08-v4.26.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-08-v4.26.1-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.1: Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131, Rezervasyon, \xd6deme ve Sepet G\xf6rsel Cilas\u0131","description":"v4.26.1, v4.26.0 ile devreye giren rezervasyon-\xf6deme ak\u0131\u015f\u0131n\u0131n \xfcst\xfcne gelen g\xf6rsel tutars\u0131zl\u0131klar\u0131 temizliyor. Ara\xe7 detay sayfas\u0131ndan sepete, sepetten \xf6deme sayfas\u0131na kadar m\xfc\u015fterinin g\xf6rd\xfc\u011f\xfc her ekranda kart, ikon ve hizalama sorunlar\u0131 giderildi. Fonksiyonel bir de\u011fi\u015fiklik yok \u2014 sadece deneyim daha temiz.","date":"2026-04-08T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"patch","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/patch"},{"inline":true,"label":"ui","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/ui"},{"inline":true,"label":"checkout","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/checkout"},{"inline":true,"label":"cart","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/cart"},{"inline":true,"label":"booking","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/booking"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":2.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.1-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.1: Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131, Rezervasyon, \xd6deme ve Sepet G\xf6rsel Cilas\u0131","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","patch","ui","checkout","cart","booking","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-08T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.2: Tam Kald\u0131rma Temizli\u011fi ve CLI Bootstrap G\xfc\xe7lendirmesi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.2-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.0: Depozito Rezervasyonlar\u0131nda Kalan \xd6deme","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.0-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.1, v4.26.0 ile devreye giren rezervasyon-\xf6deme ak\u0131\u015f\u0131n\u0131n \xfcst\xfcne gelen g\xf6rsel tutars\u0131zl\u0131klar\u0131 temizliyor. Ara\xe7 detay sayfas\u0131ndan sepete, sepetten \xf6deme sayfas\u0131na kadar m\xfc\u015fterinin g\xf6rd\xfc\u011f\xfc her ekranda kart, ikon ve hizalama sorunlar\u0131 giderildi. Fonksiyonel bir de\u011fi\u015fiklik yok \u2014 sadece deneyim daha temiz.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfa8 Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131 Kenar \xc7ubu\u011fu\\n\\n- **\xd6zellik etiketleri ta\u015fma sorunu:** Vites, yak\u0131t, koltuk say\u0131s\u0131 gibi spec chip\'leri dar ekranlarda kart kenar\u0131ndan ta\u015f\u0131yordu. Art\u0131k kart s\u0131n\u0131rlar\u0131 i\xe7inde kal\u0131yor ve uzun etiketler do\u011fru \u015fekilde sarmalan\u0131yor.\\n- **Hibrit yak\u0131t ikonu:** Yak\u0131t t\xfcr\xfc \\"hybrid\\" se\xe7ili ara\xe7larda yanl\u0131\u015f ikon g\xf6steriliyordu. Do\u011fru simgeyle de\u011fi\u015ftirildi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc5 Takvim\\n\\n- **Bo\u015f sat\u0131r kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131:** Takvim bile\u015feninin alt\u0131nda fazladan bir bo\u015f sat\u0131r render ediliyordu \u2014 kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131.\\n- **Kutu i\xe7inde kutu g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcm\xfc:** Kenar \xe7ubu\u011funda takvim widget\'\u0131n\u0131n kendi arka plan\u0131 ile d\u0131\u015f kart arka plan\u0131 i\xe7 i\xe7e iki kutu izlenimi yarat\u0131yordu. \u0130\xe7 kayna\u011f\u0131n arka plan\u0131 n\xf6trle\u015ftirildi, art\u0131k tek bir kart olarak g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcyor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcdd Rezervasyon Formu\\n\\n- **Ara\xe7 g\xf6rseli g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcrl\xfc\u011f\xfc:** Form ba\u015fl\u0131\u011f\u0131ndaki ara\xe7 g\xf6rseli a\xe7\u0131k arka planlarda d\xfc\u015f\xfck kontrasta sahipti. Alt\u0131na bir degrade arka plan eklenerek ara\xe7 her zaman g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcr durumda tutuluyor.\\n- **Kart ba\u015fl\u0131k stili birle\u015fimi:** Rezervasyon formunun farkl\u0131 b\xf6l\xfcmleri (tarih, m\xfc\u015fteri bilgisi, ek hizmetler, fiyat \xf6zeti) birbirinden farkl\u0131 ba\u015fl\u0131k stillerine sahipti. T\xfcm b\xf6l\xfcmler art\u0131k ayn\u0131 ba\u015fl\u0131k tipografisi ve padding de\u011ferlerini kullan\u0131yor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcb3 \xd6deme Sayfas\u0131\\n\\n- **\xd6deme y\xf6ntemleri dikey:** \xc7oklu \xf6deme y\xf6ntemi (kart, havale, kap\u0131da \xf6deme) etkin oldu\u011funda se\xe7enekler yatay olarak s\u0131ralan\u0131yor ve mobilde ta\u015f\u0131yordu. Art\u0131k tek s\xfctun, dikey stack \u2014 her ekran geni\u015fli\u011finde tutarl\u0131.\\n- **Kupon alan\u0131 ikon:** \\"Kupon kodunuz var m\u0131?\\" uyar\u0131 sat\u0131r\u0131ndaki ikon belirli tema kombinasyonlar\u0131nda bozuk (kare/?) g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcyordu. \u0130kon emoji ile de\u011fi\u015ftirildi, her temada render oluyor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\uded2 Sepet\\n\\n- **Rezervasyon meta sat\u0131rlar\u0131nda yeniden d\xfczen:** Rezervasyon detaylar\u0131 (tarih aral\u0131\u011f\u0131, ek hizmetler, teslim lokasyonu) daha \xf6nce tek bir c\xfcmle i\xe7inde virg\xfclle ayr\u0131lm\u0131\u015f \u015fekilde g\xf6steriliyordu \u2014 okunmas\u0131 zor. Art\u0131k her bilgi `Etiket: De\u011fer` format\u0131nda ayr\u0131 sat\u0131rlar halinde g\xf6steriliyor.\\n- **\xd6demeye git butonu hover:** Buton \xfczerine gelindi\u011finde yaz\u0131 rengi arka planla ayn\u0131 tonda kal\u0131p okunam\u0131yordu. Hover state rengi d\xfczeltildi, yaz\u0131 her durumda okunur.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| Alan | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|------|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131 | Spec chip ta\u015fma + hibrit yak\u0131t ikonu |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Takvim | Fazladan bo\u015f sat\u0131r + kutu i\xe7inde kutu g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcm\xfc |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Rezervasyon Formu | Ara\xe7 g\xf6rseli degrade arka plan + kart ba\u015fl\u0131k birle\u015ftirme |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 \xd6deme | Dikey \xf6deme y\xf6ntemleri + kupon ikon emoji |\\n| \ud83d\udd27 Sepet | Meta etiket/de\u011fer sat\u0131rlar\u0131 + \xf6demeye git hover |\\n\\n## \u2b06\ufe0f G\xfcncelleme Notu\\n\\nv4.26.1 **yaln\u0131zca CSS ve \u015fablon d\xfczeltmeleri** i\xe7erir \u2014 fonksiyonel de\u011fi\u015fiklik, DB \u015fema g\xfcncellemesi veya yeni ayar yoktur. v4.26.0\'dan g\xfcncellemek i\xe7in herhangi bir i\u015flem gerekmez:\\n\\n- WordPress admin \u2192 Eklentiler \u2192 G\xfcncelle\\n- Veya `wp plugin update mhm-rentiva --allow-root`\\n\\n\xd6zel tema override\'lar\u0131 yapmad\u0131ysan\u0131z g\xfcncelleme sonras\u0131 ek ad\u0131m gerekmez. Child theme ile `cart.php`, `checkout/form.php` veya rezervasyon formu \u015fablonlar\u0131n\u0131 override ettiyseniz, yeni s\xfcr\xfcmle uyumluluk i\xe7in \u015fablonlar\u0131n\u0131z\u0131 kar\u015f\u0131la\u015ft\u0131rman\u0131z\u0131 \xf6neririz.\\n\\n---\\n\\nDaha fazla bilgi i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edin."},{"id":"v4.26.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-07-v4.26.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-07-v4.26.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.0: Depozito Rezervasyonlar\u0131nda Kalan \xd6deme","description":"v4.26.0, depozito ile olu\u015fturulan rezervasyonlarda m\xfc\u015fterilerin kalan bakiyeyi do\u011frudan Hesab\u0131m ekran\u0131ndan \xf6deyebilmesini sa\u011fl\u0131yor. WooCommerce\'in native \xf6deme altyap\u0131s\u0131 kullan\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131ndan aktif t\xfcm \xf6deme y\xf6ntemleri otomatik olarak \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor.","date":"2026-04-07T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"payment","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/payment"},{"inline":true,"label":"woocommerce","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/woocommerce"},{"inline":true,"label":"deposit","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/deposit"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":1.45,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.26.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.0: Depozito Rezervasyonlar\u0131nda Kalan \xd6deme","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","payment","woocommerce","deposit","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-07T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.1: Ara\xe7 Detaylar\u0131, Rezervasyon, \xd6deme ve Sepet G\xf6rsel Cilas\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.1-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.25.0: Y\xf6netici Taraf\u0131ndan D\xfczenlenebilir Vendor E-posta \u015eablonlar\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.25.0-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.26.0, depozito ile olu\u015fturulan rezervasyonlarda m\xfc\u015fterilerin kalan bakiyeyi do\u011frudan Hesab\u0131m ekran\u0131ndan \xf6deyebilmesini sa\u011fl\u0131yor. WooCommerce\'in native \xf6deme altyap\u0131s\u0131 kullan\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131ndan aktif t\xfcm \xf6deme y\xf6ntemleri otomatik olarak \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kan Yenilik\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcb3 Kalan \xd6deme \u2014 Depozito Rezervasyonlar\u0131 i\xe7in\\n\\nDepozito ile rezervasyon olu\u015fturuldu\u011funda kalan bakiye daha \xf6nce yaln\u0131zca manuel takip ya da operat\xf6rle ileti\u015fim gerektiriyordu. v4.26.0 ile m\xfc\u015fteriler bu ad\u0131m\u0131 tamamen kendi ba\u015flar\u0131na tamamlayabiliyor.\\n\\n**Nas\u0131l \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131r:**\\n\\n1. M\xfc\u015fteri **Hesab\u0131m \u2192 Rezervasyon Detay\u0131** sayfas\u0131na gider\\n2. Kalan bakiye > 0 ise **\\"Kalan \xd6demeyi Yap\\"** butonu g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcr\\n3. Butona t\u0131kland\u0131\u011f\u0131nda tam tutar i\xe7in minimal bir WC sipari\u015fi arka planda olu\u015fturulur\\n4. M\xfc\u015fteri WooCommerce\'in native order-pay sayfas\u0131na y\xf6nlendirilir\\n5. \xd6deme ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 oldu\u011funda rezervasyon g\xfcncellenir: kalan bakiye s\u0131f\u0131rlan\u0131r, durum onaylan\u0131r\\n\\n**Teknik \xf6zellikler:**\\n\\n- `RemainingPaymentHandler` \u2014 AJAX endpoint, nonce + sahiplik do\u011frulamas\u0131\\n- **Tekrar sipari\u015f korumas\u0131:** Bekleyen kalan \xf6deme sipari\u015fi varsa yeni sipari\u015f olu\u015fturulmaz, mevcut sipari\u015f yeniden kullan\u0131l\u0131r (`_mhm_remaining_order_id` meta)\\n- **HPOS uyumlu:** T\xfcm WC sipari\u015f i\u015flemleri `$order->update_meta_data() + $order->save()` ile yap\u0131l\u0131r\\n- `WooCommerceBridge`: processing durumunda `_mhm_is_remaining_payment` bayra\u011f\u0131 varsa `_mhm_remaining_amount` s\u0131f\u0131rlan\u0131r\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Hata D\xfczeltmeleri\\n\\n### CSS Kapsam D\xfczeltmesi\\n\\nT\xfcm genel hesap sayfas\u0131 s\u0131n\u0131flar\u0131 (`.btn`, `.booking-item`, `.stat-card` vb.) art\u0131k `.mhm-rentiva-account-page` sarmalay\u0131c\u0131s\u0131 alt\u0131na al\u0131nd\u0131. Bu de\u011fi\u015fiklik WoodMart, Flatsome gibi premium temalarla ya\u015fanan g\xf6rsel \xe7ak\u0131\u015fmalar\u0131 engelliyor.\\n\\n### WC Hesab\u0131m Izgara D\xfczeni\\n\\nEntegre modda \u0131zgara tabanl\u0131 temalarda ya\u015fanan `grid-column` d\xfczeni sorunu giderildi (`grid-column: 1/-1`).\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \u2728 Yeni | Kalan \xf6deme butonu \u2014 Hesab\u0131m \u2192 Rezervasyon Detay\u0131 |\\n| \u2728 Yeni | `RemainingPaymentHandler` s\u0131n\u0131f\u0131 (AJAX + do\u011frulama) |\\n| \u2728 Yeni | Tekrar sipari\u015f korumas\u0131 (`_mhm_remaining_order_id` meta) |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | CSS kapsam \u2014 t\xfcm s\u0131n\u0131flar `.mhm-rentiva-account-page` alt\u0131na al\u0131nd\u0131 |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | WC Hesab\u0131m \u0131zgara d\xfczeni (grid-column: 1/-1) |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc1 De\u011fi\u015ftirilen Dosyalar\\n\\n- `src/Admin/Payment/WooCommerce/RemainingPaymentHandler.php` *(yeni)*\\n- `src/Admin/Payment/WooCommerce/WooCommerceBridge.php`\\n- `src/Admin/Frontend/Account/AccountController.php`\\n- `templates/account/booking-detail.php`\\n- `mhm-rentiva.php` *(versiyon g\xfcncelleme)*\\n\\n---\\n\\nDaha fazla bilgi i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edin."},{"id":"v4.25.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.25.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-04-01-v4.25.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-01-v4.25.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.25.0: Y\xf6netici Taraf\u0131ndan D\xfczenlenebilir Vendor E-posta \u015eablonlar\u0131","description":"v4.25.0, vendor bildirimleri i\xe7in y\xf6netici panelinden d\xfczenlenebilir e-posta \u015fablonlar\u0131 getiriyor. 22 vendor bildirim \u015fablonu art\u0131k Ayarlar ekran\u0131ndan \xf6zelle\u015ftirilebilir. Ayr\u0131ca Site Instance Check-in cron\'u Cron \u0130\u015f Monit\xf6r\xfc\'ne eklendi ve weekly WP cron interval\'inin g\xfcvenilir kayd\u0131 garanti alt\u0131na al\u0131nd\u0131.","date":"2026-04-01T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"email","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/email"},{"inline":true,"label":"accessibility","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/accessibility"},{"inline":true,"label":"bugfix","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/bugfix"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":1.71,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.25.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.25.0: Y\xf6netici Taraf\u0131ndan D\xfczenlenebilir Vendor E-posta \u015eablonlar\u0131","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","vendor","email","accessibility","bugfix","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-04-01T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.26.0: Depozito Rezervasyonlar\u0131nda Kalan \xd6deme","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.26.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.24.0: Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc Y\xf6netimi & Vendor Self-Servis","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.24.0-release-summary"}},"content":"v4.25.0, vendor bildirimleri i\xe7in y\xf6netici panelinden d\xfczenlenebilir e-posta \u015fablonlar\u0131 getiriyor. 22 vendor bildirim \u015fablonu art\u0131k Ayarlar ekran\u0131ndan \xf6zelle\u015ftirilebilir. Ayr\u0131ca Site Instance Check-in cron\'u Cron \u0130\u015f Monit\xf6r\xfc\'ne eklendi ve `weekly` WP cron interval\'inin g\xfcvenilir kayd\u0131 garanti alt\u0131na al\u0131nd\u0131.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kan Yenilikler\\n\\n### \u2709\ufe0f Y\xf6netici Taraf\u0131ndan D\xfczenlenebilir Vendor E-posta \u015eablonlar\u0131\\n\\n22 vendor bildirim \u015fablonu art\u0131k do\u011frudan admin panelinden d\xfczenlenebilir: **Ayarlar \u2192 Bildirim \u015eablonlar\u0131 \u2192 Vendor Bildirimleri** sekmesi.\\n\\n\u015eablonlar 4 b\xf6l\xfcme ayr\u0131lm\u0131\u015f durumda:\\n\\n| B\xf6l\xfcm | \u015eablon Say\u0131s\u0131 |\\n|-------|--------------|\\n| Vendor Hesap (kay\u0131t, onay, ret, ask\u0131) | 5 |\\n| Ara\xe7 \u0130nceleme (onay, ret, d\xfczenleme, yeniden inceleme) | 4 |\\n| Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc (duraklatma, devam, sona erme vb.) | 9 |\\n| Finansal E-postalar (\xf6deme, iade, fatura) | 4 |\\n\\n**Ak\u0131ll\u0131 Fallback Sistemi:**\\n- Konu alan\u0131 bo\u015f b\u0131rak\u0131l\u0131rsa \u2192 varsay\u0131lan konu metni g\xf6sterilir (admin ne g\xf6nderilece\u011fini g\xf6r\xfcr)\\n- G\xf6vde alan\u0131 bo\u015f = Gold Standard HTML dosya fallback \u2014 \xf6zelle\u015ftirme yap\u0131lmad\u0131\u011f\u0131nda profesyonel tasar\u0131m korunur\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf10 \xc7eviri Deste\u011fi\\n\\nVendor e-posta admin aray\xfcz\xfc i\xe7in **56 yeni T\xfcrk\xe7e \xe7eviri** eklendi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Teknik \u0130yile\u015ftirmeler\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfa8 Gold Standard E-posta \u015eablonu Gradient D\xfczeltmesi\\n\\nHeader ba\u015fl\u0131\u011f\u0131nda ger\xe7ek renk ge\xe7i\u015fi art\u0131k do\u011fru \xfcretiliyor \u2014 \xf6nceki s\xfcr\xfcmde gradient olu\u015fturma hesaplama hatas\u0131 vard\u0131.\\n\\n### \u267f Eri\u015filebilirlik: CTA Buton Kontrast Oran\u0131\\n\\nAra\xe7 yeniden inceleme admin e-postas\u0131ndaki amber CTA butonunun kontrast oran\u0131 **2.97:1\'den 6.8:1\'e** y\xfckseltildi. WCAG AA standard\u0131n\u0131 kar\u015f\u0131l\u0131yor.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd27 Site Instance Check-in Cron G\xf6r\xfcn\xfcrl\xfc\u011f\xfc\\n\\n`mhm_rentiva_instance_checkin` cron g\xf6revi art\u0131k **Cron \u0130\u015f Monit\xf6r\xfc**\'nde g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcyor ve \\"\u015eimdi \xc7al\u0131\u015ft\u0131r\\" butonu ile manuel tetiklenebiliyor. Bu sayede Lite site instance\'lar\u0131n\u0131n lisans sunucusuna kayd\u0131 izlenebilir.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd27 Weekly Cron Interval Garantisi\\n\\n`weekly` WP cron interval\'i art\u0131k eklenti taraf\u0131ndan a\xe7\u0131k\xe7a kay\u0131t ediliyor \u2014 WooCommerce gibi harici eklentilere ba\u011f\u0131ml\u0131l\u0131k kald\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \u2728 Yeni | 22 vendor bildirim \u015fablonu admin panelinden d\xfczenlenebilir |\\n| \u2728 Yeni | 4 b\xf6l\xfcm: Hesap (5), \u0130nceleme (4), Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc (9), Finansal (4) |\\n| \u2728 Yeni | Bo\u015f konu \u2192 varsay\u0131lan g\xf6ster; bo\u015f g\xf6vde \u2192 Gold Standard HTML fallback |\\n| \ud83c\udfa8 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Gold Standard gradient \xfcretimi d\xfczeltildi |\\n| \u267f Eri\u015filebilirlik | Amber CTA kontrast oran\u0131 2.97:1 \u2192 6.8:1 (WCAG AA) |\\n| \ud83c\udf10 \xc7eviri | 56 yeni T\xfcrk\xe7e \xe7eviri (vendor e-posta admin UI) |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | Site Instance Check-in cron Cron Monit\xf6r\xfc\'nde g\xf6r\xfcn\xfcr oldu |\\n| \ud83d\udc1b D\xfczeltme | weekly interval art\u0131k eklenti taraf\u0131ndan garantili kay\u0131t ediliyor |\\n\\n---\\n\\nDaha fazla bilgi i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edin."},{"id":"v4.24.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.24.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-03-28-v4.24.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-28-v4.24.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.24.0: Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc Y\xf6netimi & Vendor Self-Servis","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.24.0 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, ara\xe7lar\u0131n t\xfcm \xf6mr\xfc boyunca y\xf6netilebilece\u011fi tam durum makinesi, vendor\'lar\u0131n ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131 kendi kendine y\xf6netebilece\u011fi AJAX self-servis u\xe7 noktalar\u0131 ve adil rekabeti koruyan anti-gaming mekanizmalar\u0131 getiriyor.","date":"2026-03-28T20:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"lifecycle","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/lifecycle"},{"inline":true,"label":"reliability","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/reliability"},{"inline":true,"label":"notifications","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/notifications"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":3.11,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.24.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.24.0: Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc Y\xf6netimi & Vendor Self-Servis","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","vendor","lifecycle","reliability","notifications","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-03-28T20:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.25.0: Y\xf6netici Taraf\u0131ndan D\xfczenlenebilir Vendor E-posta \u015eablonlar\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.25.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.1: Vendor Form Yeniden Tasarimi & Sehir SelectWoo Migrasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.1-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.24.0** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, ara\xe7lar\u0131n t\xfcm \xf6mr\xfc boyunca y\xf6netilebilece\u011fi tam durum makinesi, vendor\'lar\u0131n ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131 kendi kendine y\xf6netebilece\u011fi AJAX self-servis u\xe7 noktalar\u0131 ve adil rekabeti koruyan anti-gaming mekanizmalar\u0131 getiriyor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kan Yenilikler\\n\\n### \ud83d\ude80 Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc Durum Makinesi\\n\\nv4.24.0\'\u0131n ana \xf6zelli\u011fi: ara\xe7lar\u0131n **Aktif \u2192 Duraklat\u0131lm\u0131\u015f \u2192 S\xfcresi Dolmu\u015f \u2192 Geri \xc7ekilmi\u015f** durumlar\u0131 aras\u0131ndaki ge\xe7i\u015flerini y\xf6neten tam durum makinesi.\\n\\n- **5 Durum:** `pending_review`, `active`, `paused`, `expired`, `withdrawn` \u2014 her ge\xe7i\u015f kurallarla korunuyor.\\n- **Ge\xe7i\u015f kurallar\u0131:** Hangi durumdan hangi duruma ge\xe7ilece\u011fi `VehicleLifecycleManager` taraf\u0131ndan zorunlu k\u0131l\u0131n\u0131r.\\n- **Admin UI:** Ara\xe7 listesinde ya\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc s\xfctunu, ara\xe7 d\xfczenleme ekran\u0131nda meta kutu.\\n\\n### \u23f1\ufe0f 90 G\xfcnl\xfck Listeleme S\xfcresi\\n\\n- Ara\xe7lar yay\u0131nland\u0131ktan **90 g\xfcn** sonra otomatik olarak s\xfcresi dolar.\\n- Sona ermeden **10 g\xfcn** ve **3 g\xfcn** \xf6nce vendor\'a uyar\u0131 e-postalar\u0131 g\xf6nderilir.\\n- G\xfcnl\xfck cron ile kontrol edilir; s\xfcresi dolan ara\xe7lar `expired` durumuna ge\xe7er.\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfae Vendor Self-Servis AJAX U\xe7 Noktalar\u0131\\n\\nVendor\'lar art\u0131k ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131 admin m\xfcdahalesi olmadan y\xf6netebilir:\\n\\n| \u0130\u015flem | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-------|----------|\\n| **Duraklat** | Aktif ara\xe7 ge\xe7ici olarak pasife al\u0131n\u0131r |\\n| **Devam Et** | Duraklat\u0131lm\u0131\u015f ara\xe7 tekrar aktifle\u015ftirilir |\\n| **Geri \xc7ek** | Ara\xe7 platformdan kal\u0131c\u0131 olarak \xe7ekilir (ceza uygulanabilir) |\\n| **Yenile** | S\xfcresi dolmu\u015f ara\xe7 yeniden aktifle\u015ftirilir |\\n| **Yeniden Listele** | Geri \xe7ekilmi\u015f ara\xe7 tekrar yay\u0131nlan\u0131r |\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcb8 Artan Geri \xc7ekme Ceza Sistemi\\n\\nVendor\'lar\u0131n s\u0131k s\u0131k ara\xe7 geri \xe7ekmesini \xf6nleyen kademeli ceza mekanizmas\u0131:\\n\\n- **1. geri \xe7ekme:** \xdccretsiz \u2014 ceza yok.\\n- **2. geri \xe7ekme:** Ayl\u0131k ortalama gelirin **%10**\'u kesilir.\\n- **3. ve sonras\u0131:** Ayl\u0131k ortalama gelirin **%25**\'i kesilir.\\n- **12 ayl\u0131k kayan pencere:** Ceza sayac\u0131 12 ay ge\xe7ince s\u0131f\u0131rlan\u0131r.\\n- Kesintiler do\u011frudan ledger\'a kaydedilir, payout hesab\u0131ndan d\xfc\u015f\xfcl\xfcr.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Anti-Gaming: Bloklu Tarih Korumas\u0131\\n\\nVendor\'lar\u0131n fiyat manip\xfclasyonunu \xf6nlemek i\xe7in:\\n\\n- Vendor iptal etti\u011fi rezervasyonun tarihleri **30 g\xfcn boyunca yeniden bloklan\u0131r**.\\n- Vendor d\xfc\u015f\xfck fiyatla almak i\xe7in iptal edip daha y\xfcksek fiyata satamaz.\\n- `AntiGamingBlocker` s\u0131n\u0131f\u0131 bu tarih blokajlar\u0131n\u0131 y\xf6netir.\\n\\n### \u2b50 Vendor G\xfcvenilirlik Puan\u0131\\n\\nT\xfcm platformda vendor kalitesini \xf6l\xe7en 0-100 aras\u0131 puan sistemi:\\n\\n- **G\xfcnl\xfck cron** ile yeniden hesaplama.\\n- **Form\xfcl:** \u0130ptal oran\u0131, geri \xe7ekme s\u0131kl\u0131\u011f\u0131, duraklatma ge\xe7mi\u015fi ve tamamlanan rezervasyon say\u0131s\u0131 bazl\u0131.\\n- Admin kullan\u0131c\u0131 listesinde vendor g\xfcvenilirlik s\xfctunu eklendi.\\n- Ara\xe7 kartlar\u0131nda vendor badge olarak g\xf6sterilmeye haz\u0131r.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce7 9 Yeni E-posta \u015eablonu\\n\\nYa\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfcn\xfcn her ad\u0131m\u0131 i\xe7in ayr\u0131 e-posta \u015fablonlar\u0131:\\n\\n| \u015eablon | Tetikleyici |\\n|--------|-------------|\\n| Ara\xe7 Aktifle\u015ftirildi | Ara\xe7 `active` durumuna ge\xe7ti\u011finde |\\n| Ara\xe7 Duraklat\u0131ld\u0131 | Vendor veya admin duraklatt\u0131\u011f\u0131nda |\\n| Duraklatma Devam Etti | Ara\xe7 yeniden aktifle\u015ftirildi\u011finde |\\n| Ara\xe7 Geri \xc7ekildi | Vendor geri \xe7ekme i\u015flemi yapt\u0131\u011f\u0131nda |\\n| Listeleme S\xfcresi Doldu | 90. g\xfcn sonunda otomatik |\\n| 10 G\xfcn Uyar\u0131s\u0131 | S\xfcre dolumundan 10 g\xfcn \xf6nce |\\n| 3 G\xfcn Uyar\u0131s\u0131 | S\xfcre dolumundan 3 g\xfcn \xf6nce |\\n| Ara\xe7 Yenilendi | S\xfcresi dolmu\u015f ara\xe7 yenilendi\u011finde |\\n| Ara\xe7 Yeniden Listelendi | Geri \xe7ekilmi\u015f ara\xe7 tekrar yay\u0131nland\u0131\u011f\u0131nda |\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Teknik \u0130yile\u015ftirmeler\\n\\n- **Aktif Filtre:** 6 frontend shortcode art\u0131k `MetaQueryHelper` arac\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131yla bak\u0131mdaki/pasif ara\xe7lar\u0131 filtreler \u2014 m\xfc\u015fteriler ge\xe7ersiz ara\xe7lar\u0131 g\xf6remez.\\n- **Veritaban\u0131:** `DatabaseMigrator v3.5.0` \u2014 mevcut t\xfcm aktif ara\xe7lar i\xe7in ya\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc durumu otomatik migrate edildi.\\n- **Login Y\xf6nlendirme:** `wp-login.php` eri\u015fimi WooCommerce hesap sayfas\u0131na y\xf6nlendirildi.\\n- **Lisans Check-in:** Haftal\u0131k cron ile instance check-in.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\ude80 Durum Makinesi | 5 durum, ge\xe7i\u015f kurallar\u0131, VehicleLifecycleManager. |\\n| \u23f1\ufe0f Listeleme S\xfcresi | 90 g\xfcn, cron tabanl\u0131, 10/3 g\xfcn uyar\u0131 e-postalar\u0131. |\\n| \ud83c\udfae Self-Servis | Duraklat, devam et, geri \xe7ek, yenile, yeniden listele AJAX. |\\n| \ud83d\udcb8 Ceza Sistemi | %0/%10/%25 kademeli, 12 ayl\u0131k kayan pencere, ledger entegrasyonu. |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Anti-Gaming | \u0130ptal edilen tarihler 30 g\xfcn bloklan\u0131r. |\\n| \u2b50 G\xfcvenilirlik | Vendor skoru 0-100, g\xfcnl\xfck cron yeniden hesaplama. |\\n| \ud83d\udce7 Bildirimler | 9 yeni ya\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc e-posta \u015fablonu. |\\n| \ud83d\udcca Admin UI | Ya\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc s\xfctunu, meta kutu, vendor g\xfcvenilirlik s\xfctunu. |\\n| \ud83d\udd0d Aktif Filtre | 6 shortcode MetaQueryHelper ile pasif ara\xe7lar\u0131 filtreler. |\\n| \ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f Veritaban\u0131 | v3.5.0 migration, mevcut ara\xe7lar migrate edildi. |\\n| \u2705 Test | 665 test, 2248 assertion (567/2036\'dan art\u0131\u015f). |\\n\\n### S\xfcr\xfcm Notlar\u0131\\n\\nv4.24.0, MHM Rentiva\'n\u0131n ara\xe7 y\xf6netim altyap\u0131s\u0131n\u0131 k\xf6kten g\xfc\xe7lendiriyor. Art\u0131k ara\xe7lar yaln\u0131zca \\"aktif/pasif\\" de\u011fil; tam bir ya\u015fam d\xf6ng\xfcs\xfcne sahip. Vendor\'lar ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131 kendi kendine y\xf6netirken platform, adil rekabeti ceza sistemi ve anti-gaming mekanizmalar\u0131yla koruyor. G\xfcvenilirlik puan\u0131 ise kaliteli vendor\'lar\u0131n \xf6ne \xe7\u0131kmas\u0131n\u0131 sa\u011flayan yeni bir rekabet boyutu ekliyor.\\n\\n---\\nMHM Rentiva hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi ve dok\xfcmantasyon i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edebilirsiniz."},{"id":"v4.23.1-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.1-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-03-28-v4.23.1-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-28-v4.23.1-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.1: Vendor Form Yeniden Tasarimi & Sehir SelectWoo Migrasyonu","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.1 surumu yayinlandi! Bu surum, vendor ayarlar sayfasinin tamamen yeniden tasarlanmasini, basvuru formundaki alan degisikliklerini, sehir secici bilesenlerin SelectWoo\'ya donusturulmesini ve arac sigorta belgesi yukleme ozelligini icerir.","date":"2026-03-28T18:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"forms","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/forms"},{"inline":true,"label":"selectwoo","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/selectwoo"},{"inline":true,"label":"vehicle","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vehicle"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":2.3,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.23.1-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.1: Vendor Form Yeniden Tasarimi & Sehir SelectWoo Migrasyonu","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","vendor","forms","selectwoo","vehicle","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-03-28T18:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.24.0: Ara\xe7 Ya\u015fam D\xf6ng\xfcs\xfc Y\xf6netimi & Vendor Self-Servis","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.24.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.0: Vendor Transfer Mimarisi & Dashboard Denetimi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.0-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.23.1** surumu yayinlandi! Bu surum, vendor ayarlar sayfasinin tamamen yeniden tasarlanmasini, basvuru formundaki alan degisikliklerini, sehir secici bilesenlerin SelectWoo\'ya donusturulmesini ve arac sigorta belgesi yukleme ozelligini icerir.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Onemli Yenilikler\\n\\n### Vendor Ayarlar Sayfasi Yeniden Tasarimi\\n\\nVendor ayarlar sayfasi (`vendor-settings.php`) sifirdan yeniden yazildi:\\n\\n- **Inline stil temizligi:** Tum inline CSS kaldirildi, `.mhm-vendor-form__*` CSS sinif yapisi ile `vendor-forms.css` dosyasina tasinarak bakim kolayligi saglandi.\\n- **Yeni alanlar:** Hesap Sahibi (Account Holder) ve Vergi Dairesi (Tax Office) alanlari eklendi.\\n- **Bildirim sistemi:** Bildirimler artik `mhm-vendor-notice` siniflariyla gosteriliyor.\\n\\n### Basvuru Formu Guncellemeleri\\n\\nVendor basvuru formunda onemli alan degisiklikleri yapildi:\\n\\n- **Hizmet Alanlari kaldirildi:** Checkbox olarak sunulan Hizmet Alanlari (Service Areas) bolumu kaldirildi; yerine bilgi notu eklendi.\\n- **Arac Sigortasi tasinidi:** Basvuru formundan kaldirilip arac ekleme formuna (`[rentiva_vehicle_submit]`) tasindi.\\n- **Yeni finansal alanlar:** Hesap Sahibi (zorunlu) ve Vergi Dairesi (opsiyonel) alanlari eklendi.\\n- **Meta senkronizasyonu:** `VendorApplicationManager` ve `VendorOnboardingController` onay akisinda yeni alanlarin senkronizasyonu saglandi.\\n\\n### Sehir SelectWoo Migrasyonu\\n\\nTum sehir metin girisleri (`<datalist>`) modern bir secim bilesenine donusturuldu:\\n\\n- **Yeni mimari:** `<select>` + WooCommerce selectWoo ile aranabilir, kullanici dostu sehir secimi.\\n- **Yeni metot:** `CityHelper::render_select()` \u2014 tum sehir secicilerde tek kaynak (SSOT).\\n- **Guncellenen formlar:** vendor-settings.php, VendorApply.php, VehicleSubmit.php, TransferAdmin.php.\\n- **CSS/JS enqueue:** UserDashboard.php, VendorApply.php ve VehicleSubmit.php dosyalarina SelectWoo asset\'leri eklendi.\\n\\n### Arac Sigorta Belgesi Yukleme\\n\\nArac ekleme formuna yeni bir belge yukleme bolumu eklendi:\\n\\n- Arac ruhsatindan sonra sigorta belgesi (`_mhm_rentiva_vehicle_insurance_doc`) yuklenebilir.\\n- VehicleSubmit.php AJAX handler\'i sigorta dosyasi isleme destegi ile guncellendi.\\n\\n### Arac Yasam Dongusu Yonetimi (Tasarim)\\n\\nKapsamli bir tasarim dokumani olusturuldu (`docs/plans/2026-03-28-vehicle-lifecycle-management-design.md`):\\n\\n- **Durumlar:** Aktif / Duraklatildi / Geri Cekildi / Suresi Doldu\\n- **Listeleme suresi:** 90 gun, yenileme mekanizmasi ile\\n- **Iptal ceza sistemi:** Kademeli ceza puanlari\\n- **Guvenilirlik skoru:** 0-100 arasi performans degerlendirmesi\\n- **Soguma suresi:** Geri cekilmeden sonra 7 gun bekleme\\n- **Tarih engelleme:** Kotu niyetli kullanima karsi onlem\\n- **8 fazli uygulama plani** hazirland\u0131\\n\\n## Kesfedilen Hatalar (Henuz Duzeltilmedi)\\n\\n| Hata | Detay |\\n|------|-------|\\n| Arac durumu arama filtresi | `_mhm_vehicle_status` arama sorgularinda kontrol edilmiyor \u2014 bakimdaki araclar arama sonuclarinda gorunuyor. |\\n| Vendor askiya alma | `VendorOnboardingController::suspend()` vendor\'un araclarini yayindan kaldirmiyor. |\\n\\n## Degisiklik Kaydi\\n\\n| Tur | Aciklama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| Vendor Ayarlar | Sayfa tamamen yeniden tasarlandi; inline stiller CSS sinif yapisina tasindi. |\\n| Vendor Ayarlar | Hesap Sahibi ve Vergi Dairesi alanlari eklendi. |\\n| Basvuru Formu | Hizmet Alanlari ve Arac Sigortasi alanlari kaldirildi/tasindi. |\\n| Basvuru Formu | Hesap Sahibi (zorunlu) ve Vergi Dairesi (opsiyonel) eklendi. |\\n| Sehir Secici | Tum datalist sehir girisleri SelectWoo bilesenine donusturuldu. |\\n| Arac Formu | Sigorta belgesi yukleme bolumu eklendi. |\\n| Tasarim | Arac Yasam Dongusu Yonetimi tasarim dokumani olusturuldu. |\\n| Hata Kesfedilen | 2 hata tespiti: arac durumu filtresi, vendor askiya alma. |\\n\\n### Surum Notlari\\nBu surum, vendor formlarinin modernizasyonu, sehir secici bilesenlerinin WooCommerce SelectWoo\'ya tas\u0131nmas\u0131 ve arac sigorta belgesi yukleme destegi ile vendor deneyimini onemli olcude iyilestirmistir. Arac Yasam Dongusu Yonetimi tasarim dokumani gelecek surumler icin yol haritasi saglamaktadir.\\n\\n---\\nMHM Rentiva hakkinda daha fazla bilgi ve dokumantasyon icin [Dokuman Sayfamizi](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edebilirsiniz."},{"id":"v4.23.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-03-26-v4.23.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-26-v4.23.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.0: Vendor Transfer Mimarisi & Dashboard Denetimi","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.0 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, vendor\'lar\u0131n transfer hizmetlerini \u015fehir bazl\u0131 y\xf6netebilmesini sa\u011flayan yeni bir mimari, kapsaml\u0131 Dashboard widget denetimi ve onlarca hata d\xfczeltmesi getiriyor.","date":"2026-03-26T18:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"dashboard","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/dashboard"},{"inline":true,"label":"export","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/export"},{"inline":true,"label":"search","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/search"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":2.4,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.23.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.0: Vendor Transfer Mimarisi & Dashboard Denetimi","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","vendor","transfer","dashboard","export","search","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-03-26T18:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.1: Vendor Form Yeniden Tasarimi & Sehir SelectWoo Migrasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.1-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.21.2: Vendor Y\xf6netimi ve Finansal Mimari Devrimi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.21.2-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.23.0** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, vendor\'lar\u0131n transfer hizmetlerini \u015fehir bazl\u0131 y\xf6netebilmesini sa\u011flayan yeni bir mimari, kapsaml\u0131 Dashboard widget denetimi ve onlarca hata d\xfczeltmesi getiriyor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kan Yenilikler\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Vendor Transfer Lokasyon Sistemi\\n\\nv4.23.0\'\u0131n en b\xfcy\xfck yenili\u011fi, **\u015eehir \u2192 Nokta hiyerar\u015fisi** ile vendor\'lar\u0131n transfer operasyonlar\u0131n\u0131 y\xf6netebilmesidir:\\n\\n- **\u015eehir bazl\u0131 filtreleme:** Her lokasyona bir \u015fehir alan\u0131 eklendi. Vendor\'lar yaln\u0131zca kendi \u015fehirlerindeki lokasyonlar\u0131 ve rotalar\u0131 g\xf6rebilir.\\n- **Rota bazl\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma:** Admin\'in belirledi\u011fi `min_price` \u2014 `max_price` aral\u0131\u011f\u0131nda her vendor kendi rota fiyat\u0131n\u0131 belirleyebilir.\\n- **Transfer arama motoru:** Rota bazl\u0131 ara\xe7 filtreleme ve vendor fiyat\u0131 deste\u011fi ile yeniden yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. Vendor fiyat\u0131 yoksa rotan\u0131n `base_price` de\u011feri fallback olarak kullan\u0131l\u0131r.\\n- **Veritaban\u0131:** `DatabaseMigrator v3.4.0` ile lokasyonlara `city` s\xfctunu, rotalara `max_price` s\xfctunu eklendi.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcca Dashboard Widget Denetimi (11 D\xfczeltme)\\n\\nDashboard widget\'lar\u0131nda kapsaml\u0131 bir denetim yap\u0131ld\u0131:\\n- **Timezone tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131:** Geri say\u0131m ve operasyon widget\'lar\u0131 WordPress timezone ayar\u0131na uyumlu hale getirildi.\\n- **Cache invalidation:** \u0130statistik cache key prefix uyumsuzlu\u011fu d\xfczeltildi.\\n- **WC email g\xf6rselleri:** Rezervasyon onay e-postalar\u0131nda ara\xe7 g\xf6rseli art\u0131k do\u011fru g\xf6steriliyor.\\n- **Tasar\u0131m iyile\u015ftirmeleri:** 2x2 grid istatistik kartlar\u0131, yerelle\u015ftirilmi\u015f gelir grafi\u011fi, mesajlar widget\'\u0131 yeniden tasarland\u0131.\\n- **Lite gating:** Gelir Grafi\u011fi ve Yakla\u015fan Operasyonlar widget\'lar\u0131 art\u0131k Pro-only.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd0e Arama ve Filtreleme D\xfczeltmeleri\\n\\n- **strtotime(\'\') hatas\u0131:** Bo\u015f tarih parametresi bug\xfcn\xfcn tarihini d\xf6nd\xfcr\xfcyordu, aktif booking\'li ara\xe7lar hatal\u0131 filtreleniyordu. Guard eklendi.\\n- **Lokasyon filtresi:** Radio butonlardan checkbox\'a d\xf6n\xfc\u015ft\xfcr\xfcld\xfc; birden fazla lokasyon se\xe7ilebilir.\\n- **Transfer tab do\u011frulama:** Transfer alanlar\u0131 (`origin_id`, `destination_id`, `date`, `luggage_*`) hardcoded required olarak ayarland\u0131.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udce4 D\u0131\u015fa Aktar\u0131m (4 D\xfczeltme)\\n\\n- \xd6deme g\xfcnl\xfckleri post_type uyumsuzlu\u011fu giderildi.\\n- Kay\u0131t say\u0131s\u0131 daima 0 d\xf6nen sorgu hatas\u0131 d\xfczeltildi.\\n- Ge\xe7mi\u015f silme i\u015flevi art\u0131k \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor (transient tabanl\u0131).\\n- Ara\xe7 CSV/JSON PHP 8 strict types fatal error\'\u0131 giderildi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc64 Vendor \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri\\n\\n- **Ara\xe7 ruhsat do\u011frulama:** Vendor ara\xe7 ekleme formunda ruhsat bilgisi do\u011frulan\u0131yor.\\n- **D\xfczenleme formu:** Vendor ara\xe7 d\xfczenlemesinde yeniden inceleme (re-review) mekanizmas\u0131.\\n- **Vendor rozeti:** Vendor ara\xe7lar\u0131nda tedarik\xe7i rozeti g\xf6r\xfcnt\xfcleniyor.\\n\\n## \u2699\ufe0f Di\u011fer \u0130yile\u015ftirmeler\\n\\n- **Engellli tarihler:** \\"T\xfcm\xfcne Uygula\\" AJAX d\xfczeltmesi; taray\u0131c\u0131 verisi payload\'da g\xf6nderiliyor.\\n- **Elementor:** 7 widget\'ta attribute kontrol say\u0131s\u0131 art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131 (VehicleComparison, MyBookings, MyFavorites, VehicleDetails, Testimonials, VehiclesGrid, FeaturedVehicles).\\n- **Ayarlar:** Cache tekrar\u0131, \xf6l\xfc ayarlar temizli\u011fi, SetupWizard sayfa listesi ve AssetManager guard d\xfczeltmeleri.\\n- **\xc7eviri:** 15+ yeni T\xfcrk\xe7e \xe7eviri, WP 6.5+ `.l10n.php` dosyas\u0131 yenilendi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Mimari | Vendor Transfer Lokasyon sistemi: \u015eehir\u2192Nokta hiyerar\u015fisi. |\\n| \ud83d\udcb0 Fiyatlama | Vendor rota bazl\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma (min/max aral\u0131\u011f\u0131). |\\n| \ud83d\udd0d Arama | Transfer arama motoru rota bazl\u0131 filtreleme + vendor fiyat\u0131. |\\n| \ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f Veritaban\u0131 | v3.4.0 migration: city + max_price s\xfctunlar\u0131. |\\n| \ud83d\udcca Dashboard | 11 hata d\xfczeltmesi: timezone, cache, WC email, tasar\u0131m, Lite gating. |\\n| \ud83d\udd0e Filtre | strtotime hatas\u0131, lokasyon checkbox, transfer tab do\u011frulama. |\\n| \ud83d\udcc5 Engelli Tarihler | \\"T\xfcm\xfcne Uygula\\" AJAX d\xfczeltmesi. |\\n| \ud83d\udce4 D\u0131\u015fa Aktar\u0131m | 4 kritik hata d\xfczeltmesi. |\\n| \ud83d\udc64 Vendor | Ruhsat do\u011frulama, yeniden inceleme, vendor rozeti. |\\n| \ud83c\udfa8 Elementor | 7 widget attribute iyile\u015ftirmesi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Ayarlar | Cache, \xf6l\xfc ayarlar, SetupWizard, AssetManager d\xfczeltmeleri. |\\n| \ud83c\udf10 \xc7eviri | 15+ yeni T\xfcrk\xe7e \xe7eviri, .l10n.php yenilendi. |\\n| \u2705 Test | 567 test, 2036 assertion. |\\n\\n### S\xfcr\xfcm Notlar\u0131\\nBu s\xfcr\xfcm, MHM Rentiva\'n\u0131n vendor transfer mimarisini temelden yeniden yap\u0131land\u0131rm\u0131\u015ft\u0131r. \u015eehir bazl\u0131 lokasyon filtresi, rota bazl\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma ve Dashboard widget denetimi ile platform daha kararl\u0131 ve zengin bir yap\u0131ya kavu\u015fmu\u015ftur.\\n\\n---\\nMHM Rentiva hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi ve dok\xfcmantasyon i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edebilirsiniz."},{"id":"v4.21.2-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.21.2-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-03-11-v4.21.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-11-v4.21.2-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.21.2: Vendor Y\xf6netimi ve Finansal Mimari Devrimi","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.21.2 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, eklentinin ticaret ve operasyon yeteneklerini k\xf6kten de\u011fi\u015ftiren \\"Vendor Management\\", \\"Financial Architecture\\" ve \\"VIP Transfer\\" mod\xfcllerini beraberinde getiriyor.","date":"2026-03-11T16:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"vendor","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vendor"},{"inline":true,"label":"finance","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/finance"},{"inline":true,"label":"payment","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/payment"},{"inline":true,"label":"vip-transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vip-transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":1.47,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.21.2-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.21.2: Vendor Y\xf6netimi ve Finansal Mimari Devrimi","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","vendor","finance","payment","vip-transfer","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-03-11T16:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.23.0: Vendor Transfer Mimarisi & Dashboard Denetimi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.23.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.10.0: Block/Shortcode Parity Stabilizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.10.0-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.21.2** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, eklentinin ticaret ve operasyon yeteneklerini k\xf6kten de\u011fi\u015ftiren \\"Vendor Management\\", \\"Financial Architecture\\" ve \\"VIP Transfer\\" mod\xfcllerini beraberinde getiriyor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kan Yenilikler\\n\\nBu g\xfcncelleme, MHM Rentiva\'y\u0131 sadece bir rezervasyon motoru olmaktan \xe7\u0131kar\u0131p, tam te\u015fekk\xfcll\xfc bir pazaryeri (marketplace) ve transfer y\xf6netim platformuna d\xf6n\xfc\u015ft\xfcr\xfcyor.\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfe2 Vendor (Tedarik\xe7i) Y\xf6netimi\\nArt\u0131k platformunuzda birden fazla tedarik\xe7iyi y\xf6netebilirsiniz. Her tedarik\xe7i kendi ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131, fiyatland\u0131rmas\u0131n\u0131 ve rezervasyonlar\u0131n\u0131 kontrol edebilir.\\n- **Tedarik\xe7i Paneli:** \xd6zelle\u015ftirilmi\u015f admin aray\xfcz\xfc.\\n- **Performans Takibi:** Tedarik\xe7i bazl\u0131 doluluk ve gelir raporlar\u0131.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcb0 Yeni Finansal Mimari\\n\xd6deme y\xf6netimi ve komisyon hesaplamalar\u0131 tamamen standardize edildi.\\n- **Commission Management:** Esnek komisyon oranlar\u0131 ve otomatik hesaplama.\\n- **Ledger System:** T\xfcm finansal hareketlerin \u015feffaf bir \u015fekilde kaydedildi\u011fi muhasebe defteri.\\n- **Payouts:** Tedarik\xe7i \xf6demelerinin merkezi takibi.\\n\\n### \ud83d\ude90 VIP Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc\\nNoktadan noktaya rota bazl\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma ve rezervasyon sistemi.\\n- **Rota Bazl\u0131 Fiyatland\u0131rma:** Mesafe veya rota bazl\u0131 dinamik fiyat tan\u0131mlama.\\n- **Transfer Rezervasyonu:** Ara\xe7 kiralama ak\u0131\u015f\u0131ndan ba\u011f\u0131ms\u0131z, optimize edilmi\u015f transfer deneyimi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Teknik \u0130yile\u015ftirmeler ve G\xfcvenlik\\n\\nSadece \xf6zellik de\u011fil, altyap\u0131 olarak da g\xfc\xe7lendik:\\n- **Hardened REST API:** `SecurityHelper` ve `AuthHelper` ile API u\xe7 noktalar\u0131 daha g\xfcvenli hale getirildi.\\n- **WP 6.7+ Uyumlu:** En son WordPress s\xfcr\xfcmleriyle tam uyumluluk ve performans optimizasyonu.\\n- **Modern Gereksinimler:** Minimum PHP 8.1+ ve WP 6.7+ standartlar\u0131na ge\xe7i\u015f yap\u0131ld\u0131.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \u2728 Yeni Mod\xfcl | Vendor Y\xf6netim Sistemi (Multi-vendor deste\u011fi). |\\n| \ud83d\udcb8 Finans | Geli\u015fmi\u015f finansal mimari, komisyon ve defter (ledger) sistemi. |\\n| \ud83d\udeeb Transfer | VIP Transfer mod\xfcl\xfc ve rota bazl\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma motoru. |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | REST API g\xfcvenlik katmanlar\u0131 (`AuthHelper` entegrasyonu). |\\n| \ud83d\ude80 Performans | PHP 8.1+ optimizasyonu ve autoloader iyile\u015ftirmeleri. |\\n| \ud83e\uddf9 Paketleme | `.distignore` ile optimize edilmi\u015f, tertemiz eklenti paketi yap\u0131s\u0131. |\\n\\n### S\xfcr\xfcm Notlar\u0131\\nBu s\xfcr\xfcm, `mhm-rentiva` ekosisteminde bug\xfcne kadar yap\u0131lm\u0131\u015f en kapsaml\u0131 mod\xfcler geni\u015fletmedir. Mod\xfcller aras\u0131 veri b\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc `Util::has_overlap()` ve `DepositCalculator` gibi merkezi s\u0131n\u0131flar \xfczerinden garanti alt\u0131na al\u0131nm\u0131\u015ft\u0131r.\\n\\n---\\nMHM Rentiva hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi ve dok\xfcmantasyon i\xe7in [Dok\xfcman Sayfam\u0131z\u0131](https://maxhandmade.github.io/mhm-rentiva-docs/) ziyaret edebilirsiniz."},{"id":"v4.10.0-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.10.0-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-02-18-v4.10.0-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-18-v4.10.0-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.10.0: Block/Shortcode Parity Stabilizasyonu","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.10.0 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu b\xfcy\xfck g\xfcncelleme ile Gutenberg bloklar\u0131 ve k\u0131sa kodlar (shortcode) aras\u0131ndaki tam e\u015flik (parity) sa\u011fland\u0131; 19/19 deterministic y\xfczey do\u011fruland\u0131.","date":"2026-02-18T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"gutenberg","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/gutenberg"},{"inline":true,"label":"blocks","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/blocks"},{"inline":true,"label":"shortcode","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/shortcode"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":0.82,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.10.0-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.10.0: Block/Shortcode Parity Stabilizasyonu","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","gutenberg","blocks","shortcode","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-02-18T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.21.2: Vendor Y\xf6netimi ve Finansal Mimari Devrimi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.21.2-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.8: URL Tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve WooCommerce \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.8-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.10.0** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu b\xfcy\xfck g\xfcncelleme ile Gutenberg bloklar\u0131 ve k\u0131sa kodlar (shortcode) aras\u0131ndaki tam e\u015flik (parity) sa\u011fland\u0131; 19/19 deterministic y\xfczey do\u011fruland\u0131.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83c\udfaf E\u015flik (Parity) | Block \u2194 Shortcode tam e\u015fli\u011fi sa\u011fland\u0131 \u2014 19/19 deterministic y\xfczey do\u011fruland\u0131. |\\n| \ud83d\udd17 E\u015fleme (Mapping) | `vehicle-comparison`, `booking-form` ve `testimonials` bloklar\u0131 i\xe7in deterministik alias e\u015flemesi eklendi. |\\n| \ud83d\udd04 D\xf6n\xfc\u015f\xfcm (Transform) | `showFeatures` de\u011fer d\xf6n\xfc\u015f\xfcm\xfc kapsam izolasyonuyla stabilize edildi (boolean \u2192 `all`/`basic`). |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Booking form dinamik varsay\u0131lan korumas\u0131 eklendi (`defaultDays`/`minDays`/`maxDays` statik override engellendi). |\\n| \ud83d\udccb Denetim | 19/19 Light Parity Audit tam kan\u0131t zinciriyle tamamland\u0131. |\\n| \u2705 Kalite Kap\u0131lar\u0131 | PHPCS, Plugin Check, PHPUnit \u2014 0 hata, tam suite ge\xe7i\u015fi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\n\\nBu s\xfcr\xfcm, MHM Rentiva\'n\u0131n blok ve k\u0131sa kod \xe7\u0131kt\u0131lar\u0131n\u0131 birbirinin ayn\u0131s\u0131 haline getiren kapsaml\u0131 bir stabilizasyon \xe7al\u0131\u015fmas\u0131n\u0131n \xfcr\xfcn\xfcd\xfcr. Art\u0131k ayn\u0131 i\xe7erik hem Gutenberg blo\u011fu hem de `[mhm_rentiva_*]` k\u0131sa kodu olarak eklendi\u011finde birebir ayn\u0131 HTML \xe7\u0131kt\u0131s\u0131 ve davran\u0131\u015f elde edilmektedir.\\n\\nKalite kap\u0131lar\u0131 post-bump olarak do\u011fruland\u0131:\\n\\n| Kap\u0131 | Sonu\xe7 |\\n|------|-------|\\n| PHPCS | \u2705 0 hata |\\n| Plugin Check | \u2705 PASS (exit code 0) |\\n| PHPUnit | \u2705 216 test, 0 ba\u015far\u0131s\u0131zl\u0131k |"},{"id":"v4.9.8-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.8-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-02-09-v4.9.8-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-09-v4.9.8-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.8: URL Tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve WooCommerce \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.8 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile WooCommerce entegrasyonu g\xfc\xe7lendirildi ve kal\u0131c\u0131 link (permalink) yap\u0131s\u0131ndaki tutarl\u0131l\u0131k art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131.","date":"2026-02-09T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"woocommerce","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/woocommerce"},{"inline":true,"label":"mhm-rentiva","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/mhm-rentiva"}],"readingTime":0.43,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.9.8-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.8: URL Tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve WooCommerce \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","woocommerce","mhm-rentiva"],"date":"2026-02-09T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.10.0: Block/Shortcode Parity Stabilizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.10.0-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.7: Gutenberg UI/UX Standardizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.7-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.9.8** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile WooCommerce entegrasyonu g\xfc\xe7lendirildi ve kal\u0131c\u0131 link (permalink) yap\u0131s\u0131ndaki tutarl\u0131l\u0131k art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | WooCommerce Hesab\u0131m u\xe7 noktalar\u0131nda fiziksel sayfa k\u0131sa isimlerine (slug) mutlak \xf6ncelik verildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Entegre panel d\xfczeni korundu; \xf6zel linklerde (\xf6rn. /favorilerim/) d\u0131\u015fa y\xf6nlendirme sorunu giderildi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Kararl\u0131l\u0131k | URL tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\xe7in kal\u0131c\u0131 linklerin (rewrite rules) otomatik yenilenmesi sa\u011fland\u0131. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nBu s\xfcr\xfcm, kullan\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n \\"Hesab\u0131m\\" panelindeki deneyimini p\xfcr\xfczs\xfcz hale getirmeye odaklan\u0131yor. \xd6zellikle \xf6zel sayfa yap\u0131s\u0131 kullanan temalarda ya\u015fanan y\xf6nlendirme sorunlar\u0131 giderilerek sistem daha kararl\u0131 hale getirildi."},{"id":"v4.9.7-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.7-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-02-08-v4.9.7-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-08-v4.9.7-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.7: Gutenberg UI/UX Standardizasyonu","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.7 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile Gutenberg blok edit\xf6r\xfc deneyimi standartla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131 ve konsol uyar\u0131lar\u0131 temizlendi.","date":"2026-02-08T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"gutenberg","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/gutenberg"},{"inline":true,"label":"ui-ux","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/ui-ux"}],"readingTime":0.37,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.9.7-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.7: Gutenberg UI/UX Standardizasyonu","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","gutenberg","ui-ux"],"date":"2026-02-08T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.8: URL Tutarl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve WooCommerce \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.8-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.6: Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc ve B\xfcy\xfck Bak\u0131m","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.6-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.9.7** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile Gutenberg blok edit\xf6r\xfc deneyimi standartla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131 ve konsol uyar\u0131lar\u0131 temizlendi.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \u2728 \xd6zellik | Gutenberg blok kenar \xe7ubuklar\u0131 (InspectorControls) tutarl\u0131 UI/UX i\xe7in standartla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. |\\n| \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | Blok edit\xf6r\xfcndeki konsol uyar\u0131lar\u0131 giderilerek kararl\u0131l\u0131k art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Proje dok\xfcmantasyonu ve kurallar\u0131 g\xfcncellendi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nEdit\xf6r taraf\u0131ndaki kullan\u0131c\u0131 deneyimini iyile\u015ftirmek ad\u0131na Gutenberg blok kontrolleri daha d\xfczenli hale getirildi. Arka planda \xe7al\u0131\u015fan scriptlerdeki ufak hatalar giderilerek temiz bir \xe7al\u0131\u015fma ortam\u0131 sa\u011fland\u0131."},{"id":"v4.9.6-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.6-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-02-02-v4.9.6-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-02-v4.9.6-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.6: Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc ve B\xfcy\xfck Bak\u0131m","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.6 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc entegrasyonu ve kapsaml\u0131 veritaban\u0131 ta\u015f\u0131ma mant\u0131\u011f\u0131 gibi kritik g\xfcncellemeler i\xe7ermektedir.","date":"2026-02-02T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/transfer"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/performance"}],"readingTime":0.5,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.9.6-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.6: Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc ve B\xfcy\xfck Bak\u0131m","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","transfer","performance"],"date":"2026-02-02T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.7: Gutenberg UI/UX Standardizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.7-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.7: G\xfcvenlik ve Performans Optimizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.7-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.9.6** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc entegrasyonu ve kapsaml\u0131 veritaban\u0131 ta\u015f\u0131ma mant\u0131\u011f\u0131 gibi kritik g\xfcncellemeler i\xe7ermektedir.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \u2728 \xd6zellik | Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc: \xd6n ek standardizasyonu (rentiva_) ve veritaban\u0131 ta\u015f\u0131ma mant\u0131\u011f\u0131 tamamland\u0131. |\\n| \u26a1 Performans | Genel kod optimizasyonu ve performans iyile\u015ftirmeleri yap\u0131ld\u0131. |\\n| \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | M\xfcsaitlik Takvimi i\xe7in HTML yap\u0131s\u0131 daha iyi eri\u015filebilirlik i\xe7in g\xfcncellendi. |\\n| \ud83c\udfa8 Stil | Daha iyi bak\u0131m i\xe7in CSS mimarisi temizlendi ve yeniden yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. |\\n| \ud83c\udf10 i18n | Yeni \xe7eviri dosyalar\u0131 eklendi ve mevcut \xe7eviriler iyile\u015ftirildi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nY\xfcksek performansl\u0131 bir altyap\u0131 i\xe7in CSS ve PHP taraf\u0131nda b\xfcy\xfck \xe7apl\u0131 temizlik yap\u0131ld\u0131. Transfer mod\xfcl\xfcn\xfcn veritaban\u0131 yap\u0131s\u0131 standartlara uygun hale getirilerek sistem kararl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131."},{"id":"v4.6.7-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.7-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-02-01-v4.6.7-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-01-v4.6.7-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.7: G\xfcvenlik ve Performans Optimizasyonu","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.7 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile y\xf6nlendirme g\xfcvenli\u011fi, SQL optimizasyonu ve stil y\xf6netimi modern standartlara ta\u015f\u0131nd\u0131.","date":"2026-02-01T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/performance"}],"readingTime":0.42,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.7-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.7: G\xfcvenlik ve Performans Optimizasyonu","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","security","performance"],"date":"2026-02-01T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.9.6: Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc ve B\xfcy\xfck Bak\u0131m","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.9.6-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.6: Rezervasyon Formu ve Fiyatland\u0131rma \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.6-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.7** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme ile y\xf6nlendirme g\xfcvenli\u011fi, SQL optimizasyonu ve stil y\xf6netimi modern standartlara ta\u015f\u0131nd\u0131.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Y\xf6nlendirme g\xfcvenli\u011fini art\u0131rmak i\xe7in `wp_safe_redirect` kullan\u0131m\u0131na ge\xe7ildi. |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | `SecurityHelper::safe_output()` metodu ba\u011flam do\u011frulamas\u0131 ve JSON deste\u011fiyle modernize edildi. |\\n| \u26a1 Performans | SQL transient silme i\u015flemi, native `delete_transient()` fonksiyonuna \xe7evrildi. |\\n| \ud83c\udfa8 Stil | Sat\u0131r i\xe7i CSS kodlar\u0131 `wp_add_inline_style` API\'sine ta\u015f\u0131narak standartla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nEklentinin \xe7ekirdek fonksiyonlar\u0131 daha g\xfcvenli ve performansl\u0131 hale getirildi. \xd6zellikle y\xf6nlendirme ve veri \xe7\u0131kt\u0131 i\u015flemleri WordPress\'in en g\xfcncel g\xfcvenlik protokollerine g\xf6re optimize edildi."},{"id":"v4.6.6-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.6-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-28-v4.6.6-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-28-v4.6.6-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.6: Rezervasyon Formu ve Fiyatland\u0131rma \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.6 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme, rezervasyon formundaki g\xf6rsel hatalar\u0131 giderir ve yeni bir fiyatland\u0131rma detay\u0131 ekler.","date":"2026-01-28T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"interface","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/interface"},{"inline":true,"label":"booking","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/booking"}],"readingTime":0.51,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.6-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.6: Rezervasyon Formu ve Fiyatland\u0131rma \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","interface","booking"],"date":"2026-01-28T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.7: G\xfcvenlik ve Performans Optimizasyonu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.7-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.5: WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu ve Kod Standartlar\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.5-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.6** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme, rezervasyon formundaki g\xf6rsel hatalar\u0131 giderir ve yeni bir fiyatland\u0131rma detay\u0131 ekler.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | Rezervasyon formundaki ara\xe7 \xf6zellik ikonlar\u0131n\u0131n (yak\u0131t, vites vb.) kaybolma sorunu giderildi. |\\n| \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltme | Ara\xe7 \xf6zellik verilerinin i\u015flenmesi s\u0131ras\u0131nda olu\u015fan mant\u0131ksal hatalar d\xfczeltildi. |\\n| \u2728 \xd6zellik | Rezervasyon formu fiyat detay\u0131na \'Hafta Sonu Fark\u0131\' g\xf6sterimi eklendi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Rezervasyon formu g\xf6rselle\u015ftirmesi ve ikon boyutland\u0131rmalar\u0131 optimize edildi. |\\n| \ud83e\uddf9 Temizlik | \xc7ak\u0131\u015fan eski CSS kodlar\u0131 temizlendi ve modern yap\u0131ya ge\xe7ildi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nKullan\u0131c\u0131 deneyimini iyile\u015ftirmek ad\u0131na rezervasyon formundaki ikon sorunlar\u0131 \xe7\xf6z\xfcld\xfc ve fiyatland\u0131rma \u015feffafl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\xe7in hafta sonu fark\u0131 detay\u0131 eklendi. CSS yap\u0131s\u0131 daha sade ve h\u0131zl\u0131 hale getirildi."},{"id":"v4.6.5-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.5-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-26-v4.6.5-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-26-v4.6.5-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.5: WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu ve Kod Standartlar\u0131","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.5 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu b\xfcy\xfck \xf6l\xe7ekli altyap\u0131 g\xfcncellemesi ile 110.000+ sat\u0131r kod WordPress standartlar\u0131na (WPCS) uyumlu hale getirildi.","date":"2026-01-26T15:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"refactoring","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/refactoring"}],"readingTime":0.43,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.5-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.5: WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu ve Kod Standartlar\u0131","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","security","refactoring"],"date":"2026-01-26T15:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.6: Rezervasyon Formu ve Fiyatland\u0131rma \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.6-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.4: Veri B\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc ve \xc7\u0131kt\u0131 G\xfcvenli\u011fi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.4-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.5** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu b\xfcy\xfck \xf6l\xe7ekli altyap\u0131 g\xfcncellemesi ile 110.000+ sat\u0131r kod WordPress standartlar\u0131na (WPCS) uyumlu hale getirildi.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | 50+ WPCS g\xfcvenlik uyar\u0131s\u0131 \xe7\xf6z\xfcld\xfc (Girdi Sanitizasyonu & DB \u0130nterpolasyonu). |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Handler.php ve AccountController.php XSS\'e kar\u015f\u0131 g\xfc\xe7lendirildi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Kararl\u0131l\u0131k | Eski `error_log` yap\u0131s\u0131 modern `AdvancedLogger` mimarisiyle de\u011fi\u015ftirildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | 110.000+ WordPress Kodlama Standartlar\u0131 (WPCS) uyumsuzlu\u011fu otomatik d\xfczeltildi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nBu g\xfcncelleme eklentimizin gelecekteki geli\u015fimini sa\u011flam bir temele oturtmaktad\u0131r. Geni\u015f \xe7apl\u0131 kod standartlar\u0131 denetimi ile hem g\xfcvenlik hem de bak\u0131m kolayl\u0131\u011f\u0131 en \xfcst d\xfczeye \xe7\u0131kar\u0131ld\u0131."},{"id":"v4.6.4-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.4-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-26-v4.6.4-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-26-v4.6.4-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.4: Veri B\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc ve \xc7\u0131kt\u0131 G\xfcvenli\u011fi","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.4 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcmde y\xf6netici paneli \xe7\u0131kt\u0131 g\xfcvenli\u011fi ve para birimi sembollerindeki tutarl\u0131l\u0131k hatalar\u0131 giderildi.","date":"2026-01-26T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"data-integrity","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/data-integrity"}],"readingTime":0.5,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.4-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.4: Veri B\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc ve \xc7\u0131kt\u0131 G\xfcvenli\u011fi","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","security","data-integrity"],"date":"2026-01-26T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.5: WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu ve Kod Standartlar\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.5-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.3: SQL G\xfcvenli\u011fi ve REST API Kararl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.3-release-summary"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.4** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcmde y\xf6netici paneli \xe7\u0131kt\u0131 g\xfcvenli\u011fi ve para birimi sembollerindeki tutarl\u0131l\u0131k hatalar\u0131 giderildi.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Admin sekmelerinde `esc_html` ve `wp_kses_post` kullan\u0131larak \xe7\u0131kt\u0131 ka\xe7\u0131rma i\u015flemleri g\xfc\xe7lendirildi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Kararl\u0131l\u0131k | AddonManager ve Rezervasyon Meta Kutular\u0131ndaki fiyat/ID alanlar\u0131 i\xe7in sanitizasyon iyile\u015ftirildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Rezervasyon D\xfczenleme ekranlar\u0131ndaki hardcoded para birimi sembol sorunlar\u0131 giderildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Ara\xe7 kolonlar\u0131 ve sistem bilgisi sayfalar\u0131ndaki SQL sorgular\u0131 optimize edildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Manuel rezarvasyon ve ara\xe7 y\xf6netiminde kalan baz\u0131 T\xfcrk\xe7e dizeler \u0130ngilizce\'ye \xe7evrildi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nY\xf6netici panelindeki veri giri\u015f ve \xe7\u0131k\u0131\u015f noktalar\u0131nda g\xfcvenlik standartlar\u0131 art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. \xd6zellikle fiyatland\u0131rma alanlar\u0131ndaki sanitizasyon iyile\u015ftirmeleri veri b\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfcn\xfc garanti alt\u0131na almaktad\u0131r."},{"id":"v4.6.3-release-summary","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.3-release-summary","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-25-v4.6.3-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-25-v4.6.3-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.3: SQL G\xfcvenli\u011fi ve REST API Kararl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.3 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme, SQL Injection korumas\u0131 ve AJAX g\xfcvenilirli\u011fi \xfczerine \xf6nemli iyile\u015ftirmeler i\xe7ermektedir.","date":"2026-01-25T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"rest-api","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/rest-api"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.3-release-summary","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.3: SQL G\xfcvenli\u011fi ve REST API Kararl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","security","rest-api"],"date":"2026-01-25T09:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.4: Veri B\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc ve \xc7\u0131kt\u0131 G\xfcvenli\u011fi","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.4-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.2: G\xfcvenlik Tahkimat\u0131 ve WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.2-security-update"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.3** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu g\xfcncelleme, SQL Injection korumas\u0131 ve AJAX g\xfcvenilirli\u011fi \xfczerine \xf6nemli iyile\u015ftirmeler i\xe7ermektedir.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 De\u011fi\u015fiklik Kayd\u0131\\n\\n| T\xfcr | A\xe7\u0131klama |\\n|-----|----------|\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | Mesaj arama sorgular\u0131 prepared statements kullan\u0131larak SQL Injection\'a kar\u015f\u0131 g\xfc\xe7lendirildi. |\\n| \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik | REST API entegrasyon ayarlar\u0131n\u0131n backend mimarisi, AJAX buton g\xfcvenilirli\u011fini art\u0131racak \u015fekilde g\xfcncellendi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Kararl\u0131l\u0131k | Asenkron isteklerde \'-1\' hatas\u0131n\u0131 \xf6nlemek i\xe7in AJAX hook kay\u0131t sistemi iyile\u015ftirildi. |\\n| \u2699\ufe0f Kararl\u0131l\u0131k | REST ayarlar\u0131nda IP listesi sanitizasyon hatalar\u0131 giderildi. |\\n| \u26a1 \u0130yile\u015ftirme | Proje kaynak kodu dok\xfcmantasyonu WPCS uyumlulu\u011fu i\xe7in tamamen \u0130ngilizce\'ye \xe7evrildi. |\\n\\n### Detaylar\\nBu s\xfcr\xfcmle birlikte mesajla\u015fma sistemindeki arama fonksiyonlar\u0131 ve AJAX tabanl\u0131 ayar kaydediciler daha g\xfcvenli ve kararl\u0131 hale getirildi. \xd6zellikle geli\u015ftiriciler i\xe7in kod taban\u0131ndaki yorum sat\u0131rlar\u0131 d\xfcnya standartlar\u0131na (WPCS) uygun hale getirildi."},{"id":"v4.6.2-security-update","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.2-security-update","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-22-v4.6.2-release.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-22-v4.6.2-release.md","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.2: G\xfcvenlik Tahkimat\u0131 ve WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.2 yay\u0131nda! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, eklentinin t\xfcm mod\xfcllerini kapsayan devasa bir g\xfcvenlik ve altyap\u0131 g\xfc\xe7lendirme g\xfcncellemesidir. Yeni \xf6zellik eklemekten ziyade, mevcut sistemin a\u015f\u0131lmaz bir kale haline getirilmesine odakland\u0131k.","date":"2026-01-22T06:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"wpcs","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/wpcs"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":1.21,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4.6.2-security-update","title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.2: G\xfcvenlik Tahkimat\u0131 ve WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","security","wpcs","update"],"date":"2026-01-22T06:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.3: SQL G\xfcvenli\u011fi ve REST API Kararl\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.3-release-summary"},"nextItem":{"title":"v4.6.1 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-1-released"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.2** yay\u0131nda! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, eklentinin t\xfcm mod\xfcllerini kapsayan devasa bir g\xfcvenlik ve altyap\u0131 g\xfc\xe7lendirme g\xfcncellemesidir. Yeni \xf6zellik eklemekten ziyade, mevcut sistemin **a\u015f\u0131lmaz bir kale** haline getirilmesine odakland\u0131k.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f G\xfcvenlik Denetimi \xd6zeti\\n\\nSon 24 saat i\xe7inde, MHM Rentiva\'n\u0131n 22 farkl\u0131 mod\xfcl\xfc \xfczerinde sat\u0131r sat\u0131r kod analizi ger\xe7ekle\u015ftirdik. Hedefimiz sadece \\"\xe7al\u0131\u015fan\\" bir eklenti de\u011fil, \\"en g\xfcvenli\\" kiralama eklentisi olmakt\u0131r.\\n\\n\u0130\u015fte bu g\xfcncellemenin karnesi:\\n\\n| Metrik | De\u011fer |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| **Denetlenen Mod\xfcller** | 22 (T\xfcm\xfc) |\\n| **D\xfczenlenen Dosyalar** | 59+ |\\n| **Nonce (CSRF) Yamas\u0131** | 91+ |\\n| **WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu** | %100 |\\n\\n### Neler De\u011fi\u015fti?\\n\\n#### 1. Tam Kapsaml\u0131 Nonce Korumas\u0131\\nWordPress\'in g\xfcvenlik mekanizmas\u0131 olan `nonce` (number used once) kullan\u0131m\u0131 t\xfcm form ve AJAX i\u015flemlerinde standartla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131. Her bir do\u011frulama i\u015flemi art\u0131k `sanitize_text_field(wp_unslash())` sarmalay\u0131c\u0131s\u0131 ile ekstra bir temizlik katman\u0131ndan ge\xe7iriliyor.\\n\\n#### 2. REST API ve Rate Limiting\\nAPI taraf\u0131nda **H\u0131z S\u0131n\u0131rlama (Rate Limiting)** ve **IP K\u0131s\u0131tlama** mekanizmalar\u0131 \xe7ekirdek yap\u0131ya daha s\u0131k\u0131 entegre edildi. Art\u0131k `CoreSettings` yerine `RESTSettings` \xfczerinden y\xf6netilen bu yap\u0131, yetkisiz eri\u015fim denemelerini an\u0131nda engelliyor.\\n\\n> Detaylar i\xe7in yenilenen [REST API Dok\xfcmantasyonu](../docs/api/overview) sayfas\u0131n\u0131 inceleyebilirsiniz.\\n\\n#### 3. Kod Kalitesi ve PHP 8.4+ Uyumu\\nGelece\u011fe haz\u0131rl\u0131k kapsam\u0131nda, PHP 8.4 ve \xfczeri s\xfcr\xfcmlerde ortaya \xe7\u0131kabilecek \\"Implicit Nullable Parameter\\" uyar\u0131lar\u0131 giderildi. Kod taban\u0131 daha modern, temiz ve hatas\u0131z hale getirildi.\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Yeni Teknik Dok\xfcmantasyon\\n\\nMod\xfcler yap\u0131m\u0131z\u0131 daha iyi anlatabilmek ve geli\u015ftiricilere rehberlik etmek i\xe7in dok\xfcmantasyonumuza yeni bir b\xf6l\xfcm ekledik:\\n\\n*   [**Mod\xfcl Mimarisi ve Teknik Harita:**](../docs/developer/core/technical-architecture) Eklentinin 22 mod\xfcl\xfcn\xfcn ili\u015fkilerini, dosya yap\u0131s\u0131n\u0131 ve g\xfcvenlik durumunu g\xf6steren kapsaml\u0131 bir rehber.\\n\\n---\\n\\nMHM Rentiva ile g\xfcvenli ve performansl\u0131 kiralamalar dileriz! \ud83d\ude80"},{"id":"v4-6-1-released","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-1-released","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-21-v4-6-1-released.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-21-v4-6-1-released.md","title":"v4.6.1 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.1 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, veri b\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc, g\xfcvenlik ve WooCommerce entegrasyonu konular\u0131nda kritik iyile\u015ftirmeler i\xe7eren bir g\xfcvenlik ve kararl\u0131l\u0131k g\xfcncellemesidir.","date":"2026-01-21T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"v4.6.1","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/v-4-6-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"critical","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/critical"},{"inline":true,"label":"woocommerce","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/woocommerce"}],"readingTime":1.18,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4-6-1-released","title":"v4.6.1 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","v4.6.1","security","critical","woocommerce"],"date":"2026-01-21T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.2: G\xfcvenlik Tahkimat\u0131 ve WPCS Uyumlulu\u011fu","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4.6.2-security-update"},"nextItem":{"title":"v4.6.0 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-0-released"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.1** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, **veri b\xfct\xfcnl\xfc\u011f\xfc**, **g\xfcvenlik** ve **WooCommerce entegrasyonu** konular\u0131nda kritik iyile\u015ftirmeler i\xe7eren bir g\xfcvenlik ve kararl\u0131l\u0131k g\xfcncellemesidir.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Kritik G\xfcvenlik ve Veri Koruma\\n\\n### \ud83e\uddf9 DatabaseCleaner \u0130yile\u015ftirmesi\\nVeritaban\u0131 temizleme arac\u0131m\u0131z, art\u0131k \xe7ok daha ak\u0131ll\u0131 ve g\xfcvenli.\\n- **Geni\u015fletilmi\u015f Koruma:** WooCommerce sipari\u015f ID\'leri, \xf6deme detaylar\u0131 ve m\xfc\u015fteri meta verileri dahil olmak \xfczere **40\'tan fazla kritik meta anahtar** (`_mhm_` prefixli) koruma listesine eklendi.\\n- **Veri Kayb\u0131 \xd6nleme:** Bak\u0131m i\u015flemleri s\u0131ras\u0131nda yanl\u0131\u015fl\u0131kla veri silinmesinin \xf6n\xfcne ge\xe7mek i\xe7in koruma mekanizmalar\u0131 g\xfc\xe7lendirildi.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd12 SQL G\xfcvenli\u011fi (Hardening)\\nSistem genelinde SQL sorgular\u0131 g\xf6zden ge\xe7irildi ve g\xfcvenlik seviyesi art\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131.\\n- **Prepared Statements:** `BookingColumns` ve `ExportStats` s\u0131n\u0131flar\u0131ndaki dinamik sorgular, SQL Injection risklerine kar\u015f\u0131 `wpdb->prepare()` kullan\u0131larak standardize edildi.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udecd\ufe0f WooCommerce ve \xd6deme \u0130yile\u015ftirmeleri\\n\\n### \u269b\ufe0f Atomik \xc7ak\u0131\u015fma Kilidi (Atomic Overlap Lock)\\nYo\u011fun rezervasyon trafi\u011fi olan siteler i\xe7in hayati bir \xf6zellik eklendi.\\n- **\xc7ift Rezervasyon \xd6nleme:** WooCommerce \xfczerinden ayn\u0131 saniyede gelen rezervasyon isteklerinde \xe7ak\u0131\u015fmay\u0131 \xf6nlemek i\xe7in veritaban\u0131 seviyesinde atomik kilit mekanizmas\u0131 devreye al\u0131nd\u0131.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcb0 Vergi Hesaplama D\xfczeltmesi\\n- **Do\u011fru Vergi Matrah\u0131:** Depozito \xf6demelerinde verginin sadece \xf6denen depozito \xfczerinden de\u011fil, **toplam rezervasyon tutar\u0131** \xfczerinden hesaplanmas\u0131 sa\u011fland\u0131. Bu sayede faturaland\u0131rma ve muhasebe s\xfcre\xe7leri hatas\u0131z hale getirildi.\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfa8 Kullan\u0131c\u0131 Aray\xfcz\xfc\\n- **\xd6deme Ayarlar\u0131 Uyar\u0131s\u0131:** WooCommerce aktif oldu\u011funda, kullan\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131n yanl\u0131\u015f (lokal) \xf6deme ayarlar\u0131yla vakit kaybetmesini \xf6nlemek i\xe7in \\"\xd6deme i\u015flemleri WooCommerce taraf\u0131ndan y\xf6netilmektedir\\" \u015feklinde bilgilendirici bir uyar\u0131 eklendi.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Nas\u0131l G\xfcncellerim?**\\nWordPress y\xf6netim panelinizden **Eklentiler** sayfas\u0131n\u0131 ziyaret ederek g\xfcncellemeyi tek t\u0131kla y\xfckleyebilirsiniz. Bu s\xfcr\xfcm **Kritik** olarak i\u015faretlenmi\u015ftir, t\xfcm kullan\u0131c\u0131lar\u0131n en k\u0131sa s\xfcrede ge\xe7i\u015f yapmas\u0131 \xf6nerilir.\\n\\nG\xfcvenli ve keyifli kiralamalar! \ud83d\ude97\ud83d\udca8"},{"id":"v4-6-0-released","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-0-released","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-16-v4-6-0-released.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-16-v4-6-0-released.md","title":"v4.6.0 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.6.0 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, uzun zamand\u0131r beklenen VIP Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc, geli\u015fmi\u015f rota y\xf6netimi ve esnek fiyatland\u0131rma motoru gibi b\xfcy\xfck \xf6zellikler i\xe7eriyor.","date":"2026-01-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"v4.6.0","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/v-4-6-0"},{"inline":true,"label":"vip-transfer","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/vip-transfer"}],"readingTime":1.17,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4-6-0-released","title":"v4.6.0 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","v4.6.0","vip-transfer"],"date":"2026-01-16T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"v4.6.1 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-1-released"},"nextItem":{"title":"v4.5.5 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-5-5-released"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.6.0** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, uzun zamand\u0131r beklenen **VIP Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc**, geli\u015fmi\u015f rota y\xf6netimi ve esnek fiyatland\u0131rma motoru gibi b\xfcy\xfck \xf6zellikler i\xe7eriyor.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf1f \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kanlar\\n\\n### \ud83d\ude80 VIP Transfer Mod\xfcl\xfc (\u015eof\xf6rl\xfc Hizmet)\\nArt\u0131k sadece ara\xe7 kiralama de\u011fil, **VIP Transfer** hizmeti de verebilirsiniz!\\n- **Noktadan Noktaya Transfer:** Belirli lokasyonlar aras\u0131nda sabit veya mesafeye dayal\u0131 fiyatland\u0131rma.\\n- **\u015eof\xf6rl\xfc Ara\xe7 Kiralama:** Saatlik veya g\xfcnl\xfck \u015fof\xf6rl\xfc ara\xe7 opsiyonlar\u0131.\\n- **Ekstra Hizmetler:** Kar\u015f\u0131lama, bebek koltu\u011fu, ikramlar gibi ekstralar.\\n\\n### \ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f Rota ve Lokasyon Y\xf6netimi\\nAdmin panelinden detayl\u0131 **Rota Y\xf6netimi** yapabilirsiniz.\\n- Kalk\u0131\u015f ve Var\u0131\u015f noktalar\u0131 i\xe7in \xf6zel fiyatlar tan\u0131mlay\u0131n.\\n- \u0130ki nokta aras\u0131ndaki mesafeyi ve s\xfcreyi otomatik hesaplay\u0131n veya manuel girin.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udcb0 Esnek Fiyatland\u0131rma Motoru\\nTransferler i\xe7in geli\u015fmi\u015f fiyatland\u0131rma se\xe7enekleri:\\n- **Sabit Fiyat:** \\"Havaliman\u0131 -> \u015eehir Merkezi: 500 TL\\" gibi sabit rotalar olu\u015fturun.\\n- **Mesafe Bazl\u0131:** KM ba\u015f\u0131na \xfccretlendirme ile dinamik fiyatlar hesaplay\u0131n.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd0d Geli\u015fmi\u015f Transfer Arama\\nYeni **`[mhm_rentiva_transfer_search]`** k\u0131sa kodu ile web sitenize profesyonel bir transfer arama motoru ekleyin.\\n- Tarih, saat, kalk\u0131\u015f ve var\u0131\u015f noktas\u0131 se\xe7imi.\\n- Yolcu say\u0131s\u0131 ve bagaj kapasitesine g\xf6re ara\xe7 filtreleme.\\n\\n### \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Operasyonel Kontrol (Buffer Time)\\nAra\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131z\u0131n temizli\u011fi ve haz\u0131rl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\xe7in iki rezervasyon aras\u0131na otomatik **Tampon S\xfcre (Buffer Time)** ekleyebilirsiniz. Art\u0131k ara\xe7lar\u0131n\u0131z\u0131n \\"M\xfcsait\\" durumu daha ger\xe7ek\xe7i y\xf6netiliyor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltmeler ve \u0130yile\u015ftirmeler\\n\\n- **Cart & Payment:** WooCommerce sepet entegrasyonu \\"Depozito\\" veya \\"Tam \xd6deme\\" se\xe7enekleriyle g\xfc\xe7lendirildi.\\n- **Data Integrity:** Transfer detaylar\u0131 (kalk\u0131\u015f/var\u0131\u015f, yolcu say\u0131s\u0131) art\u0131k sipari\u015f notlar\u0131na ve meta verilerine eksiksiz kaydediliyor.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Nas\u0131l G\xfcncellerim?**\\nWordPress panelinizden otomatik g\xfcncelleme yapabilirsiniz. Herhangi bir sorun ya\u015farsan\u0131z l\xfctfen GitHub \xfczerinden veya destek sayfam\u0131zdan bize ula\u015f\u0131n.\\n\\nKeyifli s\xfcr\xfc\u015fler! \ud83c\udfce\ufe0f\ud83d\udca8"},{"id":"v4-5-5-released","metadata":{"permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-5-5-released","editUrl":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade/mhm-rentiva-docs/tree/main/blog/2026-01-15-v4-5-5-released.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-15-v4-5-5-released.md","title":"v4.5.5 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","description":"MHM Rentiva v4.5.5 s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, kararl\u0131l\u0131k iyile\u015ftirmeleri, kritik performans d\xfczeltmeleri ve dok\xfcmantasyon altyap\u0131s\u0131nda b\xfcy\xfck yenilikler i\xe7eriyor.","date":"2026-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"update","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/update"},{"inline":true,"label":"v4.5.5","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/tags/v-4-5-5"}],"readingTime":0.64,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"MaxHandMade","title":"Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade","imageURL":"https://github.com/MaxHandMade.png","key":"maxhandmade","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"v4-5-5-released","title":"v4.5.5 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","authors":["maxhandmade"],"tags":["release","update","v4.5.5"],"date":"2026-01-15T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"v4.6.0 Yay\u0131nda! \ud83d\ude80","permalink":"/mhm-rentiva-docs/blog/v4-6-0-released"}},"content":"MHM Rentiva **v4.5.5** s\xfcr\xfcm\xfc yay\u0131nland\u0131! Bu s\xfcr\xfcm, kararl\u0131l\u0131k iyile\u015ftirmeleri, kritik performans d\xfczeltmeleri ve dok\xfcmantasyon altyap\u0131s\u0131nda b\xfcy\xfck yenilikler i\xe7eriyor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf1f \xd6ne \xc7\u0131kanlar\\n\\n*   **G\xfcvenlik & Mimari:** Plugin kaynak kodlar\u0131 art\u0131k Private bir repoda korunurken, dok\xfcmantasyon (bu site) Public bir repoda herkesin eri\u015fimine a\xe7\u0131k hale getirildi.\\n*   **Performans:** Raporlama mod\xfcl\xfcndeki SQL sorgular\u0131, `DATE()` fonksiyonu kald\u0131r\u0131larak indeks kullan\u0131m\u0131na uygun hale getirildi. Art\u0131k \xe7ok daha h\u0131zl\u0131 \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor.\\n*   **Mobil Uyumluluk:** Ara\xe7 detay sayfalar\u0131 mobilde art\u0131k ta\u015fma yapm\u0131yor, butonlar ve g\xf6rseller tam uyumlu.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f D\xfczeltmeler\\n\\n*   **Fixed:** `Plugin.php` i\xe7indeki m\xfckerrer kodlar temizlendi.\\n*   **Fixed:** `ReportRepository` s\u0131n\u0131f\u0131ndaki yava\u015f sorgular optimize edildi.\\n*   **Fixed:** Ara\xe7 k\u0131yaslama sayfas\u0131ndaki hizalama sorunlar\u0131 giderildi.\\n*   **Fixed:** \\"Hizmete Kapal\u0131\\" (Out of Use) etiketi art\u0131k varyasyonlu \xfcr\xfcnlerde de do\u011fru \xe7al\u0131\u015f\u0131yor.\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Y\xfckseltme\\n\\nWordPress panelinizden otomatik g\xfcncelleme yapabilirsiniz. Herhangi bir sorun ya\u015farsan\u0131z l\xfctfen GitHub \xfczerinden veya destek sayfam\u0131zdan bize ula\u015f\u0131n.\\n\\nKeyifli kiralamalar! \ud83d\ude97\ud83d\udca8"}]}}')}}]);